#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:11
msgid "Master Rule Book Foreword"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:15
msgid ""
"This rule book is a consolidation of all the rules for <i>Space Empires "
"4X, Close Encounters, Replicators,</i> and <i>All Good Things</i>. All "
"expansions are necessary to take advantage of all the options found here."
" References to the Competitive Scenario Book (CSB) and the Solo/Co-Op "
"Scenario Book (SSB) will be notated accordingly, e.g., (SSB 8.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:22
msgid "Game Overview"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:26
msgid ""
"<i>Space Empires</i> is a classic \"4X\" game: eXplore, eXpand, eXploit, "
"and eXterminate. Each player will grow a space Empire and will attempt to"
" win by eliminating other players. The time scale of this game is very "
"large – at least an Earth year in-between Economic Phases. The Scenario "
"Books provide game setup details and additional rules based on the chosen"
" scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:33
msgid "Base Rules and Optional Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:37
msgid ""
"If you have made it this far in the series, there is little need to roll "
"rules out slowly. These are organized into Base Rules, which I (Jim "
"Krohn) recommend always playing with (with experienced players), and "
"Optional Rules which can be added in for flavor or change of pace. Not "
"all Optional Rules are created equal. For instance, I rarely play with "
"Unique Ships (while for other players they are considered a must), I "
"sometimes play with Resource Cards, and I often play with Alternate "
"Empires. <strong>Play the game anyway you want using the rules that you "
"like the most!</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:44
msgid "Glossary of Commonly Used Terms:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:48
msgid ""
"<strong>Colonize:</strong> The process of putting a Colony on a planet in"
" the Movement Phase (4.4) or Combat Phases ([5.10.3], [21.13]) and "
"continuing that process in the Economic Phase (7.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:49
msgid ""
"<strong>Combat-Capable Units:</strong> These include all units with an "
"Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:50
msgid ""
"<strong>Construction Point (CP):</strong> Homeworlds and Colonies produce"
" Construction Points. Construction Points are used in the Economic Phase "
"to purchase units, maintain spaceships, and develop technology. A "
"Production Sheet has been provided to facilitate keeping track of CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:51
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\"><strong>Deep Space:</strong> Non-Home System "
"hexes where Deep Space system markers are placed at the start of the "
"game.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:52
msgid ""
"<strong>Enemy:</strong> A unit that is an opponent to a given player. "
"This includes Alien ships ([18.0], [SSB 4.0]), Doomsday Machines ([29.0],"
" [SSB 2.0]), and Amoebas ([SSB 3.0], [CSB 10.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:53
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\"><strong>Fleet:</strong> All ships belonging to "
"one Empire within a hex.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:54
msgid ""
"<strong>Group:</strong> One to six units of the same type and technology "
"level, represented by a Group counter (2.3). Counters do not always "
"represent single units, but have a numeral marker stacked underneath them"
" to indicate the number of units in that Group (from one to six). Colony "
"Ships, Miners, and MS Pipelines are the only exceptions to this rule as "
"they always represent a single ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:55
msgid ""
"<strong>Home System:</strong> A group of hexes where the Homeworld (2.8) "
"and Home System markers (2.1) are placed during set up."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:56
msgid ""
"<strong>Non-Combat Units:</strong> These units have no Attack Strength "
"and include Colony Ships, Miners, MS Pipelines and Decoys."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:57
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\"><strong>Non-Player Alien (NPA):</strong> Combat "
"ships that defend Deep Space barren planets.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:58
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\"><strong>Permanent Terrain:</strong> System "
"Markers that stay in the hex in which they are revealed (Planets, "
"Asteroids, Black Holes, etc).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:59
msgid ""
"<strong>Ships (Spaceships):</strong> Other than non-Group ships (2.6), "
"ships are always represented by a Group counter, even if only one ship is"
" present (don't be thrown by the term \"Group\")."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:60
msgid ""
"<strong>System:</strong> A vast zone of space, represented in this game "
"by a single hex printed on the game board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:61
msgid ""
"<strong>Unit:</strong> Ship, Ground Unit, Decoy, Miner, Colony Ship, MS "
"Pipeline, Shipyard, Base, <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbase, Missile, or "
"Defense Satellite Network.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:68
#, fuzzy
msgid "BASE RULES"
msgstr "Phase"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:77
msgid "Playing Pieces"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:81
msgid ""
"<i>Each player should pick a color to represent their Empire and will "
"receive System and Group counters of their color.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:88
msgid "System Markers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:92
msgid ""
"At setup, sort the System markers according to the border printed on "
"their back. The markers with white borders are Deep Space. The markers "
"with colored borders will populate each player's stellar neighborhood, "
"called the \"Home System.\" The red player will have red-bordered System "
"markers in their Home System, and so forth. System markers must be placed"
" randomly; their front-sides should remain unknown to all players. Turn "
"all the markers with the same-colored border face down, carefully mix "
"them, and randomly place them on the map board, one in each hex, inside "
"their Home System. <mark class=\"hl-blue\"><i>Note: eight additional Home"
" System markers have been provided for each color. These are marked with "
"a \"v\" on the front side. They should not be used unless using the "
"Variable Home System Set Up (CSB 1.1.13).</i></mark> The white System "
"markers occupy the hexes between the Home Systems of the players. Set "
"aside any unused white System markers as they will not be needed. See the"
" Scenario Books for the exact details of setup for each scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:99
msgid "Planets"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:103
msgid ""
"Planets have no effect on play until colonized (4.4.1). Terraforming "
"technology is required for colonizing Barren Planets (9.7). Barren "
"Planets in Deep Space are inhabited by uncooperative aliens (18.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:110
msgid "Groups"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:114
msgid ""
"Group counters have pictures of units on them and represent 1-6 units of "
"the same type and technology level. Place a numeral marker underneath the"
" Group counter to indicate the number of units in the Group. Units of the"
" same type and technology may join and leave Groups as they choose at any"
" time (as counters allow). Group counters have two sides – the back side "
"is used to hide the unit's type and combat information. Group counters "
"and their numeral markers start with their identity hidden from other "
"players and are only revealed in combat. Some Replicator (40.0) Group "
"counters have a 1 in the upper-right corner to indicate that they have "
"Tactics 1 technology (9.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:121
msgid "Type"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:125
msgid ""
"The unit type is indicated by the large letters in the upper-left corner "
"of the counter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:132
msgid "Weapon Class"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:136
msgid ""
"This letter is used in determining which unit fires first in combat (an "
"A-Class fires first in combat before a B-Class)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:143
msgid "Attack Strength"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:147
msgid ""
"The number needed to score a hit (a 4 means a player must roll a 4 or "
"less to hit a target)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:154
msgid "Defense Strength"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:158
msgid ""
"Defense Strength is the number printed next to the Attack Strength. For "
"example, a Cruiser has a Defense Strength of 1. This number is subtracted"
" from the attacker's Attack Strength, so the higher this number the "
"harder it is to hit the unit in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:165
msgid "Hull Size (aka Ship Size)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:169
msgid ""
"Hull Size is the number after the \"x\". Measured in Hull Points, it "
"indicates the number of hits required to destroy a unit in the Group. For"
" example, a Cruiser's Hull Size is \"2\", which means that two hits "
"destroy one Cruiser. Hull Size also determines the maintenance cost of a "
"unit, the level of technology it can utilize, and the construction "
"capacity needed to build it at a Shipyard. Notice that the Hull Size is "
"printed on the Group counter, but it applies to each unit within that "
"Group. Ground Units don't have Hulls, but for simplicity's sake they use "
"the same metric."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:176
msgid "Group Identification Number"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:180
msgid "Use this number to identify the Group on the Ship Technology Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:187
msgid "Numeral Markers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:191
msgid ""
"Each Group in play must have ONE of these stacked underneath it to "
"indicate the number of units represented by the Group counter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:192
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If there are two Cruisers with the same tech level in a "
"Cruiser Group, place a \"2\" numeral marker underneath the CA Group "
"counter. Even if only a single unit is in a Group, place a \"1\" numeral "
"marker underneath it. Other players won't know how many spaceships are in"
" that Group.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:199
msgid "Fleet Markers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:203
msgid ""
"To help with crowding, three Fleet Markers have been provided for each "
"Empire. Fleet Displays are kept in clear view of all players. Any number "
"of a player's units may be placed on their Fleet Display and represented "
"by the corresponding Fleet Marker on the map. In all ways, a counter on a"
" player's Fleet Display is considered in the hex with the Fleet marker."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:210
msgid "Non-Group Units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:214
msgid ""
"Colony Ships, MS Pipelines, and Miners are non-Group units. They always "
"represent a single ship – never place a numeral marker underneath them, "
"and always place them face up."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:221
msgid "Damage Markers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:225
msgid ""
"Place damage markers on top of a Group to keep track of the hits applied "
"to this Group during the Combat Phase (5.6). These are removed at the "
"conclusion of the Combat Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:232
msgid "Homeworlds"
msgstr "Bonjour le Monde !"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:236
msgid ""
"A Homeworld represents the player's home planet plus possible "
"installations on moons and planets within the same solar system. Each "
"player starts with one Homeworld from which they will explore the galaxy."
" A Homeworld produces 30 CP each Economic Phase. The 20 CP Homeworld "
"counter should be used when playing with the optional rules for "
"Facilities (36.0). Except as noted, rules that apply to Colonies also "
"apply to Homeworlds."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:243
msgid "Colony Number Counters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:247
msgid ""
"These are numbered counters with the word \"Colony\" on them and are "
"placed on top of Colonies to track Colony growth on a planet. Several of "
"these are marked with the word \"Home\"; use them only when a Homeworld "
"takes damage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:254
msgid "Additional Counters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:258
msgid ""
"Counters that are labeled DYO on their revealed side are to cover "
"lost/damaged counters or to allow the players to add their own "
"unit/terrain rules to the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:265
msgid "Dice"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:269
msgid ""
"The game comes with 10-sided dice which are used for all rolls in the "
"game. On these dice, a 0 represents a 10."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:276
msgid "Sequence of Play"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:280
msgid ""
"For the first turn of the game, players roll a die to determine first "
"player; player order proceeds clockwise around the map board. After the "
"first three turns (B, C, D, below), Player Order is determined by bidding"
" in the Economic Phase (7.4). The Sequence of Play is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:281
msgid "<strong>A. Determine Player Order (First Turn Only – see above.)</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:282
msgid "<strong>B. Turn One:</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:283
msgid "<strong><i>Player 1:</i></strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:284
msgid "a. Movement Phase (4.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:285
msgid "b. Combat Phase (5.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:286
msgid "c. Exploration Phase (6.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:287
msgid "<strong><i>Players 2-4:</i></strong> Same as Player 1"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:288
msgid "<strong>C. Turn Two: (same as turn one)</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:289
msgid "<strong>D. Turn Three: (same as turn one)</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:290
msgid ""
"<strong>E. Economic Phase:</strong> All players conduct this phase "
"simultaneously, not in player order (7.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:291
msgid ""
"Keep track of the current turn using the Turn marker and the Turn Track "
"printed on the game board. After the Economic Phase, the Turn marker is "
"reset to 1. Continue until a winner is determined."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:298
msgid "Movement Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:307
msgid "Movement Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:311
msgid ""
"Units move from System to adjacent System (from hex to adjacent hex). The"
" distance a unit can move is determined by its level of Movement "
"technology, and is measured in hexes. Units may be moved separately or "
"together. All players start the game at Movement technology level 1. This"
" means each unit may move only one hex during the Movement Phase of each "
"turn. If a player develops their Movement technology during the Economic "
"Phase (7.5), they increase the number of hexes each ship may move in a "
"turn, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:312
msgid ""
"- Level 2: 1 hex in each of the first two turns, 2 hexes in the third "
"turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:313
msgid ""
"- Level 3: 1 hex in the first turn, 2 hexes in each of the second and "
"third turns."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:314
msgid "- Level 4: 2 hexes in all three turns."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:315
msgid ""
"- Level 5: 2 hexes in each of the first two turns, 3 hexes in the third "
"turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:316
msgid ""
"- Level 6: 2 hexes in the first turn, 3 hexes in each of the second and "
"third turns."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:317
msgid "- Level 7: 3 hexes in all three turns."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:324 app/data/master_rule_book.py:514
msgid "Non-Combat Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:328
msgid ""
"Regardless of a player's Movement technology level, these ships (8.4, "
"8.5, 13.1) move only 1 hex each turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:335 app/data/master_rule_book.py:1216
msgid "Decoys"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:339
msgid ""
"Decoys (8.3) always move at the speed of the current Movement technology "
"level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:346
msgid "Non-Moving Units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:350
msgid ""
"Bases (8.1), <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases (38.5), Defense Satellite "
"Networks (14.0)</mark>, and Shipyards (8.2) cannot move."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:357 app/data/master_rule_book.py:2086
msgid "Movement Restrictions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:361
msgid ""
"A unit may not enter a hex with a face down (unexplored) System marker, a"
" Nebula, or Asteroids unless it starts its turn adjacent to it and moves "
"into that hex as its first move. Also, entering a hex with any of these "
"markers ends that unit's movement, regardless of its Movement technology "
"level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:362
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Group that could move two hexes begins the Movement Phase "
"adjacent to a hex with an Asteroids marker. It may enter the hex but must"
" stop after doing so.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:363
msgid ""
"Non-combat ships (5.4) may not enter a hex with a face down (unexplored) "
"System marker, enemy unit, or enemy Colony unless a combat-capable ship "
"also enters that hex (it need not have started in the same location)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:370
msgid "Enemy-Occupied Hexes"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:374
msgid ""
"Units must immediately stop all movement when entering a hex containing "
"enemy combat capable units and attack them during the Combat Phase. If a "
"unit enters a System containing only enemy non-combat capable ships, "
"those defenseless ships are immediately destroyed and do not impede "
"movement or reveal ships (or technology; 9.10); the moving (attacking) "
"units may continue moving. Combat capable units may ignore enemy Colonies"
" on a planet and pass through the hex or stay in the hex. If a unit ends "
"its move in a hex with an enemy Colony, the unit may attack during the "
"Combat Phase (5.10)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:381
msgid "Planets & Colonization"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:385
msgid ""
"A planet without a Colony on it has no effect on movement. A non-"
"colonized planet may be colonized by a Colony Ship (8.4). A colonized "
"planet may not be colonized again until the existing Colony is destroyed "
"([5.10.3], [21.9])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:392
msgid "Initiating Colonization"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:396
msgid ""
"Place the Colony Ship (ship side up) on the planet marker. A player may "
"do this at any point during their turn if there are no non-cloaked (16.0)"
" enemy units in the same hex as the colony ship and empty planet. Once "
"colonization is announced in this way, the Colony Ship may no longer "
"move. It has begun the process of forming a Colony and has dismantled "
"itself for the raw material needed to start the process. From this point "
"on, it is considered a Colony. Colonization takes time and the Colony "
"will grow in future Economic Phases (7.7)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:403
msgid "Colonizing Barren Planets"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:407
msgid ""
"Some planets are labeled \"Barren.\" They may not be colonized without "
"Terraforming technology (9.7). Once a Barren Planet is colonized, the "
"planet functions like any other planet. It delivers resources and grows "
"just like other planets. If a Colony on a Barren Planet is destroyed, the"
" planet immediately reverts to a Barren Planet. If playing with Alien "
"Technology cards, see [11.0]."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:414
msgid "Combat Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:423
msgid "Combat Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:427
msgid ""
"Combat occurs during the Combat Phase whenever opposing units (enemies) "
"are in the same hex. Combat is mandatory and takes place within a hex. "
"The units which moved into the hex and initiated combat are the "
"attackers, while the opposing units are referred to as the defenders. "
"Both the attacking and defending units may fire, often more than once, "
"and combat continues until only one side has units remaining in the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:428
msgid ""
"There is no three-way combat in this game. If a player moves into a hex "
"with units from two different sides, they may pick which one they want to"
" engage first. Only units that survive/remain in the hex may be used in "
"the second battle. Damage is removed between battles."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:429
msgid ""
"If multiple combats are initiated during the same turn the active player "
"decides the order in which they are resolved."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:436
msgid "Move Units Off Map"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:440
msgid ""
"If a Decoy is present (8.3), it is eliminated before any combat takes "
"place (if a side only has Decoys, the other side doesn't have to reveal "
"their units). Take all units in the System temporarily to a convenient "
"area off the playing board. Alternatively, players may use the Battle "
"Board (37.4.2). Mark the System in which the battle takes place with the "
"Battle marker as a reminder. The attacker and defender both reveal and "
"arrange their units in \"battle lines\". Each line should be organized "
"according to Weapon Class (A-Class at one end, B-Class next to A-Class, "
"etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:447
msgid "Determine Combat Screening"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:451
msgid ""
"Next, each side counts the number of combat-capable units involved in the"
" battle, including Bases (8.1), <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases (38.5),"
" Defense Satellite Networks (14.0)</mark>, and Shipyards (8.2). The side "
"with the greater number of combat-capable units has the option of Combat "
"Screening (5.7)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:458
msgid "Determine Fleet Size Bonus"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:462
msgid ""
"If a player has twice as many unscreened, combat-capable units as their "
"opponent, their firing units enjoy a +1 bonus to their Attack Strengths. "
"Determine this Fleet Size Bonus at the start of each firing round. It is "
"possible that as a battle progresses, and units are destroyed or retreat,"
" the size differential will change, so that the side who enjoys this "
"bonus at the start of combat may lose it in a later round, and vice "
"versa. Note that the smaller side is not penalized in its fire. Mines "
"(17.1) do not count towards Fleet Size in any way. Bases, <mark class"
"=\"hl-blue\">Starbases, Defense Satellite Networks,</mark> and Shipyards "
"count towards this bonus."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:469
msgid "Resolve Combat"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:473
msgid ""
"Combat is resolved starting with the A-Class units, progressing to the "
"B-Class units, and so forth in descending order, until all units have had"
" the opportunity to fire. No unit may fire more than once in a combat "
"round but can be a target more than once."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:480
msgid "Repeat if Necessary"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:484
msgid ""
"If both the attacker and defender still have units in the hex after a "
"round of combat, perform another round of combat starting with the Combat"
" Screening step (5.7). Combat may last any number of rounds. After the "
"first round is completed a unit which has an opportunity to fire at a "
"target may retreat instead (5.9)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:491
msgid "Firing Order"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:495
msgid ""
"Combat fire is never simultaneous. A-Class units fire before B-Class "
"units, B-Class units fire before C-Class units, etc. If multiple groups "
"with the same firing class are present the Group with the highest Tactics"
" technology fires first. If the Weapon Class and Tactics technology of "
"multiple Groups are the same then the Defender's Groups fire first. If "
"the Groups belong to the same player, that player decides which of their "
"Groups fires first, but must resolve the entire fire by one Group before "
"moving to the next. If combat is taking place in a System with Asteroids "
"or a Nebula (5.8), all ships except for Boarding Ships (19.0) are "
"considered E-Class regardless of what is printed on the counters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:496
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-purple\"><strong>PLAY NOTE:</strong> It is possible for "
"all of one player's units to fire before their opponent has a chance to "
"roll the dice. It is also possible for a ship to be destroyed before it "
"fires even once. Developing a higher Tactics technology than your "
"opponent can be critical.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:503
msgid "Who May Fire"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:507
msgid ""
"Only combat-capable units may fire. A unit may fire at any enemy unit in "
"the same hex except units that are screened (5.7). If units are part of "
"the same Group, they may fire individually and at different targets. A "
"unit may always decide not to fire. Fighter Squadrons (15.2) may also "
"fire and they do so independently of their Carriers (15.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:518
msgid "Decoys are eliminated before any combat takes place."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:519
msgid ""
"Colony Ships, Miners, and MS Pipelines may not retreat and are "
"automatically destroyed if alone or if all accompanying friendly combat-"
"capable units are eliminated or retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:526
msgid "Fire Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:530
msgid ""
"Select a firing unit and a target. Add the firing unit's Attack Strength "
"to its Attack technology level (9.2). The sum is the total Attack "
"Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:531
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Cruiser's Attack Strength is 4, and if it has an Attack "
"technology level of 1, the total Attack Strength is 5.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:532
msgid ""
"Increase the Attack Strength by one (+1) if the Fleet Size Bonus is "
"applicable (5.1.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:533
msgid ""
"Next, add the target's Defense Strength to its Defense technology level "
"and subtract this sum from the total Attack Strength to get the \"To "
"Hit\" number. The attacking side rolls a die for each unit in the Group "
"that is firing on the target. Dice may be rolled one at a time for each "
"unit and the result seen before deciding on the target for the next unit."
" For each die rolled, if the die roll is equal to or less than the number"
" needed to hit, a hit is scored. Regardless of the number needed to hit, "
"a roll of 1 will always score a hit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:534
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If a target has a Defense Strength of 1 and a Defense "
"technology level of 1, 2 is subtracted from the total Attack Strength. If"
" the Cruiser from the above example is the firing unit, it would need to "
"roll a 3 or less to score a hit.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:535
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-beige\"><strong>Important:</strong> The Attack and "
"Defense technology modification may not normally exceed a unit's Hull "
"Size (9.2).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:542
msgid "Recording Hits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:546
msgid ""
"Damage is cumulative and is recorded by placing Damage markers near the "
"Group counter during battle. When a unit receives hits equal to its Hull "
"Size, it is destroyed. Adjust the numeral marker under the Group counter "
"to reflect the loss of the unit, and if the Group only had one unit, "
"remove the Group counter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:547
msgid ""
"Two or more units in the same Group may not have damage applied to them "
"at the same time; all damage must be applied to a single unit, and only "
"after it is destroyed may subsequent damage be applied to another unit in"
" the same Group. Outside of this restriction the firing player may select"
" which unit in the group to target."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:548
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: Cruiser Group 1 has two Cruisers, which can each sustain two "
"hits before being destroyed. Therefore, at the start of combat, there is "
"a marker with a number 2 under the Group counter. During combat a hit was"
" scored on one of the Cruisers, so a 1 Damage marker is placed on top of "
"the counter to record the hit. Later, a second hit was scored on the same"
" Cruiser. The Damage marker currently marking the first hit is removed, "
"while the numeral marker underneath the Group counter is flipped to 1 to "
"show that only one Cruiser remains in the Group. If the Cruiser is later "
"destroyed, the Group counter and its numeral marker will be removed.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:549
msgid ""
"Unless there are enough hits to destroy a target, hits do not affect "
"performance in any way. If otherwise able, a damaged unit may be split "
"off into a separate Group and may retreat (5.9) or be screened (5.7). At "
"the conclusion of combat, if a unit has hits but is not destroyed, the "
"hits are removed. Thus, units are considered automatically repaired after"
" combat (the turns represent a long period of time in which the crew can "
"repair the damage)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:550
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Battleship in BB Group 2 suffers two hits in combat. After "
"the last enemy ship retreats to conclude combat, the Damage marker is "
"removed.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:557
msgid "Combat Screening"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:561
msgid ""
"At the start of each firing round, if a player has more combat-capable "
"units than their opponent, they may choose to screen a number of units up"
" to the difference. Screening combat units is always voluntary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:562
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If the attacker has 10 combat-capable units and the defender "
"has 5, the attacker may screen as many as 5 combat-capable units.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:569
msgid "Select Units to Screen"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:573
msgid ""
"Before rolling the dice to resolve firing, set aside any units chosen to "
"be screened; they may not fire or be fired upon that round. They may "
"retreat, but only when it is their turn to do so (5.9). A combat-capable "
"unit that is screened cannot be fired on for the round even if the units "
"screening it are destroyed or retreat. Players are allowed to change the "
"composition of their screened units at the start of each round of combat "
"so that units that fired in the first round may be screened in a later "
"round and vice-versa."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:574
msgid ""
"All non-combat ships (5.4) are automatically screened until the end of "
"the battle, even if the player has less combat-capable units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:581
msgid "Exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:585
msgid ""
"Players cannot screen against a Doomsday Machine (29.0) or Space Amoeba "
"([SSB 3.0]/[CSB 10.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:592
msgid "Special Conditions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:601
msgid "Asteroids"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:605
msgid ""
"If combat is occurring in a System with an Asteroids marker, the Attack "
"technology level of all units in the combat is considered zero, "
"regardless of the player's technology level. In addition, all units in "
"the combat are considered to be E-Class, regardless of what is printed on"
" their counters. This represents the extra protection provided by the "
"Asteroids and the difficulty involved in bringing longer ranged and more "
"advanced weapons to bear in the middle of an asteroid belt. Note that a "
"unit's base Attack Strength is unaffected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:612
msgid "Nebulae"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:616
msgid ""
"If combat is occurring in a System with a Nebula marker, the Defense "
"technology level of all units in the combat is considered zero, "
"regardless of the player's technology level. In addition, all units in "
"the combat are considered to be E-Class, regardless of what is printed on"
" their counters. This represents the nebula wreaking havoc on the unit's "
"defensive systems. Note that a unit's base Defense Strength is "
"unaffected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:623
msgid "Additional Effects"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:627
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">See Additional Terrain (25.0) for more combat "
"effects.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:634
msgid "Retreats"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:638
msgid ""
"Retreat is a voluntary action. After the first round, a unit that can "
"move may choose to retreat instead of firing when it would be its regular"
" turn to fire. Retreat may require a player to place a new Group counter "
"on the game board (that is, if one ship in a Group retreats, leaving the "
"rest of the Group in the hex). Non-combat ships (5.4), Bases (8.1), <mark"
" class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases (38.5), Defense Satellite Networks "
"(14.0)</mark>, Shipyards (8.2), Titans (22.0), and <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">Missiles (24.4)</mark> may not retreat. Retreats may not be "
"conducted after all enemy space combat-capable ships have been destroyed "
"or have retreated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:645
msgid "Retreat Location"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:649
msgid "A retreating spaceship must:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:650
msgid "- Be shifted to an adjacent System."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:651
msgid "- The hex may not contain any enemy units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:652
msgid "- It may not be an unexplored System or a Super Nova (6.5)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:653
msgid ""
"- It may retreat into a Black Hole hex (6.3) but may not use Black Hole "
"Slingshot (31.0) during the retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:654
msgid ""
"- It must retreat into a System that is <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">closer</mark> to one of its Colonies than the hex that it is "
"retreating from; this does not need to be the closest Colony. Closeness "
"is determined counting hexes and ignoring intervening terrain and units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:655
msgid "- If no legal retreat exists, the ship may not retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:662
msgid "Colonies & Combat"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:671 app/data/master_rule_book.py:956
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1052 app/data/master_rule_book.py:1116
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1149 app/data/master_rule_book.py:2222
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2627 app/data/master_rule_book.py:3665
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3718 app/data/master_rule_book.py:4114
msgid "Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:675
msgid ""
"A ship in a System occupied by an enemy Colony may attack the Colony only"
" after space combat is resolved in the hex. If all enemy units have "
"either been destroyed, have retreated, or decided to remain cloaked, the "
"Colony may be fired upon. Each Colony ship may only fire once at the "
"Colony per turn, and the Colony may not return fire. An attacking ship "
"may fire at a Colony only during its Combat Phase (not during the Combat "
"Phase of the Colony owner's turn). Each Colony has a Defense Strength of "
"zero and no Defense technology (but see [21.6] if playing with Ground "
"Units). Only an attacking ship's Attack Strength and Attack technology "
"are used for the purpose of determining the chance of hitting. No Fleet "
"Size Bonus (5.1.3) is applied during Colony combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:682
msgid "Effect of Hits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:686
msgid ""
"A hit reduces the Colony one step. A Colony with 5 CP is reduced to 3 CP,"
" a 3 CP Colony is stepped down to 1 CP, and a 1 CP Colony that receives a"
" hit is removed (the planet may be colonized by another Colony Ship). A "
"newly colonized planet (the Colony Ship has been placed on the planet but"
" has not yet been flipped to the Colony side) also requires one hit to "
"destroy. If a Homeworld is hit, instead of using the 3 CP and 1 CP "
"markers, it reduces in value in increments of five. Thus, the first hit "
"reduces it to 25 CP, another hit reduces it to 20 CP, and so on. A "
"Homeworld marked with a 5 CP marker is destroyed if it takes a hit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:693
msgid "Damaged Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:697
msgid ""
"Reduced Colonies function normally. They provide CP (as indicated on the "
"marker) and grow during the Economic Phase. If reduced completely (i.e., "
"destroyed), the planet may be colonized again. If the attacking player "
"has a Colony Ship in the hex, it may immediately initiate colonization "
"(4.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:704
msgid "Post-Combat"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:708
msgid ""
"Groups revealed in combat are now returned to the map but remain face up "
"and may be examined, along with their numeral markers, by other players "
"at any time. If Groups start their turn in the same hex as one of their "
"Colonies, they may be flipped face down (hiding their numeral marker "
"also) before being moved (if able) and remain that way until they once "
"again engage in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:715
msgid "Exploration"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:719
msgid ""
"Except for the players' Homeworlds, all Systems are unexplored at the "
"start of the game. This is indicated by the placement of face-down System"
" markers during setup."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:726
msgid "Exploration Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:730
msgid ""
"If a unit shares a hex with a face-down (unexplored) System marker during"
" the Exploration Phase, it must explore that System. Flip the marker over"
" and reveal its identity to all players. Apply effects immediately. "
"Cruisers can be equipped with Exploration technology (9.8), which allows "
"them to explore during the Movement Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:737
msgid "Planets, Nebulae, Asteroids"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:741
msgid "These markers remain in the hex and affect future game play."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:742
msgid "- Planets: Can be colonized (4.4)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:743
msgid "- Nebulae, Asteroids: Affect movement (4.2) & combat (5.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:750
msgid "Black Holes"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:754
msgid ""
"Any ship that moves or explores into a hex containing a Black Hole must "
"momentarily pause movement to check for survival. Each ship in a Group "
"must be checked individually for survival. On a roll of 1-6 the ship "
"survives; on a roll of 7-10, it is destroyed. This die roll is made the "
"instant a ship enters a Black Hole. Ships that begin their Movement Phase"
" in a Black Hole do not have to roll again, unless they move out of the "
"Black Hole and back in. If the ship survives its encounter with the Black"
" Hole, it may continue moving (Movement technology level permitting). The"
" Black Hole remains in the hex for the rest of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:755
msgid ""
"Fighters (15.2) and Ground Units (21.2) do not have to roll for survival "
"when entering the hex of a Black Hole and are only eliminated if the "
"surviving ships do not have the capacity to carry them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:762
msgid "Danger!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:766
msgid ""
"Space is dangerous, especially the unexplored bits of it. When this "
"marker is revealed, all units in the hex are destroyed. The marker is "
"then removed from play. The hex remains empty."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:773
msgid "Super Nova"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:777
msgid ""
"A Super Nova dominates this sector of space. A unit revealing the Super "
"Nova must immediately retreat to the hex it just left. The Super Nova "
"remains in the hex for the rest of the game. No unit may move or retreat "
"into this System."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:784
msgid "Lost in Space"
msgstr "Sauvegardée le"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:788
msgid ""
"When a unit reveals this marker, the player to the right of the revealing"
" player immediately shifts the unit one hex in any direction. If more "
"than one unit is in the hex, all the units present must be shifted "
"together as a stack. If units are placed in a hex with an unrevealed "
"System marker, that marker must immediately be explored. After shifting "
"units out of the hex, the Lost in Space marker is removed, and the hex "
"remains empty."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:795 app/data/master_rule_book.py:4945
msgid "Minerals"
msgstr "Parties"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:799
msgid "<i>Precious resources vital to industry.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:806 app/data/master_rule_book.py:850
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1236 app/data/master_rule_book.py:1822
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1853 app/data/master_rule_book.py:2352
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3305 app/data/master_rule_book.py:3424
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4030
msgid "Characteristics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:810
msgid ""
"This marker has no effect on movement or combat and remains in the hex "
"until towed away by a Mining Ship (8.5). Minerals may not be voluntarily "
"destroyed. If towed to a Colony or Homeworld, the Mineral marker is "
"removed from the game in the Economic Phase and generates a one-time CP "
"bonus equal to the value printed on the marker (7.2) as long as the "
"Colony or Homeworld is not blockaded (7.1.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:817
msgid "Towing Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:821
msgid ""
"Only a Mining Ship may tow a Mineral marker. A Mining Ship may only carry"
" one Mineral marker at a time. To signify towing, place the marker on top"
" of the ship towing it; the marker moves with the Mining Ship. There is "
"no cost to do this, and it may be done at any time. When the ship and its"
" Mineral marker reach a Homeworld or Colony (even a new one), the Mineral"
" may be deposited on the planet where it will remain until the Economic "
"Phase. Any number of Mineral markers may be deposited on the same "
"colonized planet. A Mineral marker, once towed by a Mining Ship, will "
"leave a hex empty. A Mining Ship may not dump its cargo in space in order"
" to pick up a better Mineral or a Space Wreck."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:828 app/data/master_rule_book.py:862
msgid "Destroyed"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:832
msgid ""
"If a Mining Ship is destroyed while towing a Mineral marker, the Mineral "
"is destroyed as well. Likewise, if a Colony with a Mineral marker is "
"destroyed or captured, the Mineral marker is also destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:839
msgid "Space Wreck"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:843
msgid "<i>A derelict spacecraft from an advanced civilization.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:854
msgid ""
"A Space Wreck may be towed to a Homeworld or Colony (even a new one) by a"
" Mining Ship just as if it were a Mineral marker (6.7.2). Instead of a CP"
" bonus, it earns the player a free technology upgrade during the Economic"
" Phase (7.2). To determine which technology is upgraded, roll a die and "
"consult the Space Wreck Technology table on page 48."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:855
msgid ""
"If the technology rolled by the player is already at the maximum level in"
" that category, the upgrade is wasted. Regardless of the result, remove "
"the Space Wreck from the game at the end of the Economic Phase. Space "
"Wrecks may not be voluntarily destroyed. A Mining Ship may not dump a "
"Space Wreck in space in order to pick up a Mineral marker."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:866
msgid ""
"If a Mining Ship is destroyed while towing a Space Wreck marker, the "
"Space Wreck is destroyed as well. Likewise, if a Colony with a Space "
"Wreck marker is destroyed or captured, the Space Wreck marker is also "
"destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:873
msgid "Other Deep Space Discoveries"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:877
msgid ""
"Additional Terrain (25.0) and Optional Deep Space Discoveries (28.0) add "
"variety to Deep Space exploration. If not playing with a particular "
"Terrain type, remove them before set up or, when its marker is flipped, "
"remove the marker from play."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:884
msgid "Using the Terrain Tiles"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:888
msgid ""
"When a permanent terrain is revealed during exploration, replace that "
"counter with the appropriate terrain tile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:895
msgid "Home System Planets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:899
msgid ""
"While Home System planets are permanent terrain, they are only replaced "
"by the terrain tile once a Colony is started on them. This is because "
"these tiles have a 5 CP/Full Colony counter printed on them. Once a "
"Colony is placed, the Colony growth counter will be placed over the Full "
"counter. If the Colony is subsequently destroyed, replace the terrain "
"tile with the original System marker. If a player colonizes a planet in "
"the home space of another player, place that player's Colony marker over "
"the artwork on the tile. The exception to this is the Barren Planet in "
"each Home System, which sometimes never gets colonized; this tile has an "
"uncolonized side."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:906
msgid "Asteroids and Planet Destruction"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:910
msgid ""
"Asteroids are on the back of most planet tiles in case the planet gets "
"destroyed by a Titan (22.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:917
msgid "Epic Scenarios"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:921
msgid ""
"Most non-planet tiles have empty space on the back. Twelve of them would "
"be needed to connect two Space Empires boards together for Epic Scenarios"
" (CSB 8.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:928
msgid "Economic Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:932
msgid ""
"The Economic Phase takes place at the end of every third turn. This phase"
" consists of a sequence of tasks that the players perform secretly and "
"simultaneously:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:933
msgid "- Collect Colony Income (7.1)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:934
msgid "- Collect Mineral Income (7.2)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:935
msgid "- Pay Maintenance Costs (7.3)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:936
msgid "- Bid to determine player order (7.4)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:937
#, fuzzy
msgid "- Purchase units and technology (7.5)"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:938
msgid "- Place purchased units at allowable Colonies (7.6)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:939
msgid "- Adjust Colony counters to reflect growth (7.7)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:940
msgid ""
"A Production Sheet has been provided which lists these specific steps "
"with room to record the Construction Points (CP) produced and spent on "
"each item."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:947
msgid "Collect Colony Income"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:960
msgid ""
"First, each player that has more than 30 CP must discard down to 30 CP. "
"Then, the players collect income. Each Colony counter is printed with a "
"number which represents its value in CP. Players begin the Economic Phase"
" by adding the CP of all their Colonies and noting this sum on their "
"Production Sheets as income."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:961
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player has colonized two worlds besides their Homeworld. "
"They earn 30 CP for their Homeworld and 5 CP for each of the other two "
"worlds for a total of 40 CP.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:962
msgid ""
"A Colony Ship is worth 0 CP and will remain valueless until it is flipped"
" to its \"Colony\" side (7.7)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:969
msgid "Blockade Effects"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:973
msgid ""
"A Colony that has an enemy unit in the same hex (and no friendly units in"
" the case of an enemy Raider, 16.0) does not produce income but does grow"
" normally (7.7). Facilities (36.0) will also not produce income. Only "
"units with an Attack Strength may blockade a Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:980
msgid "Collect Mineral Income"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:984
msgid ""
"Players add the value of all Mineral markers transported by Mining Ships "
"to their non-blockaded Colonies since the last Economic Phase (6.7.2) and"
" record the sum of these Mineral markers on their Production Sheets. The "
"Mineral markers are then removed from the game. This is a one-time "
"income. If a player has salvaged a Space Wreck (6.8), they roll for the "
"technology upgrade now. If a Colony is blockaded (7.1.2), the benefit "
"from Minerals and Space Wrecks on the planet cannot be collected until "
"the blockade is lifted."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:991
msgid "Pay Maintenance Costs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1000
msgid "Maintenance Cost"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1004
msgid ""
"All units except those noted below have a maintenance cost equal to their"
" Hull Size. Players add up the Hull Size of all these units and note the "
"sum on their Production Sheet, subtracting this maintenance cost from "
"their income. If the total maintenance cost exceeds a player's income, "
"the player's net income is zero."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1005
msgid ""
"Bases, <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases, Defense Satellite "
"Networks</mark>, Colonies, Colony Ships, Mines, Mining Ships, MS "
"Pipelines, and Shipyards do not incur maintenance costs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1006
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Cruiser Group has 3 ships in it. Each Cruiser has a "
"maintenance cost of 2 CP (Hull Size of 2), so the Group costs 6 CP to "
"maintain. The player subtracts that from their income and notes the "
"remainder on their Production Sheet.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1013
msgid "Scuttling Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1017
msgid ""
"A player may scuttle any of their units currently on the board, thus "
"removing the units from play (scuttled ships may be constructed anew and "
"thus returned to play). One motive for doing so is to avoid paying "
"maintenance costs. Another is to free up group counters for newer and "
"more technologically advanced spaceships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1018
msgid "A unit can be scuttled at the following times:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1019
msgid "- An Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1020
msgid "- A player's own Movement Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1021
msgid ""
"- Another player's Movement Phase the moment they enter the hex that the "
"counter is in (treating it like a Decoy; 8.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1022
msgid "- Combat Phase – only to free up a counter to allow a ship to be screened."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1023
msgid "- During a retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1024
msgid ""
"- Because of any of the following Resource Cards (39.0): <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Self-Destruct #68</span>, <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Heroic Ship #70 #71 #72 #73</span>, <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Overload Weapons #80</span>, <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Forced System Shutdown #94 #95</span>, or <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Play Dead #102</span>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1031
msgid "Bid to Determine Player Order"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1035
msgid ""
"<i>This abstractly represents resources, supplies, intelligence, and "
"capital spent to speed production schedules, etc.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1036
msgid ""
"Players enter a number of CP as a bid on their Production Sheets. The "
"highest bid will earn the privilege of determining the player order for "
"the next turn. This bid is optional; players may bid zero CP. Likewise, "
"there is no upper limit (except the total CP a player has available). The"
" winner of this bid chooses which player will go first, with the turn "
"order rotating clockwise around the table after that. This order stays in"
" effect until the next Economic Phase. Regardless of who wins the bid, "
"all players subtract their bid from their available CP. In the event of a"
" tie (even a tie where all players bid 0), the player who was first in "
"player order this turn (among the tied players) wins the bid. Bids are "
"revealed after the Economic Phase. On the first turn of a game, the "
"players randomly determine turn order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1043
msgid "Purchase Units & Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1056
msgid ""
"Players may now spend CP to purchase new technology levels and ships. "
"Technology costs are listed in the Technology Progression section of the "
"Production Sheet and on the Research Chart. Ship building costs are "
"listed on the Ship Chart. Players record each purchase on their "
"Production Sheets. If a player concludes this phase with unspent CP, it "
"is carried over to the next turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1063
msgid "Carry-Over Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1067
msgid ""
"Players can only carry over 30 CP to the next Economic Phase. If playing "
"with Facilities (36.0), this limit includes any CP produced by Industrial"
" Centers. If a player saves more than 30 CP in order to refit ships "
"(9.11.3) and the refits do not take place, that player loses the excess "
"before the start of the next Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1074
msgid "Initial Build Limits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1078
msgid ""
"The starting technology levels only allow a player to build Scouts, "
"Colony Ships, Mining Ships, Decoys, Shipyards and MS Pipelines. Other "
"types of ships can only be built when a player's technology level is "
"sufficiently advanced (9.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1085
msgid "Ship Technology Level"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1089
msgid ""
"When a ship is purchased, it is automatically \"built\" with an empire's "
"latest technology. If a technology level and a spaceship are both "
"purchased in the same Economic Phase, the new technology level applies to"
" the new ship. However, ships already in play are not automatically "
"upgraded. Players may choose to build a ship with lower technology levels"
" than they are capable of building. The Ship Technology Sheet (on the "
"back of the Production Sheet) is used to keep track of each Group's "
"technology levels (9.11.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1096
msgid "Purchase Limits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1100
msgid ""
"If all Group counters of a particular ship type are already in play, new "
"ships of that type cannot be built (unless a player scuttles ships; "
"7.3.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1107
msgid "Place Purchased Units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1120
msgid ""
"Purchased units are placed at Shipyards (SY). At Shipyard technology "
"level 1, a single ship with a Hull Size of x1 may be placed per Shipyard."
" If two Shipyards with Shipyard technology level 1 occupy the same "
"System, two Hull Points (2.3.5) worth of ships may be placed there "
"(either one x2 or two x1s). There is no limit to the number of Shipyards "
"that may occupy a System. A player must have adequate Shipyard capacity "
"to build any given ship. Shipyard capacity can be increased by developing"
" Shipyard technology (9.6). New ships may be added to existing Groups in "
"the same hex if they are of the same type and technology level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1121
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If a player has two Shipyards and has researched Shipyard "
"technology level 1, they may only place two DD's there, or two Colony "
"Ships, or two Mines, or one CA, or one Fighter and one Mine, or any other"
" appropriate combination.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1128
msgid "Hidden Units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1132
msgid ""
"Combat units are placed face down when built and remain that way until "
"combat occurs (5.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1133
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-beige\">DESIGN NOTE: Other players will see you "
"manipulate the counters, but you do not have to announce what you are "
"building or scrapping.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1140
msgid "Adjust Colony Income"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1153
msgid ""
"A Colony must grow in order to reach its full capacity. At this point in "
"the Economic Phase, all Colonies are adjusted upwards to reflect this "
"development. Colonies producing 3 CP have their \"3 Colony\" counter "
"removed to reveal the 5 CP on the Colony (the maximum size). Next, "
"Colonies producing 1 CP have the \"1 Colony\" flipped to a \"3 Colony\". "
"Finally, Colony Ships on planets are flipped to their Colony side and a "
"\"1 Colony\" marker is placed on them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1154
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: During movement, a player colonizes a planet by placing their"
" Colony Ship on top of the planet. During the subsequent Economic Phase, "
"that planet delivers no CP, but the counter is flipped to its Colony "
"side. In the next Economic Phase, that Colony would be worth 1 CP.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1161
msgid "Damaged Homeworlds"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1165
msgid ""
"During the Economic Phase, a damaged Homeworld (5.10.2) grows one step. "
"Thus, a Homeworld marked with a 5 CP would be replaced by a 10 CP, etc."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1172
msgid "Maintenance Increase & Decrease"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1176
msgid ""
"There is a spot on the Production Sheet to track additional (future) "
"maintenance costs from purchases during this Economic Phase as well as to"
" track maintenance reductions from the loss of ships in between Economic "
"Phases. This is only an aid so that players do not have to count their "
"maintenance costs during every Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1183
msgid "Basic Unit Types"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1192
msgid "Bases"
msgstr "Phase"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1196
msgid ""
"A player must have researched Ship Size 2 to build Bases. Like other "
"Groups, a Base is built face down with a numeral marker below it. Unlike "
"other Groups, a Base may be built at any Colony that produced income (not"
" new or blockaded Colonies) in the Economic Phase. Bases are not built by"
" Shipyards. Only one Base may be built in a single hex, and no hex may "
"have more than one Base. Once in play, a Base may not move. A Base "
"participates in combat like other Groups, except that it may not retreat."
" Bases do not incur maintenance costs. A Colony may build both a Base and"
" a Shipyard in the same Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1203
msgid "Shipyards (SY)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1207
msgid ""
"<i>Shipyards represent the facilities and infrastructure necessary for "
"the construction of spaceships.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1208
msgid ""
"Newly constructed units enter play in a hex with a Shipyard, and in some "
"cases more than one Shipyard or better Shipyard Technology are needed to "
"build a single ship (9.6). Shipyards do not incur maintenance costs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1209
msgid ""
"Shipyards may only be built at Colonies that produced income (not new or "
"blockaded Colonies) in the Economic Phase. A Colony may build both a "
"Shipyard and a Base in the same Economic Phase. Shipyards may be "
"purchased and placed at multiple planets, but no more than one per "
"planet. Additional Shipyards may be purchased at those planets in future "
"Economic Phases. Like other Groups, Shipyards are built face down with a "
"numeral marker below them. Unlike other Groups, Shipyards are produced by"
" the Colony itself and therefore do not require other Shipyards to build "
"them. Since Shipyards are placed at the same time as other units, they "
"may not be used to build ships the turn they are built."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1225 app/data/master_rule_book.py:4457
msgid "Purpose"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1229
msgid ""
"Decoys are expendable, unarmed ships that are designed to fool opponents "
"into thinking they are larger ships or an entire Group. They move about "
"just like other Groups, and a numeral marker is placed under the Decoy to"
" facilitate the ruse. The numeral marker placed under a Decoy must match "
"the CP that was paid for the Decoy(s) to indicate how many Decoys are "
"present in the Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1240
msgid ""
"Decoys may not explore. Decoys move at the speed of the current Movement "
"technology level (4.1) and their Movement technology level is "
"automatically upgraded. They are not capable of attacking or defending. "
"If alone in a hex entered by another player's Group, the Decoy is "
"revealed and removed immediately from play (the attacking Group is not "
"revealed in this case). If Decoys are in a hex with a friendly Group that"
" is attacked, the Decoys are automatically eliminated at the start of "
"combat (5.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1247
msgid "Purchasing and Maintenance"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1251
msgid ""
"Decoys may only be built at Colonies that produced income (not new or "
"blockaded Colonies) in the Economic Phase. The cost is 1 CP, and do not "
"require a Shipyard to be constructed. Decoys do not incur maintenance "
"cost."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1258
msgid "Colony Ships & Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1262
msgid ""
"Colony Ship counters represent either a ship or a Colony (when on a "
"planet). When a Colony Ship colonizes a planet (4.4) it will be flipped "
"from its ship side to its Colony side in the ensuing Economic Phase. "
"Barren Planets may not be colonized unless Terraforming technology has "
"been developed (9.7). The movement rate of a Colony Ship is one hex, "
"regardless of a player's Movement technology level. Colony Ships always "
"represent a single ship and never have a numeral marker underneath them. "
"Colony Ships are always placed face up."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1269
msgid "Mining Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1273
msgid ""
"Mining Ships are used for towing Mineral markers (6.7) or Space Wrecks "
"(6.8). The movement rate of a Mining Ship is one hex, regardless of a "
"player's Movement technology level. Mining Ships always represent a "
"single ship and never have a numeral marker underneath them. Mining Ships"
" do not incur a maintenance cost. The 5 on the back of the Mining Ship "
"counter is only relevant when using the Terraforming Nebulae optional "
"rule; 34.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1280
msgid "Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1289
msgid "Purchasing Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1293
msgid ""
"Players may spend CP to improve their technologies. Technologies are "
"purchased in \"levels,\" with each level costing CP as indicated on the "
"Research Chart. When a technology level is purchased, the appropriate "
"number on the Technology Progression section of the Production Sheet is "
"circled. Levels must be purchased in numerical order and only one level "
"of technology may be purchased in each category per Economic Phase "
"(although a player may purchase levels in two or more Technologies "
"simultaneously)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1294
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: Attack technology level 2 must be purchased before Attack "
"technology level 3; and Attack technology 2 and 3 may not be purchased in"
" the same Economic Phase.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1295
msgid ""
"Several technologies have had their costs adjusted since the initial "
"release of <i>Space Empires</i>. These new costs should be used at all "
"times – even if playing with only the base game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1302
msgid "Attack & Defense Technologies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1306
msgid ""
"Improvement in these technology levels add to the combat capabilities of "
"a player's ships (5.5). Note that ships can never carry an Attack or "
"Defense technology level greater than their Hull Size (9.4). These are "
"the only technologies that are limited by Hull Size."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1307
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: Scouts, Destroyers and Shipyards can never have an Attack "
"technology greater than level 1, even if that player has purchased a "
"higher Attack technology level.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1314
msgid "Tactics Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1318
msgid ""
"This technology affects which ships fire first in combat when they have "
"the same Weapon Class (5.2). This abstractly represents not only the "
"tactical training of a player's units, but also certain aspects of "
"technology. Tactics technology is not limited by Hull Size. Like other "
"technologies, the Tactics level is specific to a Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1325
msgid "Ship Size Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1329
msgid ""
"Increasing this technology allows the purchase of larger ships. The Hull "
"Size shown on a unit's counter indicates how many Hull Points are "
"required to build it. The Research Chart shows which ships can be "
"purchased at each technology level. This tech may be used in the same "
"Econ Phase it is purchased."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1330
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player just purchased Ship Size level 3. That same Economic"
" Phase they may purchase Cruisers (CA).</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1337
msgid "Movement Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1341
msgid ""
"This represents how fast a ship may move (4.1). Reaction Movement also "
"comes with some levels of Movement technology when using that optional "
"rule (35.0). See the Movement Technology Chart near the back of this "
"book."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1348
msgid "Shipyard Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1352
msgid ""
"Each player starts with a Shipyard technology level of 1, which can "
"produce 1 Hull Point of ships each Economic Phase. At technology level 2,"
" each Shipyard produces 1.5 Hull Points (rounded down). At technology "
"level 3, each Shipyard produces 2 Hull Points each."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1353
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: a player has developed Shipyard technology level 2, and they "
"have two Shipyards in the same hex. Those Shipyards may now build a total"
" of 3 Hull Points worth of ships each Economic Phase.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1360
msgid "Terraforming Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1364
msgid ""
"After purchasing Terraforming 1, a player's Colony Ships may colonize "
"Barren Planets (4.4.2). Colony Ships that were purchased before this "
"technology do not gain this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1365
msgid ""
"Terraforming 2 is only relevant when using the Terraforming Nebulae "
"Optional rule (34.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1372
msgid "Exploration 1 Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1376
msgid ""
"This technology greatly improves the sensors and other equipment needed "
"for exploration. Only Cruisers, Flagships, Replicator Exploration Ships "
"(40.7.4) may be equipped with it. During the Movement Phase, each ship so"
" equipped may peek at one adjacent face-down (unexplored) System marker "
"before moving. The player has the choice of returning the marker face "
"down or revealing the marker. If the marker is revealed and it is a "
"marker with a one-time effect (e.g., Danger!, etc.), it is removed. "
"Whether the marker is revealed or not, any negative effects from flipping"
" that marker do not affect the exploring ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1377
msgid ""
"The ship is also allowed to move normally in that Movement Phase (and may"
" explore a different hex in the usual fashion, as per [6.1]). A ship that"
" uses Exploration 1 technology is not revealed. Exploration technology "
"cannot be used on a hex that has a Doomsday Machine or Alien Player fleet"
" (SSB 4.0) in it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1378
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-purple\"><strong>PLAY NOTE:</strong> This means that a "
"ship equipped with Exploration 1 technology can explore 2 hexes each turn"
" (one with Exploration technology and one by moving into the hex).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1379
msgid ""
"An advanced version of this technology (Reaction Movement, 35.0) is "
"available as an optional rule."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1386
msgid "Fast Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1390
msgid ""
"Some ships can be equipped with Fast technology, giving them greater "
"mobility. Such ships may move one extra space on turn 1 (only). All other"
" normal movement rules apply."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1397
msgid "Fast 1 (formerly called Fast Battlecruisers or Fast BC)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1401
msgid ""
"Allows Battlecruisers, Flagships (23.0), and Unique Ships (41.0) to be "
"equipped with Fast technology. All Space Pirates (25.7) are equipped with"
" Fast 1, regardless of whether it is researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1402
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If a player has Fast BC 1 and Movement 4, their other ships "
"may move 2 hexes each turn. Their BCs will be able to move 3 hexes on "
"turn 1.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1403
msgid ""
"Once this technology has been researched, Decoys may also use it just "
"like they can use other Movement technology. Players do not need to "
"research Ship Size 4 before researching this technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1410
msgid "Fast 2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1414
msgid ""
"Fast 2 costs 10 CP and is only available when using Advanced Construction"
" (38.0). This technology allows DestroyerXs, Battle Carriers, and "
"RaiderXs to be equipped with Fast technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1421
msgid "Revealing Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1425
msgid ""
"The technology present on any ships in a battle is revealed at the start "
"of combat if combat-capable units are involved on both sides, though "
"Movement technology is also revealed in the Movement Phase in which it is"
" used. Technology is revealed before Mines are resolved (17.0). Ground "
"Combat 2, Terraforming 1-2, and Military Academy 1 are not revealed in "
"space combat. All other technologies are revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1426
msgid ""
"To reveal a technology a player just announces it. They do not have to "
"show their Production Sheet until the end of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1433
msgid "New Technology Levels"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1437
msgid ""
"Technologies apply to ships purchased in the same and subsequent Economic"
" Phases. Thus, if a player purchases Attack 2 in the same turn that they "
"purchase a Battleship, this new Battleship is \"equipped\" with Attack 2;"
" however, ships purchased in previous turns are not equipped with it. "
"Players may choose to build a ship with lower technology levels than they"
" are capable of building."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1444
msgid "Group Uniformity"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1448
msgid ""
"Spaceships in the same Group must have identical technology (such as "
"Attack level, Tactics level, and so forth). If a player has two "
"spaceships of the same type but with different technology capabilities, "
"they must be represented by different Group counters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1455
msgid "Record-Keeping"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1459
msgid ""
"Players keep track of a Group's technology levels on the Ship Technology "
"Sheet using each Group's identification number. When a player purchases a"
" ship, they circle the current technologies on the row corresponding to "
"its Group on the sheet. There is no need to ever erase the circles on the"
" sheet since a player's technology level never decreases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1460
msgid ""
"To save space, the Ship Technology Sheet does not list the technologies "
"that a ship must have. For example, Attack 0, Tactics 0, and Move 1 are "
"not listed on the sheet. All ships must at least have those levels of "
"technology. Attack 1 is the first Attack technology listed. If Attack 1 "
"is not circled, then the ship must still be at Attack 0. Likewise, for "
"Fighters, Fighter 1 technology is not listed because the Fighter must "
"obviously be at least at Fighter 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1467
msgid "Refits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1471
msgid ""
"A ship may be upgraded to a player's current technology level. The ship "
"must be in a System with a Shipyard. There is no limit to the number of "
"ships that can be upgraded at a single Shipyard. The ship must not move "
"or use Exploration Tech for an entire turn (it must begin and end the "
"turn at the Shipyard), and a number of CP must be expended equal to its "
"Hull Size. This upgrades all its technologies to the current level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1472
msgid ""
"Normally this means that a player must have CP left over from the "
"previous Economic Phase in order to upgrade ships (7.5.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1479
msgid "Automatic Upgrades"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1483
msgid ""
"Bases, <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases, Defense Satellite "
"Networks</mark>, and Shipyards are automatically and instantly upgraded "
"to the latest technology levels without cost (limited to their Hull "
"Size). Shipyards may even use a new level of Shipyard technology that was"
" just purchased."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1484
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-purple\"><strong>PLAY NOTE:</strong> For those who wish "
"to avoid the bookkeeping required by this rule, the Instant Technology "
"Upgrade optional rule removes it (30.0).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1491
msgid "Empire Advantages"
msgstr "Avantages d'empire"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1500
msgid "Random Method"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1504
msgid ""
"Each player is dealt two Empire Advantage cards at the start of the game."
" A player using Replicators (40.0) is dealt two Replicator Empire "
"Advantage Cards instead. Players choose one and discard the other face "
"down."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1511
msgid "Balanced Method"
msgstr "Avantages d'empire"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1515
msgid ""
"This method cannot be used when any Player is using Replicators. One more"
" Empire Advantage card than the number of players is dealt face up in the"
" middle of the table. Each player begins the game with 75 CP. Open CP "
"bidding begins for choice of an Empire Advantage until no one is willing "
"to beat the highest bid. The winner of the bid subtracts their bid amount"
" from their starting CP and picks an Empire Advantage. Those who do not "
"win the bid lose nothing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1516
msgid ""
"The remaining players repeat the process and bid for choice of the next "
"Empire Advantage. When only one player is left, they bid zero, choose one"
" of the two remaining Empire Advantages, and discard the other."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1517
msgid ""
"In the unlikely event that someone bids more than 75 CP (or more than the"
" amount agreed upon), then any additional CP is subtracted from their "
"future income. In this case, maintenance would have to be paid, with any "
"income going to pay off their original bid."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1524
msgid "Revealing Empire Advantage Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1528
msgid ""
"Empire Advantage cards are placed face down in front of each player. When"
" their reveal condition is met, they are turned face up and left that way"
" for the remainder of the game. A player's card is also revealed if "
"Ground Units capture one of their Colonies (21.13). Consult the Expanded "
"Sequence of Play in the Competitive Scenario Book (CSB) for information "
"on when these cards are revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1535 app/data/master_rule_book.py:4628
msgid "Special Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1539
msgid ""
"See the Card Manifest for the complete list of Empire Advantages and "
"additional details that don't fit on the cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1546
msgid "Captured Planets"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1550
msgid ""
"Empire Advantages are never gained from a player when their planet is "
"captured."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1557 app/data/master_rule_book.py:2250
msgid "Captured Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1561
msgid ""
"Unless otherwise noted, ships captured through boarding (19.3) do not "
"retain their Empire Advantage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1568
msgid "Scenario Restrictions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1572
msgid ""
"When playing any scenario that at any point has only two hexes of Deep "
"Space between player's home areas, do not use the following Empire "
"Advantages: <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Ancient Race #36</span>, <span"
" class=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race #34</span>, <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">House of Speed #53</span>, <span class=\"text-uppercase\">On "
"the Move #58</span>, <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Industrious Race "
"#35</span>, <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Longbowmen #59</span>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1573
msgid ""
"In addition, do not use an advantage if not playing with a rule that it "
"modifies. For example, if playing with the Instant Upgrade rule (30.0), "
"don't play with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Nano-technology "
"#39</span>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1574
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">And We Still Carry Swords #47</span> "
"should not be used when playing the Planetary Gate (CSB 9.0) Scenario "
"(too powerful)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1581
msgid "Alien Technology Cards"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1590
msgid "Acquiring Alien Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1594
msgid ""
"Before the start of the game the Alien Technology deck is shuffled and "
"placed face down next to the game board. Before shuffling, the players "
"should remove any cards from the deck that only modify rules not being "
"used in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1595
msgid ""
"When a Barren Planet in the Deep Space portion of the map is initially "
"colonized (4.4.2) or captured (21.13), the player may draw two of these "
"cards. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">If a drawn card does not apply to the "
"empire you are playing, it may be revealed and discarded for a different "
"one.</mark> They secretly choose one card and discard the other face "
"down. The player must pay 10 CP during the next Economic Phase to keep "
"the chosen card, otherwise it must be discarded. This expenditure is "
"recorded under ship purchases on the Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1596
msgid ""
"If playing with Non-Player Aliens (18.0), there is no cost for the chosen"
" card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1597
msgid ""
"An Alien Technology card is not drawn for a planet that has been "
"previously colonized or captured by any player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1598
msgid ""
"The only player who may benefit from an Alien Technology card is the "
"player who drew it. An Alien Technology card may not be gained by "
"scrapping a captured ship (19.5.1) that is benefitting from it or by "
"capturing an enemy planet. Alien Technology cards only start granting "
"their benefit after the current player's turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1599
msgid ""
"Cards that can benefit ships already built (like <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Holodeck #8</span>) do so immediately (all existing ships get"
" that benefit). <i>This alien technology is so advanced that it is easy "
"to install.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1600
msgid ""
"Ships that are captured do still retain the benefit of the Alien "
"Technology card. There is just no way for the capturing player to gain "
"the ability from the ship and duplicate it for their other ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1607
msgid "Revealing Alien Technology Levels"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1611
msgid ""
"Alien Technology cards are placed face down in front of their owner. When"
" their reveal condition is met, they are turned face up and left that way"
" for the remainder of the game. A player's Alien Technology cards are "
"also revealed if Ground Units capture one of their Colonies (21.13) or if"
" a ship benefitting from it is captured. Consult the Expanded Sequence of"
" Play in the Competitive Scenario Book (CSB) for information on when "
"these cards are revealed. See the Card Manifest for a complete list of "
"Alien Technology cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1618
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Crew Cards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1622
msgid ""
"Crew Cards provide many unique combinations with which to diversify ship "
"Groups and add tactical nuance to a player's fleets. Crew Cards can be "
"used in addition or separately from Experience (37.0). If used together, "
"any bonuses of Crew Cards and Experience are cumulative. See the Card "
"Manifest for a complete list of Crew Cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1629
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Acquiring Crew Cards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1633
msgid ""
"Before the start of the game, separately shuffle the Crew Cards and "
"Replicator Crew Cards (if playing with them) into face-down piles next to"
" the game board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1634
msgid ""
"During every even-numbered Economic Phase (2, 4, 6, etc.) each player "
"draws two Crew Cards from the appropriate deck, chooses one to keep face "
"down, and discards the other. Discarded Crew Cards are always separated "
"by type and placed face down and \"messy\" so they are not mistaken for a"
" draw pile. Reshuffle a discard pile when its deck has run out of cards. "
"Each player is limited to 5 Crew Cards at a time. If a player already has"
" 5 Crew Cards in play, cards may be drawn normally, but an existing card "
"must be discarded to keep one of the new ones."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1641
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Utilizing Crew Cards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1650
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Assigning Crew Cards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1654
msgid ""
"Crew Cards must be assigned during the same Economic Phase during which "
"they are drawn. They can be assigned to a Group in the player's Home "
"System or a Group the player builds during the same Economic Phase (even "
"if built outside of the Home System). A Crew Card that cannot be assigned"
" must be discarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1655
msgid ""
"Assigned Crew Cards remain face down in front of the player. Group "
"assignments can be tracked by writing the number of the Crew Card by the "
"Group on the Ship Technology Sheet. Alternatively, a dry erase marker can"
" be used to write the Group on the Crew Card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1656
msgid ""
"Crew Cards are turned face up when their ability is used or when their "
"Group is revealed. A Crew Card used outside of combat must be revealed, "
"but its Group is not revealed. Once turned face up, they remain face up "
"for the rest of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1657
msgid ""
"Ships may join or leave a Group with a Crew Card, but the Crew Card must "
"stay with the same Group until that Group is destroyed. The only "
"exception is if two Groups combine, each with one Crew Card, both Crew "
"Cards may be kept by the newly combined Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1664
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Replicator Crew Cards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1668
msgid ""
"These represent part of the AI that have formed distinct personalities. "
"All the rules for normal Crew Cards apply to Replicator Crew Cards. Each "
"Replicator Crew has three numeral counters (1/2, 3/4, and 5/6) with its "
"name on it. These may be used in place of normal numeral markers to "
"indicate which Group that Crew is assigned to. Replicators can only have "
"one Crew on a Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1675
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Crew Card Limitations</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1679
msgid ""
"Each Group may have at most two Crew Cards, and only one Crew with the "
"same title (e.g., a Group can't have two <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Engineers #214 #215</span>)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1680
msgid ""
"All Crew Cards that improve Weapon Class have no impact in terrain that "
"modifies Weapon Class (e.g., ships in a Group with an <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Admiral #249 #250</span> would still fire as E-Class in "
"Asteroids), unless otherwise noted."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1681
msgid ""
"When playing with Crew Cards, the 4 Resource Cards for <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic Ships #70 #71 #72 #73</span> cannot make ships"
" Heroic. Instead, they can be played at any time to draw 2 Crew Cards and"
" keep 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1688
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Crew Cards in Combat</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1692
msgid ""
"After a battle, each Crew Card in a Group that had at least one ship "
"destroyed must roll for survival and is eliminated on a roll of 9-10. Add"
" +3 to the roll if the Crew Card's Group was eliminated and +3 if no "
"friendly ships remain in the battle hex after the battle (harder to pick "
"up escape pods). Crew Cards that become casualties are placed in the "
"appropriate discard pile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1693
msgid ""
"If a Crew Card survives even though its Group has been destroyed, it is "
"immediately assigned to another Group in its hex, if possible. If not "
"possible, during the next Economic Phase it must be assigned as if it had"
" been drawn. This does not prevent the player from drawing a new Crew "
"Card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1700
msgid "Merchant Ship Pipelines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1704
msgid ""
"<i>Merchant Ship Pipelines represent groups of slow-moving space vessels "
"as well as navigational beacons and portions of space that have been "
"charted and cleared for space travel.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1711
msgid "MS Pipeline Characteristics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1715
msgid ""
"Merchant Ship (MS) Pipelines always represent a single trade network – "
"never place a numeral marker underneath them. MS Pipelines move one hex "
"per turn, and do not receive any benefit from an increase in Movement "
"technology. They may be purchased and placed at a Shipyard in the usual "
"fashion. MS Pipelines are non-combat ships and do not incur maintenance "
"costs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1722
msgid "MS Pipelines Chains"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1726
msgid ""
"MS Pipelines may be organized in a \"chain\", a trade network connecting "
"planets and other regions of space. Two or more MS Pipelines adjacent to "
"one another form a chain (or pipeline). The benefits of a chain are "
"indicated below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1733
msgid "Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1737
msgid ""
"Any unit, including another MS Pipeline, that starts its movement on a "
"chain of friendly MS Pipeline counters and spends its entire Movement "
"Phase on the same chain may move an additional hex, as long as that hex "
"is also part of the chain. If used to aid a ship's movement, none of the "
"MS Pipeline counters that form this chain may move or have moved during "
"the turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1738
msgid ""
"To make it easier to keep track of which MS Pipeline counters have not "
"moved, the MS Pipeline counters have an \"Active\" side. If a MS Pipeline"
" has moved, flip it to the \"Moved\" side until the start of the next "
"turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1739
msgid ""
"MS Pipelines that survive entrance into a Black Hole hex may, in future "
"turns, use their navigational aids to allow friendly ships traveling "
"along a chain to enter the Black Hole hex without rolling for destruction"
" (in other words, a chain may extend into a Black Hole hex)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1740
msgid ""
"MS Pipelines also allow friendly ships which are traveling along a chain "
"to ignore Nebulae and Asteroids for purposes of movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1747
msgid "Trade Networks"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1751
msgid ""
"Any friendly Colony (even a new one) that is connected to the Homeworld "
"by a friendly MS Pipeline chain produces one extra CP in the Economic "
"Phase (the Homeworld does not produce an extra CP, but each Colony "
"connected to its network does). There must be an MS Pipeline counter in "
"each planet hex, including the Homeworld, and in each hex in between."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1752
msgid ""
"An unlimited number of Colonies may be connected to the Homeworld in this"
" way, each contributing an extra CP through the network. MS Pipelines may"
" contribute to this chain even if they moved this turn. Each Colony gives"
" this benefit only one time per Economic Phase, no matter how many times "
"it is connected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1759
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Defense Satellite Networks</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1768
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">DSN Characteristics</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1772
msgid ""
"Similar to Bases (8.1), a Defense Satellite Network (DSN) may be built at"
" any friendly planet with an income-producing Colony (not new or "
"blockaded Colonies). DSNs cannot move and do not incur maintenance costs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1773
msgid ""
"DSNs are not built by Shipyards; however, they cannot be built until a "
"player has researched Ship Size 2 technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1780
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">DSN Restrictions</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1784
msgid ""
"Each Colony is limited to one DSN and one Base/Starbase (38.5). If a "
"Colony builds a DSN during an Economic Phase, it may not build a Base (or"
" upgrade a Base to a Starbase) during the same Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1791
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">DSN Combat</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1795
msgid ""
"DSNs (B4-1-x2) participate in combat like other Groups, but may not "
"retreat and cannot be boarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1802
msgid "Carriers, Fighters, & Point Defense"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1806
msgid ""
"<i>Fighter technology allows you to build Carriers (CV) and Fighter "
"Squadrons. Point Defense technology applies only to Scouts, and only "
"affects their attacks against Fighters.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1813
msgid "Carriers (CV)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1826
msgid ""
"A Carrier may hold a maximum of 3 Fighter Squadrons. Carriers may "
"participate in combat but cannot be targeted until all friendly Fighters "
"(not just those on that particular Carrier) present in the battle are "
"destroyed (even if the Carrier is screened). Carriers lose this immunity "
"if their owner screens any Fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1833
msgid "Carrier Retreats"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1837
msgid ""
"Carriers that retreat may not \"orphan\" Fighters in combat. A Carrier "
"may retreat with less than its full complement of Fighter Squadrons, but "
"only if there are specific ships (15.2.3) or a friendly Colony remaining "
"in the System to absorb the Fighters left behind."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1844
msgid "Fighters (F)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1857
msgid ""
"Fighters are purchased in squadrons, and numeral markers are used "
"underneath Fighter Squadron counters to indicate the number of squadrons "
"represented by that counter. Note: Fighter Squadron counters are not "
"physically stacked on a Carrier, they just need to be in the same hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1858
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A hex could have one Carrier Group with a 2 under the counter"
" and one Fighter Group with a 6 under the counter to represent two fully "
"loaded Carriers.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1865
msgid "Fighter Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1869
msgid ""
"Fighters are small spaceships that have no interstellar movement "
"capability of their own. Fighter Squadrons therefore may not move from "
"hex to hex on their own, although they may be carried."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1876
msgid "Carrying Fighters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1880
msgid ""
"Only Carriers (15.1), Battle Carriers (38.6), Titans (22.0), or Unique "
"Ships with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Mini-Fighter Bays</span> (p.45)"
" may carry Fighter Squadrons. Thus, a squadron must remain at the "
"Shipyard where it is placed during the Economic Phase, or transfer to one"
" of the above-noted ships in the same hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1887
msgid "Transfer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1891
msgid ""
"One or more Fighter Squadrons may transfer from a colonized planet to an "
"appropriate ship type (or vice versa) which is in the same hex. Fighters "
"may also transfer between ships in the same hex. Transfer may happen any "
"time during a ship's move or during combat at no extra cost to the ship, "
"but movement is simultaneous. A Fighter Squadron cannot be moved further "
"in one turn than the speed of the fastest ship involved."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1892
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player may not use Move 4 to move a CV and 3 Fighters two "
"hexes to an empty CV and then have the second CV move 2 hexes with the 3 "
"Fighters.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1899
msgid "Fighters & Combat"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1903
msgid ""
"A Fighter Squadron is counted as a single combat-capable ship for the "
"purpose of determining screening. Fighters may not fire on the turn their"
" carrying ship declares it is retreating. Fighters that declare they are "
"retreating remain in the battle until the ship that is carrying them "
"retreats (15.1.2). They still protect the carrying ship as normal from "
"enemy fire until it retreats, or until the Fighters are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1910
msgid "Fighters and Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1914
msgid ""
"There is no limit to the number of Fighter Squadrons that may be on a "
"planet with a Colony. Fighters based on a Colony must participate in any "
"battle that occurs in its hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1921
msgid "Fighter Technology & Upgrades"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1925
msgid ""
"Fighter technology improves a Fighter's Attack and Defense Strength (as "
"indicated on the Ship Chart). In addition to upgrading the technology "
"they carry (9.11.3) Fighters may also upgrade their basic attack and "
"defense by upgrading the Fighter Technology level, this is done similarly"
" and at the same time and at no extra cost as all other technologies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1926
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">All Fighters that are Fighter 2 or 3 get +1 "
"Defense against Point Defense (15.3).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1933
msgid "Point Defense Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1937
msgid ""
"Point Defense is a technology that is equipped by Scouts and used against"
" Fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1944
msgid "Scouts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1948
msgid ""
"Point Defense technology improves a Scout's ability to contend with "
"Fighters. A Scout with Point Defense technology has an A-Class rating and"
" a higher Attack Strength (depending on the Point Defense level), but "
"only when firing at Fighter Squadrons; even then, all other capabilities "
"remain the same. In combat, a Scout with Point Defense technology firing "
"at a target other than a Fighter Squadron does so with its normal E-Class"
" rating."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1949
msgid ""
"Exception: In Asteroids and Nebulae, Point Defense equipped ships have an"
" E-Class rating like all other ships and Fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1956
msgid "Scouts and Attack/Defense Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1960
msgid ""
"Point Defense technology can be used with Attack and Defense technology "
"when Scouts combat Fighters – up to the limit of their Hull Size, which "
"is 1 in both cases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1961
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Scout (E-Class, Attack Strength 3) with Point Defense "
"technology level 1 (A6 vs. Fighters) plus Attack technology level 1 (+1 "
"to Attack Strength) would fire on Fighters with an A7 and fire on non-"
"Fighters with an E4.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1968
msgid "Raiders: Cloaking & Scanners"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1977
msgid "Raiders (R)"
msgstr "Aides"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1981
msgid ""
"Cloaking technology allows the purchase of Raiders. Raiders have the "
"additional ability to cloak. When a Raider's Cloaking technology is "
"superior to the enemy's Scanner technology (16.2), or the enemy has no "
"Scanners, then the Raider is considered cloaked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1988
msgid "Movement Advantage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1992
msgid ""
"A cloaked Raider may move into a hex occupied by an enemy unit and "
"continue moving. It need not stop. It may also occupy a hex and not "
"trigger combat. If a cloaked Raider is in the same hex as an enemy ship "
"and Colony, the Colony is not considered blockaded (7.1.2). The cloaked "
"Raider would have to defeat any enemy ships to blockade a Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:1999
msgid "Retreat Advantage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2003
msgid ""
"At the start of a battle, cloaked Raiders (both Attacking and Defending) "
"have the option to retreat after the fleets are revealed and before shots"
" are fired or Mines detonate (17.1.5). In this case, if no other ships "
"remained in combat, information about an opponent's technology would not "
"be revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2010
msgid "Firing Advantage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2014
msgid ""
"In combat, cloaked Raiders (both Attacking and Defending) have an A-Class"
" rating and – during the first firing round only – have their Attack "
"Strength increased by +1. Uncloaked Raiders have a D-Class rating."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2021
msgid "Cloaking Technology Levels"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2025
msgid ""
"A player can increase his Cloaking technology up to level 2. Level 1 "
"Scanners do not negate level 2 Cloaking technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2032
msgid "Cloaking in Nebulae"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2036
msgid ""
"Cloaking devices do not work in Nebulae. All Raider ships are treated as "
"normal ships when in a Nebula."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2043
msgid "Scanners"
msgstr "Cartes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2047
msgid ""
"To counteract Cloaking technology, a player may research Scanners. This "
"technology gives Destroyers (and Advanced Bases) the ability to scan for "
"Raiders. When a Destroyer with scanners is present, treat all enemy "
"Raiders (of equal or lower Cloaking level) as uncloaked. If all scanner "
"equipped Destroyers are eliminated, the enemy ships regain the benefits "
"of being cloaked at the start of the next firing round. To avoid this, a "
"player may combat screen a Destroyer as long as they outnumber their "
"opponent. A screened Destroyer may not participate in combat, but still "
"provides its fleet with scanning benefits."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2048
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player moves their Raiders into a hex with an enemy fleet "
"and either wants to skip combat or keep moving and so announces that they"
" are Raiders. The other player desires combat and so announces that they "
"have Scanners present. The Raider player then announces that their "
"Raiders are at Cloaking 2. The enemy player might then announce that they"
" have Scanner 2.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2055
msgid "Mines & Minesweepers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2064
msgid "Mines"
msgstr "Parties"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2068
msgid ""
"Mine technology must be researched before Mines may be purchased and "
"placed on the game board. A Mines counter operates like any other Group; "
"a numeral marker must be placed under it to indicate the number of Mines "
"represented by the counter. Mines cost no maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2075
msgid "Mine Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2079
msgid ""
"The Mine counter may move on its own, but it is limited to a movement of "
"one hex regardless of technology level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2090
msgid ""
"Mines may not explore or enter an enemy occupied hex (including one with "
"an enemy Colony) – even when accompanied by other friendly units. If "
"enemy ships enter a hex containing Mines, the Mines are automatically "
"considered deployed and active."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2097
msgid "Mines and Combat"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2101
msgid ""
"After technology is revealed (9.10), all Minesweepers (17.2) remove as "
"many Mines as they are capable of sweeping. Unswept Mines immediately "
"detonate (the Mine counters are removed from play), destroying one ship "
"each (regardless of the type of the ship). Mines may target Fighter "
"Groups; one Mine will kill one Fighter. The choice of which ship is "
"destroyed is determined by the player who controls the Mines (yes, I'm "
"picking the DN!). If a ship carrying Fighters is destroyed by a Mine, the"
" Fighters present will be destroyed only if there is not enough room to "
"carry them on other ships. After Mine sweeping and detonation, combat "
"continues as normal. Mine sweeping and Mine detonation only happen at the"
" start of a battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2108
msgid "Must Detonate"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2112
msgid ""
"If enemy ships are present, Mines must detonate – they may not choose to "
"ignore a ship. It is therefore a legitimate strategy to attempt to clear "
"Mines by attacking with only Scouts. If there are more Mines than "
"attacking ships, excess Mines remain in the hex. Except when dealing with"
" cloaked ships, under no circumstances will both Mines and enemy ships "
"remain in a hex after the sweeping and detonating of Mines."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2119
msgid "Mines and Raiders"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2123
msgid ""
"Mines only work on Cloaked Raiders if there is a Destroyer with "
"appropriate Scanner technology present. This is the only exception to "
"Mines being in the same hex as enemy ships after detonation. If a "
"Destroyer with Scanner technology enters the hex, the Mines will activate"
" during combat. During combat (not movement), a cloaked ship can decide "
"to sacrifice itself and uncloak to allow a Mine to detonate on it, but if"
" other ships are present, the owner of the Mine is still free to choose "
"the Mine's target."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2130
msgid "Minesweepers (SW)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2134
msgid ""
"Minesweeper technology allows the purchase and placement of Minesweeper "
"units. Unlike Mines, Minesweepers move using the player's Movement "
"technology (they are not limited to a movement rate of one hex). "
"Minesweepers with Minesweeper technology level 1 remove one Mine each "
"before they detonate. Minesweeper 2 allows each Minesweeper to remove two"
" Mines before detonation. Minesweeper 3 allows each to remove three Mines"
" before detonation. Note that Minesweepers may be chosen as the target of"
" a detonating Mine, but they do not have to be."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2141
msgid "Aliens (Non-Player Aliens)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2150
msgid "Placement"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2154
msgid ""
"Deep Space is inhabited by Non-Player Aliens (NPAs). <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">When a System marker in Deep Space is revealed to be a Barren "
"Planet, random NPA ship markers are drawn and placed on the planet "
"according to the Deep Space Planet Attribute (26.0). If not playing with "
"that rule, draw 4.</mark> They attack any ship that enters their hex, "
"including their exploring ship. Combat is resolved normally. If this "
"planet was discovered by a Cruiser, Flagship, or Replicator Exp ship "
"using Exploration 1 (9.8), the aliens are placed face down, unlooked at, "
"and may not be examined."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2161
msgid "Alien Behavior"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2165
msgid "Aliens normally don't leave their hex and never retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2166
msgid "- Aliens have a Tactics level of 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2167
msgid "- All NPA ships are equipped with Security Forces 1 (20.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2168
msgid "- All NPA ships with a hull size of 1 have PD2 (15.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2169
msgid ""
"- All NPA ships with a hull size of 2 have Scanner 1. However, they will "
"only use this ability when attacked. They will not stop cloaked fleets "
"that do not attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2170
msgid ""
"- Once an NPA planet hex is entered by an enemy ship, all NPA ships are "
"revealed and remain that way until the end of the game (unless captured, "
"21.12)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2171
msgid ""
"The first non-team player to the left of the active player makes "
"decisions on the alien targets. In solitaire or coop games, players "
"should make decisions on behalf of the NPA that will work towards the "
"aliens' victory over the player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2178
msgid "Conquering Alien Planets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2182
msgid ""
"Aliens do not normally get additional ships and are considered subdued "
"the moment they lose their last ship in combat. The (former) alien planet"
" can then be colonized normally by a player with Terraforming technology "
"(9.7)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2189
msgid "Boarding & Capturing Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2198
msgid "Properties of Boarding Ships (BD)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2202
msgid ""
"Boarding Technology allows the purchase of Boarding Ships. Boarding Ships"
" have the following properties:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2203
msgid "- May make Boarding Attacks (see below)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2204
msgid ""
"- If combat occurs in Asteroids or a Nebula, Boarding Ships still fire as"
" F-Class, not E-Class (5.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2205
msgid "- Like other ships, Boarding Ships always hit on a 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2206
msgid "- Boarding Ships may not mount Attack technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2213
msgid "Boarding Attacks"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2226
msgid ""
"A Boarding Ship's attack is handled differently than a regular ship's "
"attack. The Hull Size of the ship being attacked is subtracted from the "
"Attack Strength of the Boarding Ship. All other modifiers and "
"technologies are ignored (do not use Attack Tech, Defense Tech, Fleet "
"Size Bonus, etc.) except for Experience modifiers (37.0) and Security "
"Forces (20.0). If that \"To Hit\" number or less is rolled, the attacked "
"ship has been captured by the boarding parties (multiple hits are not "
"required to take over a ship – regardless of Hull Size, one successful "
"boarding attack will take over an enemy ship)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2227
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Veteran Boarding Ship (F5) is attacking a Legendary "
"Cruiser. The attack would succeed only on a roll of 1; that is 5 minus a "
"Hull Size of 3 (one larger for a Legendary Cruiser) minus an Experience "
"modifier of 1 (the target ship is 2 levels of Experience higher).</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2228
msgid ""
"Boarding Ships may attack each round regardless of the success or failure"
" of previous attempts. Boarding Ships may acquire Experience when they "
"successfully capture a ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2235 app/data/master_rule_book.py:3749
#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5163
msgid "Restrictions"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2239
msgid "The following restrictions apply to Boarding Attacks:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2240
msgid ""
"- Carriers (15.1) and Battle Carriers (38.6) are protected from being "
"targeted by their Fighters as for normal attacks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2241
msgid ""
"- Ships that are screened (5.7) from combat cannot be attacked and "
"therefore cannot be captured."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2242
msgid ""
"- Bases, <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases, Defense Satellite "
"Networks</mark>, Shipyards, Colonies, Titans, Fighters, Doomsday "
"Machines, Space Amoebas, Replicator ships (40.0), and Transport Ships "
"that are carrying <mark class=\"hl-blue\">any cargo</mark> may not be "
"captured and are instead engaged with a normal F1 attack if a Boarding "
"Ship fires on them. When using their F1 attack, Boarding Ships may get "
"the benefit of the Fleet Size Bonus but never benefit from Attack "
"technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2243
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-purple\"><strong>PLAY NOTE:</strong> Boarding Ships may "
"be boarded.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2254
msgid ""
"A ship captured by a boarding party immediately becomes controlled by the"
" capturing player. A captured ship has the following properties:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2255
msgid ""
"- May not attack or retreat in the first full round immediately following"
" capture (the boarding parties are in the process of gaining complete "
"control of the ship)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2256
msgid ""
"- Does not count for Combat Screening (5.7) or Fleet Size bonus (5.1.3) "
"on the round after they are captured."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2257
msgid "- May be fired upon, screened, and may be recaptured."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2258
msgid ""
"- May attack and retreat normally after the first round, post-capture. If"
" playing with Ship Experience (37.0), newly captured ships from other "
"players are Green (regardless of Military Academy level) but gain "
"Experience normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2259
msgid ""
"- If playing with Ship Experience, captured NPA ships (18.0) are always "
"<i>Green</i> and can never increase in Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2260
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">- Alternate Empire ships self-destruct when "
"captured, but yield a technology benefit. See [24.1] for details.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2267
msgid "Tracking Captured Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2271
msgid ""
"Until the end of the battle, a captured ship may be represented by "
"whatever spare counter is available. If either player has a free counter "
"of that unit type, it can be used. Barring that, a spare alien or other "
"counter may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2272
msgid ""
"At the conclusion of the battle, any surviving captured ships must be "
"switched over and represented by the player's own counters. A player "
"capturing a ship may have to scuttle other ships or combine other "
"counters to free up a Group counter to represent the captured ship "
"(7.3.2). If they are unwilling, they must scuttle the captured ship. If "
"it has the same technology as one of your Groups, the Group counters can "
"be combined."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2273
msgid ""
"The new Group of captured ship(s) must have the appropriate technology "
"marked on the Ship Technology Sheet like any other Group. The former "
"owner of the ship must inform the player of the current technology levels"
" on the sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2274
msgid ""
"Until upgraded or scuttled, a player must always identify a formerly "
"captured ship in battle. The original owner would recognize their former "
"ship, and this makes it easier for them to try to destroy it, preventing "
"its technology from falling into enemy hands.."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2281
msgid "Captured Ships & Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2285
msgid ""
"Captured ships may use all the technologies that they possess. However, "
"they may not give the technology to other ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2292
msgid "Scrapping Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2296
msgid ""
"If a captured ship is at a friendly Shipyard during an Economic Phase, it"
" may be scrapped for its technology. The scrapping player will gain one "
"level of technology in each area where the captured ship has better "
"technology, then the scrapped ship is removed. The player may "
"successively scrap multiple ships in the same Economic Phase to gain more"
" technology. The order in which they scrap ships is up to them. The "
"player may also purchase a level of a particular technology in the same "
"Economic Phase, either before or after scrapping a ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2297
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player with Movement 1, Attack 2, Defense 1, and Tactics 1 "
"captures a ship that has Movement 3, Attack 2, Defense 2, and Tactics 0. "
"Upon scrapping the ship, the player gains Movement 2 and Defense 2 "
"technology. If the player had another ship just like this one and "
"scrapped it also, they would immediately gain Move 3 technology. The "
"player could then choose to use CP to purchase Move 4 technology.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2298
msgid "The following restrictions apply to Scrapping technology:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2299
msgid ""
"- Scrapping a Carrier can only yield up to Fighter technology level 1, "
"regardless of the level of Fighter technology the other player possessed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2300
msgid ""
"- Ground Combat technology cannot be gained by scrapping a Transport "
"(21.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2301
msgid ""
"- Security Forces (20.0) and Military Academies (37.2) – both of which "
"are not shown on the Ship Technology Sheet – cannot be gained by "
"capturing a ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2302
msgid ""
"- Any technology gained is limited to what is present on the ship being "
"scrapped."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2303
msgid ""
"- In a game with more than two players and no teams, players cannot gain "
"technology by scrapping captured ships. This is to prevent gamey tactics "
"and/or collusion between players to advance their technology levels."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2304
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-purple\"><strong>PLAY NOTE:</strong> Ship Size "
"technology can be gained by this method.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2311
msgid "Captured Non-Player Alien Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2315
msgid ""
"NPAs (18.0) may be captured. These incur maintenance costs and may be "
"used like any of a player's ships. However, a player may never put any of"
" their technology on an NPA ship. They have the standard NPA technology "
"(18.2) in addition to Movement 3 technology. They may be scuttled (7.3.2)"
" but may not be scrapped to gain technology (19.5.1). If stacked with "
"friendly ships, it should be obvious which Empire owns them. If moved on "
"their own, they can be marked using one of the player's Empire markers "
"which have been provided for this purpose."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2322
msgid "Security Forces"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2326
msgid ""
"This technology is only used in conjunction with Boarding Ships. If a "
"player researches Security Forces 1, all of their ships immediately and "
"automatically get a +1 to their Hull Size when being attacked by a "
"Boarding Ship (a ship does not need to be upgraded to get this benefit, "
"9.11.3). Security Forces 2 doubles this benefit (+2 total). This "
"represents a player developing a coherent plan for dealing with Boarding "
"Ships and communicating it to their fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2327
msgid "All NPA ships (18.0) are equipped with Security Forces 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2334
msgid "Transports & Ground Combat"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2343
msgid "Transports"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2356
msgid ""
"At the start of game, all players have Ground Combat 1, allowing them to "
"build Transports and Infantry. Transports are used to carry Ground Units "
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">and Fighters (15.2). They may also be used to "
"transport Dilithium Crystals (see the Deep Space Planet Attributes) and "
"Logistic Points (36.5) if using those rules.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2357
msgid ""
"Transports do not need to stop to pick up or drop off Ground Units or "
"Fighters; they can pick them up while passing a planet in a similar way "
"to a CV picking up Fighters (15.2.3). <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Fighters "
"that were carried on Transports may not participate in combat that same "
"player turn, even if transferred to another ship or Colony.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2358
msgid "Transports have the following properties:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2359
msgid "- May not explore."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2360
msgid ""
"- <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Each may carry any combination of up to 6 "
"Ground Units and/or Fighters or 30 Logistic Points (36.5.6).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2361
msgid "- A loaded Transport may not be boarded (19.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2362
msgid ""
"- If a Transport is destroyed, its owner destroys any Ground Units, <mark"
" class=\"hl-blue\">Dilithium Crystals or Logistic Points</mark> now in "
"excess of Transport Capacity."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2363
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player has 2 Transports, 5 Space Marines and 3 Infantry "
"involved in a battle. One of the Transports is destroyed. The player must"
" remove 2 Ground Units because only 6 may fit on the remaining Transport."
" They choose to eliminate 2 of the Infantry.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2364
msgid ""
"- Transports participate in space combat normally. They may fire, may be "
"screened, etc."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2365
msgid ""
"- Transports cannot land units on a planet that is protected by Mines. "
"<i>(For Example: The <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Missed Rendezvous "
"#84</span> Resource Card combined with the <span class=\"text-uppercase"
"\">Anti-Sensor Hulls</span> Unique Ship Ability can lead to this quirky "
"situation.)</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2372
msgid "Upgrading Transports (Drop Ships)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2376
msgid ""
"When a player researches Ground Combat 3, their Transports may be "
"upgraded so that their Defense Strength increases from 1 to 2 (Armored "
"Transports). The Transports will also be equipped with \"Drop Ships,\" "
"which allow invading Ground Units to attack in the first round of ground "
"combat. In addition, the player may purchase Grav Armor."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2383
msgid "Ground Units"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2387
msgid ""
"Each Ground Unit represents a massive number of troops. Ground Units come"
" in 6 varieties: Infantry, Space Marines, Heavy Infantry, Militia, Grav "
"Armor, and Cyber Armor. Ground Units have the following properties:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2388
msgid "- Require no maintenance cost."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2389
msgid "- May not be placed on an uncolonized planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2390
msgid ""
"- Provide a defensive benefit against bombardment (21.6) and may not be "
"hit by bombardment (21.7.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2391
msgid ""
"- Ground Units play no part in space combat. Whether on a Colony or on a "
"Transport, they never shoot at ships, and they may never be shot at by "
"ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2392
msgid "- Are eliminated if not on a Colony or if in excess of Transport capacity."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2399
msgid "Purchasing Ground Units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2403
msgid ""
"A number of Ground Units equal to the CP number of a Colony may be "
"purchased at that un-blockaded Colony during an Economic Phase (no "
"Shipyard is needed for any)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2404
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Colony produced 3 CP that Economic Phase. Any mixture of "
"three Ground Units may be placed there after they are purchased.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2411
msgid "Militia"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2415
msgid ""
"Militia units are never purchased. They are temporarily awarded when a "
"Colony is invaded: 1 Militia per CP number on the Colony. This is in "
"addition to any Ground Units which are already on the planet. This "
"represents the police forces, etc., and the difficulty in conquering a "
"planet. Even if these Militia units are destroyed, if the planet is "
"subsequently invaded, it will again be awarded Militia units equal to the"
" CP on the Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2416
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A planet with a 3 CP marker on it will be temporarily awarded"
" 3 Militia units if attacked by Ground Units. A Homeworld could yield as "
"many as 30 Militia units!</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2423
msgid "Free Ground Units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2427
msgid ""
"A player receives one free Ground Unit for every three, un-blockaded 5 CP"
" Colonies (not the Homeworld) that they have at the start of an Economic "
"Phase (rounded down). This is in addition to any units that are "
"purchased. <i>Think of this as skimming off the population growth of the "
"more adventuresome colonists once the Colony is at full strength.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2428
msgid ""
"The free units are Infantry if at Ground Combat 1 when the units are "
"placed or they can be Heavy Infantry or Space Marines at Ground Combat 2 "
"(21.10). Grav Armor and Cyber Armor (38.7) can never be received for "
"free; they must be purchased (21.11). The free units are placed at any "
"un-blockaded 5 CP Colony or Homeworld, one per Colony. This does not "
"count against the purchased unit limit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2435
msgid "Planetary Defense"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2439
msgid ""
"Ground Units contribute to planetary defense. <i>Think of them as being "
"armed with lots of surface-to-air missiles that keep the bombarding ships"
" at arm's length.</i> If there are Ground Units besides Militia on the "
"planet when the Colony is being bombarded (21.7.4), the Colony is "
"considered to have a Defense Strength of 1 if there 1-3 Ground Units "
"present. With 4 or more Ground Units present it has a Defense Strength of"
" 2. Militia never contributes to bombardment defense."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2446
msgid "Landing Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2450
msgid ""
"If a player's units move into a Colony hex that contains enemy Ground "
"Units but no combat-capable ships, both sides are revealed immediately. "
"All unrevealed units moving into the Colony hex must be revealed; "
"however, an exception is made for RaiderXs (38.9) and the Ground Units "
"they may be carrying. Decoys are removed and the non-moving player must "
"eliminate non-combat ships if the moving player has combat ships present."
" The moving player may now decide whether they wish to continue moving or"
" stay in that hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2457
msgid "Reaction Movements in Response"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2461
msgid ""
"Since a Reaction Move (35.0) by the non-moving player can normally only "
"be made after the moving player has finished moving, the Reaction Move "
"would happen only after the non-moving player's non-combat ships had been"
" eliminated, and then only if the moving player decided to stay in that "
"hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2468
msgid "Determine Location of Ground Units"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2472
msgid ""
"If a player is defending in a hex with Ground Units, Transports, and a "
"friendly Colony, that player must decide after the fleets have been "
"revealed, but before combat, whether their Ground Units are on the planet"
" or on the Transports (or a mixture of both)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2479
msgid "Landing"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2483
msgid ""
"After the SECOND ROUND of space combat and after each round thereafter, "
"players may decide to land Ground Units on a Colony in that hex. Any "
"Ground Units on the Transports are simply placed on the planet (Ground "
"Combat will be resolved when Space Combat is done). A Transport may land "
"Ground Units this way even if it had been screened. If the planet is "
"Barren, then Ground Units may only be landed if their Empire has "
"Terraforming 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2484
msgid ""
"Regardless of whether Ground Units are landed, Transports remain in the "
"battle and the space combat continues as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2491
msgid "Bombardment"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2495
msgid ""
"After space combat is over and before ground combat occurs, the attacker "
"may decide to bombard the Colony (5.10) before landing any Ground Units. "
"Bombardment cannot take place once the attacker has landed any units. The"
" player may roll attacks against the Colony one at a time, reducing it, "
"until they decide to land their Ground Units. Once they have landed their"
" units, they may not bombard the Colony anymore that turn, even if the "
"invasion goes poorly."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2502
msgid "Ground Combat Procedure"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2506
msgid ""
"Ground combat is resolved after all space combat in the hex is finished. "
"Like space combat, Ground Units fire at each other in order of Weapon "
"Class (D-Class before E-Class), take damage, and are eliminated when they"
" take damage equal to their \"Hull Size\" <i>(not that Ground Units have "
"hulls, but for simplicity's sake they use the same metric).</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2513
msgid "Unused Mechanics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2517
msgid ""
"Ships, Fleet Size Bonus, Tactics, and Attack/Defense Tech have no effect "
"on ground combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2524
msgid "No Retreating"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2528
msgid ""
"Ground combat continues indefinitely until one side wins. There is no "
"Retreat from ground combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2535
msgid "Attacker Disadvantage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2539
msgid ""
"Ties in Weapon Class always result in the defender firing first. Any "
"Ground Units dropped off by Transports without Drop Ships (available with"
" Ground Combat 3), may not fire in the first round of ground combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2546
msgid "Ground Combat Screening"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2550
msgid ""
"Combat Screening (5.7) can be used in ground combat. Units that cannot "
"fire do not count when determining which units can be screened. A spare "
"counter of the appropriate type of unit can be used to place in the "
"\"screened units\" portion of the Battle Board (37.4.2). In the case of "
"Transports being used as <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Air Support "
"#25</span> (see the Card Manifest), a Transport can be screened provided "
"a spare Transport counter is available. A player is not limited by the "
"single <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Air Support #25</span> counter "
"provided. In the case of Militia or Heavy Infantry Militia (<span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Defending Familiar Terrain #76 #170</span>, see the "
"Card Manifest), a player may screen some of the Militia while leaving "
"some of them in combat by using any spare counter to keep track of how "
"many are being screened in each combat round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2557
msgid "Determine Victor"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2566
msgid "Defender Victory"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2570
msgid ""
"If the defender destroys the last attacking Ground Unit, the Colony has "
"been successfully defended and any remaining Militia units are removed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2577
msgid "Attacker Victory"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2581
msgid ""
"If the attacker destroys the last defending Ground Unit (including "
"Militia), the Colony has been successfully captured (21.13). To complete "
"the process, the attacker must remove one Ground Unit that is on the "
"planet (even if the attacker is recapturing a planet that was previously "
"their own.) The removal of this unit represents the permanent resources "
"needed to manage the captured Colony. The defeated Colony marker is left "
"in place and covered with one from the conquering player (21.13.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2582
msgid ""
"Any Shipyards, Bases, <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases, or Defense "
"Satellite Networks (14.0)</mark> at the Colony belonging to the defender "
"are destroyed. This means it is possible to drop Ground Units after the "
"second round of space combat, lose the space battle, yet still destroy "
"the above-noted units. In such a scenario, any of the defender's Fighters"
" in excess of the carrying capacity of their friendly "
"CVs/BVs/Titans/Unique Ships are lost if their Colony is captured. If an "
"enemy fleet remains in orbit, they may not bombard the Colony until their"
" turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2589
msgid "Space Marines & Heavy Infantry"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2593
msgid ""
"Require Ground Combat 2. Space Marines and Heavy Infantry have different "
"Weapon Classes and Attack Strengths when they are attacking or defending."
" Marines attack at C6 and defend at D5. Heavy Infantry attack at D4 and "
"defend at C6."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2600
msgid "Grav Armor"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2604
msgid ""
"Require Ground Combat 3. Grav Armor has a special ability beyond its "
"normal attack. At the start of each round of combat, for every Grav Armor"
" unit a player has over the amount that their opponent has, they can "
"provide support to one non-Grav Armor unit, including Militia (and "
"Transports if you have <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Air Support "
"#25</span>, see the Card Manifest). A supported unit gains one to its "
"Attack and Defense Strength. A unit can only be supported by one Grav "
"Armor unit per round. Units that cannot fire cannot be supported and are "
"not counted when determining how many units can be supported."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2605
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: The defender has 3 Grav Armor, 1 Space Marine and 1 Militia "
"on the planet. The attacker has no Grav Armor, so the defender can "
"support 3 units. As they only have 2 non-Grav Armor units the 3rd support"
" bonus is lost. The Space Marine will fire as a D6 unit with a Defense "
"Strength of 2 for this round. The Militia will fire as an E6 unit with a "
"Defense Strength of 1 for this round.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2612
msgid "Ground Combat Against Aliens"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2616
msgid ""
"Non-player Aliens (18.0) are a special case with several exceptions to "
"ground combat:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2617
msgid "- They may only be invaded if a player has Terraforming 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2618
msgid ""
"- They may not be invaded until their fleet is destroyed. This means that"
" Ground Units may not be landed after the second round of combat as is "
"usually allowed (21.7.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2619
msgid ""
"- After defeating the NPA fleet, the player may colonize it normally or "
"choose to invade."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2620
msgid ""
"- NPA Alien planets do not yield technology benefits other than the Alien"
" Technology cards (11.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2631
msgid ""
"The NPAs have 5 Militia units on the planet. If these are defeated, the "
"player places a 3 CP Colony of their color on the planet. If the NPAs are"
" not defeated in ground combat, the planet is considered subdued from "
"space and may be colonized normally; it may not be invaded later. A "
"player has only one shot to invade an NPA planet and that is immediately "
"after destroying its fleet. A player may NOT bombard the Colony to reduce"
" the number of Militia like they could with a human player (21.7.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2638
msgid "Amazing Diplomats"
msgstr "Diplomates Exceptionnels"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2642
msgid ""
"When a player invades a Colony on an NPA planet that was started by "
"another player using their <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Amazing "
"Diplomats #48</span> or <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats "
"#93</span> ability (see the Card Manifest), that Colony may be invaded "
"after Round 2 as normal. If the attacker wins the ground combat, any "
"remaining NPA ships still defending the planet that were not "
"boarded/captured by the attacker during space combat are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2649
msgid "Captured Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2658
msgid "Procedure and Properties"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2662
msgid ""
"Captured Colonies \"go backward\" one step of growth upon capture. A 5 CP"
" Colony becomes a 3 CP Colony, a 3 CP Colony becomes a 1 CP Colony, and a"
" 1 CP Colony is flipped back to its Colony Ship side. In this last case "
"it does not actually become a ship, it just reverts to that step in the "
"growth process. (This is the only time a Colony is ever flipped back to "
"the Colony Ship side.) It will grow to 1 CP in the following Economic "
"Phase. In the rare case where a Colony with only a Colony Ship would be "
"captured, replace the Colony Ship with one of the capturing player's. The"
" captured Colony is then treated like any of the capturing player's "
"Colonies. It will provide income and grow, Shipyards may be built, "
"Militia will be produced when attacked, etc. Any Minerals (6.7) and Space"
" Wrecks (6.8) that are on the Colony when it is captured are destroyed "
"with no benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2669
msgid "Captured Homeworlds"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2673
msgid ""
"A conquered Homeworld becomes a normal Colony (max 5 CP) for the "
"conqueror."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2680
msgid "Indicate Captured Status"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2684
msgid ""
"The Colony marker from the defeated player is left on the planet and "
"covered by the new owner because the captured status of the Colony "
"continues to impact the game. The original owner and their allies may not"
" attack their former Colony from space. If they want it back, they will "
"have to invade <i>(the planet is filled with their own colonists!)</i>. "
"If a player is eliminated, do not remove any Colony markers that they "
"have on the board that have been captured by another player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2691
msgid "Reveal Cards"
msgstr "Cartes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2695
msgid ""
"When a Colony is captured (not recaptured), the player who lost the "
"Colony must reveal to the capturing player all the Empire Advantages "
"(10.0) and Alien Tech cards (11.0) that they have at that moment."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2702
msgid "Capture in Enemy Home Systems"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2706
msgid ""
"When a Colony/Homeworld is captured (not recaptured) in an enemy player's"
" Home System, the capturing player may look at the enemy player's "
"Production Sheet and the capturing Empire immediately increases one level"
" in two technologies in which the other player is more advanced. This is "
"similar to capturing technology through scrapping captured ships except "
"that it happens immediately and not in the Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2713
msgid "Capture in Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2717
msgid ""
"If a Colony is captured (not recaptured) in Deep Space, it is handled the"
" same way as above, except that only one level of one technology may be "
"taken (capturing player's choice). If playing a scenario in which a "
"player's Home System markers are mixed with the Deep Space markers at "
"setup, then all Colonies besides the Homeworld count as Deep Space "
"planets for the purpose of this rule."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2724
msgid "Multiplayer Games"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2728
msgid ""
"In a multiplayer game that has no fixed teams you cannot gain technology "
"through capturing Colonies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2735
msgid "Recaptured Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2739
msgid ""
"If a player recaptures a Colony that was previously their own, they do "
"not get any technology benefit/increase. Once a Colony is recaptured by "
"the original owner, all other Colony markers are removed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2746
msgid "Capturing another Player's Captured Planet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2750
msgid ""
"If a third player captures a planet, they gain technology from the "
"original owner, not the current owner. The technology that can be gained "
"is only that which was researched by the original player at the time it "
"was originally captured. In multiplayer games, a note should be made of "
"the player's technology when the planet is captured in case this happens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2757
msgid "Titans"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2761
msgid "<i>Titans are massive ships – far larger than a DN.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2762
msgid ""
"A player must have Ship Size 7 Tech (9.4) to build a Titan. Titans have "
"the following properties:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2763
msgid ""
"- Each hit from a Titan does 2 damage to a single ship instead of 1. It "
"only gets 1 attack each round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2764
msgid "- May never be screened (5.7) due to their size."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2765
msgid "- May never retreat (5.9) from combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2766
msgid "- Are immune to Boarding Ships (19.2.2) due to their size."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2767
msgid ""
"- Unless the attacking ship is a Fighter, a roll of 1 is not an automatic"
" hit against a Titan. <i>It is therefore possible for some ships to not "
"be able to score a hit on a Titan, depending on the technologies on the "
"ships.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2768
msgid ""
"- Fighters receive +1 to their Attack Strength against Titans. This is in"
" addition to any modifiers from Attack Technology (9.2) and Fleet Size "
"(5.1.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2775
msgid "Fleet Size Bonus"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2779
msgid ""
"Which side gets the Fleet Size Bonus (5.1.3) is calculated normally for "
"the battle. However, when firing at the Titan, ships other than Fighters "
"do not get to claim the bonus."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2786
msgid "Can Carry Fighters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2790
msgid ""
"If the player with a Titan also has Fighter Tech, a Titan may carry 3 "
"Fighters in the same way as a Carrier (15.0). An existing Titan can be "
"upgraded to have this ability as soon as Fighter 1 is researched. "
"Although the Titan carries Fighters, it is not considered a Carrier. It "
"may be fired upon while friendly Fighters are still present in the "
"battle. In the unlikely event that a Titan is destroyed and there are "
"more Fighters left than can be carried on the remaining "
"CVs/BVs/Titans/Unique Ships/Advanced Flagships, the extra Fighters would "
"be eliminated at the conclusion of the battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2797
msgid "Planet Destroyers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2801
msgid ""
"A Titan may not attack a Colony like a normal ship would. When a Titan "
"fires at a Colony, the Colony and planet are both automatically "
"destroyed. Remove the planet from the game and replace it with one of the"
" Asteroid terrain tiles (5.8.1). This hex is now an Asteroid hex. A Titan"
" may fire at and destroy a planet that does not have a Colony on it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2808
msgid "Titans & Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2812
msgid ""
"Because of their great size, Mines (17.0) do not kill a Titan, but do one"
" point of damage each. It would take 5 Mines to kill a Titan. If a battle"
" immediately follows Mine detonation, then the Titan would enter that "
"battle with damage. Fighters carried by the Titan are immune to any Mine "
"damage unless the Titan is destroyed, which would destroy them. All "
"damage is repaired at the end of a battle as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2819
msgid "Flagships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2823
msgid ""
"Each player begins with one Flagship representing the crowning "
"achievement of an Empire (up to this point). A Flagship will always have "
"a 1 numeral marker underneath. Flagships have the following properties:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2824
msgid ""
"- Pays no maintenance but counts as Hull Size 3 for upgrading technology "
"(9.11.3) and damage (5.6)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2825
msgid ""
"- May have their technology upgraded normally, may gain Experience "
"(37.0), and function as any other ship in all other respects."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2826
msgid ""
"- May be upgraded to carry Exploration 1 (9.8) and Fast 1 (9.9) once they"
" are researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2827
msgid ""
"- If destroyed, it can never be rebuilt. The destruction of a Flagship "
"does not hurt an Empire in any other way – the player simply loses the "
"use of it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2834
msgid "Capture of Flagships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2838
msgid ""
"Flagships that are successfully boarded and captured (19.0) can be used "
"by the capturing player. In this case, the counter just continues to be "
"used by the capturing player. It operates like all other captured ships "
"except that it pays no maintenance. A separate note of its technology "
"will have to be kept on the Ship Technology Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2845
msgid "Names of Flagships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2849
msgid "The Flagships are the only ships in the game that are named:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2850
msgid ""
"- Enterprise (Blue) – <i>Besides the obvious sci-fi and space shuttle "
"connection, the aircraft carrier USS Enterprise (CVN 65) was in her last "
"deployment at the time of the Close Encounters first printing.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2851
msgid "- Victory – <i>The name of Admiral Nelson's flagship at Trafalgar.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2852
msgid ""
"- Thunder Child – <i>In H.G. Wells' book, War of the Worlds, this in an "
"ironclad ship that destroyed two Martian Tripods while covering the "
"escape of refugee ships.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2853
msgid ""
"- Argo – <i>From Greek mythology – Jason and the Argonauts. It was also "
"the American name given to the Space Battleship Yamato in the Japanese "
"movie \"Star Blazers.\"</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2854
msgid "- Fearless – <i>In \"honor\" of Honor Harrington's ship.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2855
msgid ""
"- Eagle – <i>First LEM on the Moon and the name of the spacecraft in "
"Space 1999.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2862
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Alternate Empires</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2871 app/data/master_rule_book.py:3343
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Introduction & General Rules</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2875
msgid ""
"Alternate Empires have ships with alternate costs and abilities than "
"those found in the base game. Up to two players can play Alternate "
"Empires at once or they can be played against original empires. The costs"
" and capabilities of their ships can be found on the Alternate Empire "
"Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2882
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Different Units</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2886
msgid ""
"Alternate Empires possess a new type of unit – Missile Boats (24.4). They"
" cannot research Fast 2 (9.9.2) and cannot build Titans (except for the "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">War Sun #187</span> Empire Advantage, "
"10.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2893
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Changes to Fighters</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2897
msgid ""
"Alternate Empires have advanced Fighters that do not require a ship to "
"carry them when they move. As a result, these Empires have no need to "
"(and cannot) build CVs (15.1) or BVs (38.6)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2898
msgid ""
"Alternate Empire Fighters function the same as other combat-capable "
"ships; When an Alternate Empire gets the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">On Board Workshop #56</span> Alien Technology Card (11.0), it"
" may be used on BBs and DNs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2905
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Changes to Boarding</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2909
msgid ""
"Alternate Empires do not have Boarding Ships (19.0). If their ships are "
"successfully boarded, they are destroyed instead of being captured. "
"However, every time a ship is successfully boarded, the boarding player "
"may steal one technology that was on the ship. If the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Self Destruct #68</span> Resource Card is played it prevents "
"this technology theft. A successful boarding attack still counts as "
"captured for the purpose of Ship Experience (37.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2916
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Random Special Ability Selection</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2920
msgid ""
"For Battlecruisers, Battleships, and Dreadnoughts a random special "
"ability is drawn and made available for that class of ship at the times "
"specified below. Each ability can be researched for a cost of 10 CP. Note"
" that the abilities must be researched before they are available to use. "
"When drawn, the number of the ability should be written on the player's "
"Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2921
msgid ""
"- Battle Cruisers: Draw a random special ability when Ship Size 4 is "
"researched. BCs do <i>not</i> automatically get Fast 1 (9.9)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2922
msgid ""
"- Battleships: Draw a random special ability when Advanced Construction 1"
" (38.0) is researched. BBs do not automatically get <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Tractor Beams</span> (p.45)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2923
msgid ""
"- Dreadnoughts: Draw a random special ability when Advanced Construction "
"1 is researched. DNs do not automatically get <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Shield Projectors</span> (p.45)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2924
msgid ""
"- Flagships: A Flagship may still be equipped with Exploration Technology"
" (9.8). However, instead of automatically getting Fast 1, it gets access "
"to the same special ability as the Battle Cruisers (see above) once it's "
"been researched. When upgraded to an Advanced Flagship (38.11), it may "
"pick an ability off the Unique Ship Table like any other Advanced "
"Flagship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2931
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Random Special ability table</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2935
msgid "[TABLE:random_special_ability]"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2942
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Missile Boats & Missiles</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2946
msgid ""
"<i>Although not equipped with standard weaponry, Missile Boats are a "
"highly effective addition to a player's fleet. Missile Boats fire early "
"in combat, but because they fire from a distance the warheads take some "
"time to hit their targets.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2953
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Missile Boat Characteristics</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2957
msgid ""
"MBs can mount up to Attack 3 despite their hull size, but are still "
"limited to Defense 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2958
msgid ""
"MBs are treated like DDs for the purpose of destroying a Space Amoeba "
"([SSB 3.0], [CSB 10.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2965
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Missile Boats in Combat</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2969
msgid ""
"Each Missile Boat in combat fires as an A-Class ship and launches one "
"Missile each round. Upon firing, place a Missile counter with numeral "
"marker indicating the number of missiles fired on the \"E\" section of "
"the Battle Area (5.1.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2970
msgid ""
"A Missile Boat may receive Ship Experience (37.3) if the Missile it fired"
" destroys an enemy unit. However, no Experience is gained for Missiles "
"that are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2977
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Missile Characteristics</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2981
msgid ""
"Between the moment they are fired and the moment they reach their target,"
" Missiles can be fired at. A Missile has the same Experience, Attack, and"
" Defense values as the ship which fired it. Similar to Missile Boats the "
"hull size doesn't limit their level of attack technology. Fleet Size "
"Bonus (5.1.3) applies to Missile attacks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2988
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Missiles in Combat</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2992
msgid ""
"Missiles are fired as if they are A-Class (their counter is put into "
"play) but their targets are selected and hit as if they are E-Class. This"
" represents the time between launch and impact. Once a Missile counter is"
" placed into combat it may be targeted like any other combat unit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2993
msgid ""
"During E-Class firing, Missiles resolve their attack like any other "
"combat unit.Missiles that hit their targets do 2 damage to a ship or "
"Colony and 1 damage to a Titan (22.0). After a Missile attacks, it is "
"removed from the board regardless of whether it hit its target."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2994
msgid ""
"If a Missile is fired as E-Class instead of A-Class due to terrain, it is"
" resolved immediately. These types of terrain affect the Attack and "
"Defense values of Missiles in the same way as all other units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:2995
msgid ""
"Doomsday Machines (29.0) do not fire on Missiles unless there are no "
"ships remaining. Missiles only do 1 damage to DMs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3002
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Jammer Technology</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3011 app/data/master_rule_book.py:3134
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Characteristics</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3015
msgid ""
"Jammer Technology can be researched by any Empire in order to counter "
"Missiles. Jammer Technology can only be equipped by Cruisers and is "
"unaffected by whether the ships already have Exploration Technology "
"(9.8). Jammer Technology for Replicator ships (40.0) is shown on the "
"Replicator Production Sheet. When firing at Missiles (not Missile Boats),"
" Replicators are always treated as having a Tactics level of 3."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3022
#, fuzzy
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Jammer Technology in Combat</mark>"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3026
msgid ""
"When a Cruiser with Jammer 1 is present in combat, the Attack Strength of"
" all enemy Missiles is reduced by 2. If at least two Cruisers equipped "
"with Jammer 2 are present in combat, the Attack Technology of all enemy "
"Missiles is reduced to 0. A single Cruiser with Jammer 2 only receives "
"the benefit of Jammer 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3027
msgid ""
"Cruisers and Replicator ships that are screened during a round of combat "
"can still provide the benefit of Jammer Technology during that round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3028
msgid ""
"Changes to Missile Attack Strength caused by Jammer Technology are "
"calculated each round when the first Missile attacks (during E-Class) and"
" that shift is used for all subsequent Missiles during that round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3035
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Additional Terrain</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3044
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Cosmic Storms</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3048
msgid ""
"<i>We are reminded how little we know about the universe every time a "
"Cosmic Storm rolls through.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3049
msgid "There are two types of Cosmic Storms: Plasma Storms and Ion Storms."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3056
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Movement</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3060
msgid ""
"Cosmic Storms are the only type of terrain that moves. At the end of "
"every Economic Phase, a die is rolled for every Cosmic Storm."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3061
msgid ""
"- On a roll of 1-6, the Storm will move to the resulting hex. If this "
"roll would cause the Storm to move to a forbidden hex or off the map, the"
" Storm will remain in its current hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3062
msgid "- On a roll of 7-10, the Storm will remain in its current hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3063
msgid ""
"They will only enter Deep Space hexes without terrain or containing the "
"following terrain:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3064
msgid "- Nebulae"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3065
msgid "- Asteroids"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3066
#, fuzzy
msgid "- Minerals"
msgstr "Parties"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3067 app/data/master_rule_book.py:3084
#, fuzzy
msgid "- Space Wrecks"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3068
#, fuzzy
msgid "- Doomsday Machines"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3069
msgid "- Black Holes"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3070
msgid ""
"If a Cosmic Storm enters a Black Hole hex, the Storm is destroyed and "
"removed from the board. Storms do not enter Folds in Space (25.2) but can"
" travel straight through them if the terrain in the destination hex "
"permits."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3077
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Plasma Storms</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3081
msgid ""
"Units must stop when they enter a Plasma Storm and may only move one hex "
"on the turn they leave a Plasma Storm. If a Plasma Storm is ever in the "
"same hex as the following it will destroy them immediately:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3082
msgid "- Ships that cost 9 CP or less except space pirates (25.7)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3083
msgid "- Replicator Type II Ships (and smaller)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3085
#, fuzzy
msgid "- Minerals."
msgstr "Parties"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3086
msgid ""
"Fighters are only destroyed if not enough transporting ships (15.2.3) "
"remain at any point, but they may not be used in fights in this hex. "
"Doomsday Machines are unaffected by Plasma Storms. Plasma Storms are "
"removed from the map if they move into a hex with a Space Amoeba or if a "
"Space Amoeba spreads onto them ([SSB 3.0], [CSB 10.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3087
msgid ""
"After a Plasma Storm leaves a hex, place a spare 5 CP Mineral Counter "
"face up in the hex (use a Home System Mineral counter already harvested "
"by a player)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3094
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Ion Storms</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3098
msgid ""
"All combat damage is doubled in Ion Storms (e.g., a Titan or a Missile "
"would normally do 4 damage with each hit). The first time a player "
"attempts to move their units out of an Ion Storm (including Reaction "
"Movement, 35.0, and Retreats, 5.9) they must roll a die. On a roll of a "
"9-10, none of their units may leave the hex that turn. This die roll "
"occurs only once per player turn per Ion Storm."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3099
msgid ""
"Doomsday Machines receive double damage but do not need to roll when "
"attempting to leave an Ion Storm. Amoebae are not affected by Ion Storms."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3106
msgid "Folds in Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3110
msgid ""
"When revealed, this counter stays on the map as a permanent effect. It "
"has the following characteristics:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3111
msgid ""
"- The hex containing this counter is treated as if it does not exist. "
"Ships never end their move in the hex. When moving through this hex, do "
"not count it. For example: A ship that can move two hexes that turn "
"starts adjacent to the Fold in Space. It moves into the Fold in Space and"
" can still move 2 more hexes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3112
msgid ""
"- A ship adjacent to the Fold in Space is considered adjacent to all "
"other hexes adjacent to the Fold in Space."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3113
msgid ""
"- Exploration technology can be used through a Fold in Space – even one "
"that was flipped earlier in that Exploration Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3114
msgid ""
"- MS Pipelines (13.0) can be traced through the Fold in Space, although "
"no MS Pipeline remains in the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3115
msgid ""
"- If a Fold in Space is explored by a ship entering the hex, that ship is"
" returned to the hex from which it entered. A ship may not be moved onto "
"a Fold in Space by a Lost in Space marker (6.6)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3116
msgid ""
"- Remove from the game a Fold in Space that is revealed adjacent to "
"another Fold in Space that was previously revealed. Do not replace it "
"with another marker."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3123
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Space Stations</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3127
msgid "<i>Heavily armed, automated platforms that attack on sight.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3138
msgid ""
"Space Stations do not move and must be defeated in combat if a player "
"enters the same hex. All Space Stations have Point Defense 2 (15.3) and "
"Scanner 1 (16.2) technologies, and they cannot be boarded (19.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3145
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Defeated Space Stations</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3149
msgid ""
"Players receive a benefit for destroying Space Stations based on their "
"type:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3150
msgid ""
"- A6-2-x2: Draw two Alien Tech cards (11.0) and keep one at no cost. If "
"not using Alien Tech Cards, gain 10 CP instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3151
msgid "- A5-1-x1: Gain 5 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3158
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Pulsars</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3162
msgid ""
"<i>The effects of a Pulsar's rapid fluctuations seem to be based on its "
"relation to the color spectrum.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3169
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Pulsar Characteristics</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3173
msgid ""
"All ships that spend an entire turn not moving in a Pulsar become Charged"
" and gain that Pulsar's benefit upon leaving it. If a player has units in"
" a Pulsar at the start of a turn, and no additional units enter the hex "
"that turn, mark the hex with a Charged marker. As long as there are ships"
" still within the Pulsar which are Charged no other friendly ship may "
"enter. However, other friendly ships may enter the Pulsar on the same "
"turn that the Charged ships leave."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3174
msgid ""
"If any ship leaves the Pulsar when Charged, the Charged marker is moved "
"with the ships and removed at the end of the turn and all friendly ships "
"must leave simultaneously, ending their movement in the same hex; this "
"will limit movement to the slowest ship leaving the Pulsar."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3175
msgid "Ships can never retreat from battle in a Pulsar."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3182
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Blue Pulsars (Movement)</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3186
msgid "Charged ships leaving a Blue Pulsar may move one additional hex that turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3193
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Red Pulsars (Attack)</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3197
msgid ""
"Charged ships leaving a Red Pulsar gain +1 to their Attack Strength that "
"turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3204
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Green Pulsars (Defense)</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3208
msgid ""
"Charged ships leaving a Green Pulsar gain +1 to their Defense Strength "
"that turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3215
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Quantum Filaments</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3219
msgid ""
"<i>Quantum Filaments are extremely dense astrophysical phenomena with "
"very high gravitational fields.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3226
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Movement Effects</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3230
msgid ""
"Due to the intense gravity present, ships must use one additional "
"movement hex to enter a Quantum Filament. Ships that can only move one "
"hex per Movement Phase cannot enter. A unit which reveals a Quantum "
"Filament and doesn't have the movement needed to enter must immediately "
"retreat to the hex it just left."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3231
msgid ""
"Alternate Empire Fighters (24.0) treat a Quantum Filament as if it is a "
"Super Nova (6.5)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3238
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Combat Effects</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3242
msgid ""
"Fighters must stay on the ship carrying them and therefore cannot be used"
" in combat in this hex. Cloaking tech will not work within a Quantum "
"Filament. Boarding Ships may not perform boarding attacks but may fire on"
" ships with a normal F1 attack. Ships may not retreat into a Quantum "
"Filament or enter it using Reaction Movement (35.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3249
msgid "Regional Maps"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3253
msgid ""
"This counter's effect only comes into play via a ship entering the hex. "
"If this counter is peeked at using Exploration technology, it must be "
"left face down. When this hex is entered and explored by a ship, the "
"counter is removed, and the exploring player may look at any face down "
"System markers in adjacent hexes. The player may reveal them or leave "
"them face down, just like they were looked at using Exploration "
"technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3260
msgid "Space Pirates"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3264
msgid ""
"<i>Space Pirates are interstellar nomads, technologically advanced in "
"both space travel and weaponry.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3265
msgid ""
"This counter's effect only comes into play via a ship entering the hex. "
"If this counter is peeked at using Exploration technology or a Regional "
"Map, it must be left face down. If an Alien Player fleet (SSB 4.0) or a "
"Doomsday Machine (29.0) reveals or peeks at a Space Pirate, remove the "
"Pirate from the board immediately."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3272
msgid "Restriction"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3276
msgid ""
"Do not use Pirates on maps where there are only two or fewer Deep Space "
"hexes between the players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3283
msgid "Fight or Hire"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3287
msgid ""
"When revealed, the player must state that they will fight or hire the "
"Pirate. If they decide to hire the Pirate, they pay 10 CP in the next "
"Economic Phase. These CP must be paid even if the Pirate is destroyed "
"before the next Economic Phase. Replicators must pay the CP immediately "
"or fight the Pirate. If the player decides to fight the Pirate, the "
"Pirate will not retreat. Similarly to Non-Player Aliens (18.0) the first "
"non-team player to the left of the active player decides the targets. If "
"the player retreats or is destroyed remove the Pirate from the board. If "
"the Pirate is hired the hiring ships are not revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3294
msgid "Controlling Pirates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3298
msgid ""
"The player that pays the 10 CP controls the ship until it is destroyed. "
"It acts exactly as any other ship except as noted below. Mark it with one"
" of the player's control markers. A controlled Space Pirate remains face "
"up for the rest of the game. A Player may only have one Space Pirate "
"under their control at a time. If a player while in control of a Space "
"Pirate reveals another Space Pirate, they must fight the newly revealed "
"Space Pirate."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3309
msgid "Space Pirates have the following characteristics:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3310
msgid "- Their stats are: A5-0-x1, Movement 4, Fast 1, & Tactics 0."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3311
msgid ""
"- If a Pirate is captured (19.3) it will automatically self-destruct. The"
" Boarding Ship (19.1) may still roll for Ship Experience in this case "
"(37.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3312
msgid ""
"- Space Pirates cannot be equipped with a player's technology and gain "
"none of the owner's Empire Advantage Abilities (10.0). They pay no "
"maintenance and cannot be scuttled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3313
msgid ""
"- The Space Pirates may stack and defend with a player's ships, but may "
"only attack alone."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3314
msgid ""
"- The Space Pirates may not be moved onto an unrevealed System marker by "
"the controlling player, even if other ships enter the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3315
msgid ""
"- Space Pirates are considered Skilled (37.0) and Experience may be "
"gained by destroying them (similar to Non-Player Aliens, 18.0), but Space"
" Pirates may not gain Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3316
msgid "- Space Pirates may not be scrapped (19.5.1) to gain any technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3323
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Quasars</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3327
msgid ""
"If combat is occurring in a System with a Quasar marker, both the Defense"
" Strength and Defense technology of all units in the combat are "
"considered zero. This represents the unexplainable effects of the "
"quasar's powerful radio waves on the combat systems of all units present."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3334
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Deep Space Planet Attributes</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3347
msgid ""
"Deep Space Planet Attributes provide additional challenge and flavor when"
" entering planet hexes in Deep Space. An Attribute counter is drawn and "
"revealed for each Deep Space planet when it is flipped. A counter is not "
"drawn if the planet is only scanned (returned face down) by a unit with "
"Exploration Technology (9.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3348
msgid ""
"Each counter has three pieces of information – an Attribute word followed"
" by two numbers separated by a slash. The first is the number of NPA "
"ships defending the planet. The second is the number of Heavy Infantry on"
" the planet (in addition to the standard 5 Militia, see [21.4]). A "
"complete list of Deep Space Attribute counters can be found in the \"Card"
" Manifest & Deep Space Planet Attributes\" booklet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3355
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Adjustments to Game Play</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3359
msgid "The following changes are made to Non-Player Aliens:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3360
msgid ""
"- Non-Player Aliens (18.0) must be included when using Deep Space Planet "
"Attributes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3361
msgid ""
"- Add the 20 new NPA counters to the supply (18.1). These new ships are "
"either A5-1-x2 or E7-1-x2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3362
msgid ""
"- All NPA ships with Hull Size 2 have Scanner 1 (16.2). However, they "
"will only use this ability when attacked. They will not stop cloaked "
"fleets that enter their hex and do not attack unless they are <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Aggressive #p1</span>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3363
msgid ""
"- <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats #48</span> or <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats #93</span> (see the Card "
"Manifest) gain the NPA's Heavy Infantry (as noted on the counter) when "
"colonizing, even if a planet's Deep Space Planet Attribute is later "
"removed. This Heavy Infantry <i>does</i> provide the normal defensive "
"bonus against bombardment (21.6)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3370
#, fuzzy
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Scenario Modifier Cards</mark>"
msgstr "Modificateurs de scénarios"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3374
msgid ""
"Scenario Modifier Cards can be used to provide considerable variety to a "
"game of Space Empires. During set up, two cards are randomly selected one"
" at a time. If the second card drawn conflicts with the first, it is "
"discarded and replaced with a new one. Both cards are in effect for the "
"entire game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3375
msgid ""
"If using these in the same game as Empire Advantages (10.0), the Scenario"
" Modifiers should be selected first. A complete list of Scenario Modifier"
" Cards can be found in the Card Manifest."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3382
msgid "OPTIONAL RULES"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3386
msgid ""
"Most of these rules can greatly change the game. They are not recommended"
" until players are familiar with the game, but they can be an enjoyable "
"change of pace as players become more experienced. All, some, or none of "
"the following optional rules can be used in a game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3393
msgid "Optional Deep Space Discoveries"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3402
msgid "The Galactic Capitol"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3406
msgid ""
"<i>An incredibly strong planet of a highly developed and peaceful "
"race.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3413
msgid "Usage and Restrictions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3417
msgid ""
"This counter can be used in some of the available co-op scenarios. If "
"used in a co-op scenario, use the rules as given in that scenario. In "
"competitive play, use the rules set out below. The Galactic Capitol may "
"also be placed in a specific hex of any multiplayer scenario. "
"Alternatively, it may also be mixed randomly into the Deep Space "
"counters, but that could lead to an imbalanced game. (See [CSB 2.10] for "
"an example layout.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3428
msgid "The Galactic Capitol has the following characteristics:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3429
msgid ""
"- It is a neutral space. No combat ever takes place in that hex. Both "
"combat and non-combat ships of all players may enter, pass through, and "
"end their turn in the hex (ignoring the units of other players)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3430
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">- Because combat is forbidden, Replicators do not"
" gain RPs from other ships in this hex.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3431
msgid ""
"- Players may not leave Fighters (15.2) or Ground Units (21.2) on that "
"planet, but they may be in the hex if they are on a ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3432
msgid ""
"- A fleet may, if otherwise able, retreat into the hex (5.9). The "
"presence of enemy units at the Galactic Capitol does not block retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3433
msgid ""
"- In a <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Planetary Gate (CSB 9.0)</span> "
"Scenario, the Galactic Capitol is treated as if it does not have a gate."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3440
msgid "Trade with the Galactic Capitol"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3444
msgid ""
"Players may trade with the Galactic Capitol by connecting their Homeworld"
" to it via MS Pipelines. Doing so yields 5 CP (not 1 CP) of income during"
" each Economic Phase. It is possible that multiple empires will "
"simultaneously earn this trade benefit (since it is a neutral hex). The "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Traders #49</span> Empire Advantage (10.0)"
" would earn 6 CP even though the Galactic Capitol is not a colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3451
msgid "Warp Points"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3460
msgid "Warp Point Availability"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3464
msgid ""
"There are six Warp Point markers in the game – three \"Warp Point 1\" "
"markers and three \"Warp Point 2\" markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3471
msgid "Warp Point Usage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3475
msgid ""
"Warp Points cannot be used until another Warp Point with the same number "
"has been discovered. Once a pair of matching Warp Points is discovered, "
"the third matching Warp Point counter of that number is discarded for no "
"effect if found. If no other Warp Point of the same number has been "
"discovered, the Warp point is ignored (treat the space as if it were "
"empty)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3482
msgid "Warp Point Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3486
msgid ""
"Warp Points affect movement by allowing ships to travel through them. If "
"a ship is in a System containing a Warp Point, it may move to any other "
"System containing the other Warp Point with the same number, regardless "
"of distance traveled, as if the two Systems were adjacent. Moving in this"
" way is optional, not mandatory."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3487
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A ship that can move 3 hexes starts its turn adjacent to a "
"Warp Point. It first moves into the System containing the Warp Point. At "
"this point it can continue moving to another adjacent System as if the "
"Warp Point was not there or it can move to a System containing another "
"Warp Point with the same number. If it did that, it would still have one "
"movement remaining to continue movement after arriving at the other Warp "
"Point.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3494
msgid "Warp Points and MS Pipelines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3498
msgid ""
"MS Pipelines (13.0) may connect through a Warp Point. Warp Points are "
"considered adjacent in all ways. Therefore, if two Warp Points (with the "
"same number) both share hexes with a merchant ship, the pipeline extends "
"through the Warp Point, just like it would with any adjacent hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3505
msgid "Retreating"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3509
msgid ""
"Warp Points of the same number are considered adjacent in every way, "
"including retreats."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3516
msgid "Doomsday Machines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3520
msgid ""
"Doomsday Machines are used in specific solitaire and cooperative "
"scenarios following the rules contained therein. However, they can also "
"be added to competitive play using the following alternative rules."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3527
msgid "Doomsday Machine Availability"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3531
msgid ""
"There are three Doomsday Machines (DMs) in the Deep Space System markers."
" Players need to agree on the number of DMs that will be included in the "
"game. When playing with this optional rule, a DM is not removed when "
"flipped, but stays active on the map until destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3538
msgid "Doomsday Machine Combat"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3542
msgid ""
"If flipped by normal exploration, a DM immediately attacks the exploring "
"ship(s). A DM is C-Class and gets 2 attacks per round. It has an Attack "
"Strength of 9, a Defense Strength of 2, and a Hull Size of 3. Players do "
"not get the 2:1 Fleet Size Bonus (5.1.3) in combat against a DM and "
"should not roll on any of the Doomsday Machine Weakness Tables in the "
"Solo-Coop Scenario Book. Unlike in solitaire/co-op scenarios, DMs recover"
" all damage at the end of a combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3543
msgid ""
"A player that destroys a DM immediately gets to roll twice on the Space "
"Wreck table <mark class=\"hl-blue\">and keeps both results.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3544
msgid ""
"In competitive scenarios, Doomsday Machines have Tactics 2, Scanner 2 and"
" a roll of 1 counts as a hit against them. Mines will detonate if a DM "
"moves into their hex, but the DM will take no damage. DMs are immune to "
"Fighters (their weaponry is too small to affect them), but they can still"
" protect their Carriers. Boarding Ships (19.0) must attack with a basic "
"F1 attack against DMs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3551
msgid "Doomsday Machine Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3555
msgid ""
"DMs move each turn after all players have moved (including the turn it is"
" flipped). DMs will move up to 2 hexes towards the nearest planet, "
"Asteroid, or ship within 2 hexes (stopping on it). If there is more than "
"one of those that is equidistant from the DM, then roll randomly to "
"determine which one it moves onto. Each space that qualifies has an equal"
" chance of attracting the DM. If a DM moves to an NPA planet (18.0), it "
"will attack the aliens normally. A DM will not end its move on an "
"unexplored hex or in a hex with another DM, but it will move through "
"them. If there are no planets, Asteroids, or ships within 2 hexes, the DM"
" will move one hex in a random direction and end its turn (if that would "
"move the DM to an illegal destination, reroll). A DM will not move into "
"or through a hex with an Amoeba (CSB 10.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3556
msgid ""
"Regardless of planets or ships, a DM will never move into a hex that was "
"part of a player's Home System (did not originally contain a Deep Space "
"System marker). This does not apply in variable map scenarios (CSB 3.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3563
msgid "Doomsday Machine Effects"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3567
msgid ""
"If there are ships in a hex with a DM, the DM will immediately attack "
"them. DMs may be attacked by other players normally. After combat, if a "
"DM is in a hex with an Asteroid or planet (with or without a Colony), the"
" DM will destroy it. Remove it and any Colony from play. DMs get no "
"benefits from destroying planets or Asteroids. <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">DMs are affected by Quasars (25.8) and Ion Storms (25.1.3) as "
"normal. All other terrain has no effect on DMs.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3574
msgid "Instant Technology Upgrade"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3578
msgid ""
"For players who do not like the bookkeeping required for upgrading "
"technology, it can be agreed that all existing ships are instantly "
"upgraded to a newly purchased level of technology. An assumption can be "
"made that each ship is equipped with on-board facilities to upgrade their"
" technology based on information being communicated from their home "
"planet. This is then accomplished during the large amounts of time that "
"transpire each turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3585
msgid "Black Hole Slingshot"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3589
msgid ""
"A ship that enters a System with an already revealed Black Hole (6.3) may"
" declare that it is going to try a \"Slingshot\" effect. This must be "
"declared before the die is rolled to determine if the ship is lost due to"
" the Black Hole. If this is declared, modify the Black Hole survival roll"
" by +2 (a ship is 20% more likely to be destroyed if the slingshot is "
"attempted). If it survives, the ship gains an extra point of movement for"
" that turn only. This represents ships moving closer to the event horizon"
" (more risk) to take advantage of the gravitational properties to sling "
"shot them forward. The use of MS Pipeline benefits may not be combined "
"with the Black Hole slingshot."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3596
msgid "Research Gearing Limits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3600
msgid ""
"<i>Realistically, an Empire cannot go from a zero commitment in "
"researching technologies to an all-out commitment overnight.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3601
msgid ""
"- A player may only spend 10 more on research than he spent the previous "
"turn. For example, a player spent 15 CP on research. The next turn he may"
" spend 0 to 25 on research. Note that if he does spend 0 on research, the"
" following turn he will be able to spend a max of 10. <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">Do not use Facilities (36.0) when playing with Research Gearing "
"Limits.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3608
msgid "Unpredictable Research"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3612
msgid ""
"This rule inserts an element of chance into technological development. "
"There's no guarantee your scientists will be able to make that "
"breakthrough you need, right when you need it. When using this special "
"rule, players do not use the normal Production Sheet, but must copy the "
"special one provided at the end of the CSB."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3619
msgid "Research Funding"
msgstr "Ressources"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3623
msgid ""
"During the Economic Phase, instead of purchasing a technology level, you "
"must spend CP to fund research. You may do this in increments of 5 CP, "
"and each increment is called a \"grant.\" Each grant allows you 1 die "
"roll. <i>For example, if you spend 10 CP on funding, you roll two "
"dice.</i> Funding must be specific to each technology. You must note on "
"your Production Sheet the number of grants allocated to each technology "
"type (such as Tactics, Movement, Attack, and so forth)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3630
msgid "Results"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3634
msgid ""
"After you roll each die funded by your grants, you note the sum of the "
"die rolls on the Production Sheet. If the sum is equal to or greater than"
" the cost of the technology level, you immediately acquire that "
"technology (you may apply it to spaceships you purchase this turn). If "
"it's lower, you keep whatever you rolled and will be able to add to it "
"during the next Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3635
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player who purchases five research grants is attempting to "
"research Attack 1, a technology which costs 20 CP. They spend 25 CP, "
"allocating four of the grants (at 5 CP each) to that technology by "
"circling numbers 1, 2, 3, and 4 underneath \"Attack 1\" on the Production"
" Sheet. They allocate the fifth grant to a different technology. They "
"roll the first four dice and get 7, 5, 6, and 8 for a total of 26. They "
"then write the results of each roll in the space next to the numbers they"
" circled. Since Attack 1 costs 20 CP, a total of 20 \"research\" is "
"needed to acquire Attack 1. The player's total of 26 means the technology"
" is completed and \"Attack 1\" is circled on the Production Sheet. The "
"extra 6 points (the difference between 20 and 26) is wasted. Had the "
"rolls yielded 7, 5, 6, and 1 (for a total of 19), the research would not "
"have been sufficient to complete the technology. During the next Economic"
" Phase, they would need to purchase another research grant and allocate "
"it to \"Attack 1\" (by circling the number 5). In this example, success "
"the following turn would be guaranteed because only 1 would be needed to "
"get to 20. Sometimes it is wise to allocate more research rolls than you "
"might need if you absolutely must have a certain technology that "
"turn.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3642
msgid "Research Funding Limits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3646
msgid ""
"An Empire cannot go from a zero commitment in research to an all-out "
"commitment overnight. For this reason, a player may only purchase a "
"maximum of two more research grants than they purchased the previous "
"turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3647
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player spent 15 CP to purchase three research grants. The "
"next turn he may purchase up to five research grants. Note that if they "
"purchase zero research grants, the following turn they will only be able "
"to purchase a max of two.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3654
msgid "Terraforming Nebulae"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3658
msgid ""
"Terraforming 2 technology may be purchased after Terraforming 1 (9.7) "
"with this optional rule. While not strictly terraforming, advancements in"
" Terraforming technology allow a player to set up and harvest resources "
"from Nebulae."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3669
msgid ""
"A Miner which is in a Nebula during the Economic Phase and is connected "
"by an MS Pipeline chain (13.2.2) to the Homeworld produces 5 CP each "
"Economic Phase. The Miner represents the science teams, mining teams, and"
" equipment needed to extract the resources from a Nebula. Any Miner which"
" is collecting CP from a Nebula should be flipped to the side with the "
"\"5\" showing as a reminder to collect the income during the Economic "
"Phase. Only one Miner may claim the 5 CP in a given Nebula each Economic "
"Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3676
msgid "Recording Nebulae Income"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3680
msgid ""
"This income should be recorded in the Mineral section of the Production "
"Sheet. Income from Terraforming 2 in Nebulae is not modified by any other"
" Variants, Resource Cards (39.0), Empire Advantages (10.0), or Alien "
"Technologies (11.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3687
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3691
msgid ""
"The Miner needs to have been built after Terraforming 2 technology was "
"researched or needs to be upgraded. On the Production Sheet, right next "
"to where you circle Terraforming 2, there is a 1, 2, 3, 4. Each of these "
"numbers can be circled when the corresponding Miner is built with or "
"upgraded to Terraforming 2 technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3698
msgid "Reaction Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3707
msgid "Exploration Technology Sensors"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3711
msgid ""
"Exploration 1 technology (9.8) may now be upgraded to Exploration 2 "
"technology. Once upgraded (9.11.3) this allows Bases (8.1), Shipyards "
"(8.2), CAs, Flagships (23.0), Battle Carriers (38.6.2), and Unique Ships "
"with Exploration Technology to respond to a battle in an adjacent hex and"
" send ships with the Reaction Ability to reinforce the battle. This is "
"called Reaction Movement. Ships with the Reaction Ability are listed in "
"[35.3] below. Although Bases and Shipyards are automatically upgraded "
"with Exploration 2, they do not gain the benefits of Exploration 1 (9.8)."
" Battle Carriers also do not gain the benefits of Exploration 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3722
msgid ""
"After an opposing player has finished their movement phase (4.0), a ship "
"with the Reaction Ability that is in the same hex as a unit that is "
"equipped with Exploration 2 technology may make a Reaction Move – it may "
"move one hex to join battle. As many ships that are able to make this "
"move may do so, including any ship that enabled this move. The decision "
"to make this reaction move must happen before fleets are revealed and "
"before any combats are resolved. Ships that react to join a battle are "
"part of the defending force in the battle in every way (it is like they "
"were in the hex to begin with). The following restrictions apply to "
"Reaction:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3723
msgid ""
"- The Reaction Move can only be made into a battle hex – one that "
"involves units from both sides. A friendly Colony that had enemy forces "
"move in that turn qualifies as a battle hex. Non-combat ships that are "
"not accompanied by a friendly combat-capable ship do not qualify as a "
"battle hex as they've already been removed at this point."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3724
msgid "- Ships in a hex with enemy units may not React."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3725
msgid ""
"- Reaction moves may NOT be made through Warp Points (28.2) or <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates #63</span> (p.45)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3726
msgid ""
"- All Reaction Movement is completed before any combat is resolved and "
"prior to the active player deciding the order that combats are resolved."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3733
msgid "Units Which May React"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3737
msgid "The following Ships have the React Ability:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3738
msgid "- At Movement 3 (and higher) SCs, DDs, CAs, and Rs get the React ability."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3739
msgid ""
"- At Movement 4 (and higher) Flagships, BCs, BDs, and MBs get the React "
"ability."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3740
msgid ""
"- At Movement 5 (and higher) BBs, CVs, BVs, Unique Ships, and Transports "
"get the React ability."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3741
msgid "- At Movement 6 (and higher) DNs and Minesweepers get the React ability."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3742
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-purple\"><strong>PLAY NOTE:</strong> On the Ship "
"Technology Sheet, an R appears in the place of the Move technology number"
" to remind the player that the Group gets the React ability at that Move "
"technology.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3753
msgid ""
"Reaction Movement only allows one hex of movement by the reacting ships "
"per player turn, even with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Advanced Comm "
"Array #28</span> (see the Card Manifest)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3754
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If the reacting ships are in B10, they MUST end their "
"movement in one of the following hexes: C9, C10, B9, B11, A9, or A10. "
"Note that a Fold in Space counter could boost the number of hexes that "
"can be reacted to.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3761
msgid "Facilities (IC/RC/LC/TC)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3765
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Using Facilities will add some time and "
"bookkeeping to the game, but each Facility type will provide valuable "
"abilities and reward careful planning. For a simpler game, players may "
"agree to not play with LCs and/or TCs.</mark> Different Production Sheets"
" are provided for use with this rule."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3772
msgid "Adjustments to Game Play"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3776
msgid "When playing with this rule, the following adjustments should be made:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3777
msgid "- Use the 20 CP Homeworlds."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3778
msgid "- Do NOT use Terraforming Nebulae (34.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3779
msgid "- Do NOT use Research Gearing Limits (32.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3780
#, fuzzy
msgid "- Do NOT use Replicators."
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3781
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">- Homeworlds start with 1 RC (Research Center) "
"and 1 Logistic Center (or just 1 RC if playing without LCs). Each player "
"will receive 20 CP, 5 RP, and if playing with Logistic Centers (36.5), 5 "
"LP during the first Economic Phase of the game.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3788
msgid "Common Properties"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3797
msgid "Construction/Removal"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3801
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Each Facility costs 5 CP to build and does NOT "
"provide its benefit during the Economic Phase in which it's built. "
"Facilities can be built at any non-blockaded, friendly Colony (or "
"Homeworld) that has at least a growth marker of 1. Each Colony can "
"support a single Facility of any type, while Homeworlds are able to "
"support two.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3802
msgid ""
"Facilities may be removed by their owner during an Economic Phase BEFORE "
"they provide their benefit (CP/RP/LP/TP). A new Facility may be built in "
"the same Economic Phase in which another Facility is removed, but it will"
" not provide a benefit until the next Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3803
msgid ""
"Facilities are destroyed when a Colony is eliminated or if the planet is "
"captured by Ground Units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3810
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Effects on Income</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3814
msgid ""
"When a Colony with a Facility generates income, the entire amount of "
"income is the type generated by the Facility. This does not apply to the "
"Homeworld! The Homeworld will always produce 20 CP plus whatever is "
"produced by the Facilities on it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3815
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Colony generates 1 CP in an Economic Phase and grows to 3 "
"CP. At the same time, an RC is built on the Colony. In the next Economic "
"Phase, the Colony will generate 3 RP and the Facility will produce 5 RP. "
"No CP is produced.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3816
msgid ""
"This also applies to any CP produced by other means (e.g. Resource cards)"
" unless specifically excepted (<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Police "
"State #162</span>)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3817
msgid ""
"Income generated by MS Pipelines and Minerals is never converted by the "
"presence of a Facility; it is always CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3824
msgid "Industrial Centers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3828
msgid ""
"Industrial infrastructure improvements provide much needed support for an"
" Empire's war efforts."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3829
msgid ""
"In future Economic Phases, each IC provides 5 CP. These may be "
"accumulated and used like any other CP. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">ICs do "
"not allow players to exceed the carry-over limitation of 30 CP per "
"Economic Phase (7.5.2).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3836
msgid "Research Centers"
msgstr "Ressources"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3840
msgid ""
"An investment in future technologies may decide the fate of an Empire. "
"RCs require the player to plan out research spending more deliberately "
"and will force them to continue researching technology when things "
"escalate into heavy combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3841
msgid ""
"In future Economic Phases, each RC provides 5 Research Points (RP) which "
"are tracked on the Production Sheet. Only RP can be used to research "
"technology (9.1). If playing with this rule <mark class=\"hl-blue\">CP "
"cannot be converted to RP or used to buy technologies.</mark> Up to 30 RP"
" can be carried over to the next Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3848
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Logistic Centers</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3852
msgid ""
"LCs provide a more realistic need for supply lines, making it more "
"difficult to confront the enemy with full force right from the beginning "
"of the game. Care must be taken to support fleets in enemy territory to "
"avoid them getting cut off and lost during the Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3853
msgid ""
"In future Economic Phases, each LC provides 5 Logistic Points (LP) which "
"are tracked on the Production Sheet. There is no limit to how much LP can"
" be carried over between rounds. LP is used instead of CP to pay "
"maintenance costs (7.3, Refits (9.11.3) are still paid for using CP). "
"Playing with LCs can often lengthen the game as it restricts how far "
"forward fleets can be sent without reducing their effectiveness."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3854
msgid ""
"Supply Range is only checked at the appropriate step of the Economic "
"Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3861
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Changes to Economic Phase</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3865
msgid ""
"During each Economic phase when it is time to pay maintenance costs (7.3)"
" first check if each Group is in supply range (36.5.2) and if not place "
"an Out of Supply marker (36.5.5) on it. This is done even for Groups that"
" would pay 0 maintenance (e.g. <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids "
"#43</span>, Flagship)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3866
msgid ""
"For each Group that is in Supply Range of a friendly Colony or in the "
"owner's Home System pay maintenance as normal, except that it is paid "
"with LP instead of CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3867
msgid ""
"In case that not enough LP are available the player must convert CP to LP"
" at a rate of 3 to 1. (<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race "
"#34</span> may convert the first 5 LP at 1 to 1 rate; any additional "
"deficit is converted at the 3 to 1 rate as normal.) If a player has "
"insufficient LP and CP to pay all maintenance, then the player's net "
"income is zero as per [7.3]."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3868
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A player has ships with a total maintenance cost of 26 LP in "
"Supply Range but only has 20 LP available. The player must spend all "
"their available LP in addition to 18 CP to avoid any ships being Out of "
"Supply (see below). If playing the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Giant "
"Race #34</span>, they could convert 5 CP to 5 LP, leaving 1 LP to be paid"
" by spending 3 CP.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3869
msgid ""
"Bidding for turn order (7.4) is unmodified, except that LP instead of CP "
"are used for the bidding."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3876
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Supply Range</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3880
msgid ""
"Ships within a number of hexes of a friendly Colony as determined by the "
"player's Supply Range Technology are considered to be in Supply Range."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3881
msgid ""
"Supply Range may be traced into, but not through, hexes with enemy Units "
"or Colonies, including NPA units (18.0) (except it may be traced through "
"on <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Organia #p3</span> if playing with Deep"
" Space Planet Attributes (26.0)). Supply Range may be traced into, but "
"not through, hexes with Super Novas (6.5), Space Stations (25.3), Quantum"
" Filaments (25.5), Cosmic Storms (25.1), Black Holes (6.3), or unexplored"
" System Tiles (2.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3882
msgid ""
"Supply Range may be traced through Warp Points (28.2) and <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates #63</span> (p.45) in the same way movement"
" is counted."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3883
msgid ""
"MS Pipelines generally do not impact Supply Range. However, Supply Range "
"can be traced through a Black Hole if 2 MS Pipelines are used:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3884
msgid "- A first one that is adjacent to the Black Hole."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3885
msgid "- A second one in the Black Hole hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3892
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Supply Range Exceptions</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3896
msgid ""
"Non-combat ships do not need to be in Supply Range. Ground Units are not "
"impacted by Supply Range."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3897
msgid ""
"Scouts, Raiders, and Space Pirates are always considered to be in Supply "
"Range."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3898
msgid ""
"A ship with Exploration technology (9.8) is always considered to be in "
"Supply Range if both of the following are true:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3899
msgid ""
"- It is in a Deep Space hex with no other friendly ships present (not "
"even other ships in the same Group)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3900
msgid ""
"- It has not ended a Movement Phase in a hex with another friendly combat"
" ship since the previous Econ Phase (7.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3907
#, fuzzy
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Supply Range Technology</mark>"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3911
msgid ""
"This technology determines how far ships can be from a friendly Colony "
"and still automatically receive supply."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3918
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Out of Supply (OoS)</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3922
msgid "Effects of being OoS:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3923
msgid "- The Group pays no maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3924
msgid "- The Group can only move one hex per turn during the Movement Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3925
msgid ""
"- Each ship in the Group gets -3 to its Attack Strength, to a minimum of "
"1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3926
msgid ""
"- Each ship in the Group gets -3 to its Defense Strength, to a minimum of"
" 0."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3933
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Placing OoS</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3937
msgid ""
"When paying maintenance, each Group that is not in Supply Range is given "
"an OoS marker. Each ship in the Group must roll a die. On a roll of 9-10 "
"it is eliminated (check if sufficient space for Fighters (15.2) and "
"Ground Troops (21.2) remains on other ships in the hex and if not, "
"eliminate to accommodate)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3944
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Removing OoS</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3948
msgid "OoS markers are removed in two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3949
msgid ""
"- When paying maintenance during a future Economic Phase (7.3) if the "
"Group is in Supply Range."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3950
msgid ""
"- A Logistic Group (36.5.6) on the board is used to pay maintenance. This"
" can only happen during the owning player's turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3957
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Logistic Groups</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3961
msgid ""
"Unused LP can be carried over from turn to turn with no limit or may be "
"placed on the board in groups of 5. For each 5 LP subtracted from a "
"player's Production Sheet, place a Logistic Group counter on the map at a"
" Colony with a Logistics Center. Numeral markers can be used; for "
"example, a Logistic Group with a numeral 3 counter under it could be used"
" to represent 15 LP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3962
msgid ""
"Transports that are not carrying Ground Units or Fighters are able to "
"carry up to 30 LPs (a Logistic Group with a 6 under it) and may pick them"
" up from a Colony just like they would Ground Units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3963
msgid ""
"LP placed on the board must be spent for the maintenance of Groups in the"
" same hex as the LP if they're out of Supply Range. However, LP must be "
"spent in groups of 5 with no change given (there are some inefficiencies "
"in the process.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3964
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A fleet out of Supply Range is composed of 5 CA, 1 Transport,"
" and 1 Logistic Group with a 4 under it (representing 20 LP). The "
"maintenance of this Group is 11 so 15 LP must be expended (4 LP was "
"wasted). The Supply Group now has a 1 under it (representing 5 LP).</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3965
msgid ""
"If there is not enough LP available to pay for the maintenance of all "
"ships in the hex, then the owner must choose which Groups(s) will be "
"marked Out of Supply."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3966
msgid ""
"A player may split Groups up if maintenance can be paid for some ships, "
"but if they cannot or chose not to then the entire Group is marked OoS "
"and needs to roll for elimination (36.5.5.1) even if maintenance was paid"
" for some of the ships in it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3967
msgid ""
"Being in the same hex as a Logistic Group does not automatically count as"
" being in Supply Range (but it may be in Supply Range as normal)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3968
msgid ""
"An LP Group is eliminated if it is on a Transport or a Colony that is "
"destroyed or Captured with Ground Troops (21.13)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3975
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Temporal Centers</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3979
msgid ""
"Temporal Centers represent a critical, advanced technology – the small-"
"scale manipulation of time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3980
msgid ""
"In future Economic Phases, each TC provides 5 Temporal Points (TP) which "
"are tracked on the Production Sheet. TP is spent to activate Temporal "
"Effects using a player's Temporal Engines. There is no limit to how much "
"TP can be carried over between rounds."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3987
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Temporal Engines</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3991
msgid ""
"All Bases (8.1), Advanced Bases (38.3), Starbases (38.5), and Shipyards "
"(8.2) are fitted with Temporal Engines."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3992
msgid ""
"Additionally, randomly determine a ship type at the start of the game: "
"Make a face down mix of counters from one Empire containing one each of "
"the following: SW, T, SC, DD, CV, and CA. Randomly turn one counter face "
"up to determine which ship type will carry Temporal Engines for all "
"players this game. Each player circles that ship type on their Ship "
"Technology Sheet as a reminder. If CV is selected, any player using an "
"Alternate Empire circles MB instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:3999
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Temporal Effects</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4003
msgid ""
"All available Temporal Effects are listed on the Temporal Effect Table "
"(p.46). The location of a player's Temporal Engines determines where that"
" player may activate Temporal Effects, as indicated on the table. "
"Temporal Effects can be activated during that player's turn and during "
"combat involving that player. When the order of activation is relevant, "
"the attacker must decide on spending TP first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4004
msgid ""
"Unless otherwise specified, Temporal Effects may be used as many times as"
" a player can afford using TP, but each effect can only be used on a "
"specific ship one time each turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4005
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: Redline the Engines could be used on a ship to move one extra"
" hex and enter a battle, but not two extra hexes. In the ensuing battle, "
"Reroute Targeting Computers could also be used on that Group one "
"time.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4012
msgid "Ship Experience & Military Academies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4021
msgid "Ship Experience"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4034
msgid ""
"There are five levels of Experience in the game (in order): <i>Green, "
"Skilled, Veteran, Elite, and Legendary</i>. Experience is not tracked by "
"ship, but by Group. When using this rule, every ship in a Group must have"
" the same type, technology level AND Experience. On the Ship Technology "
"Sheet, each Group has room for tracking Experience. More Groups of each "
"type have been included to facilitate this."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4041
msgid "Combining Groups"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4045
msgid ""
"Two Groups that could normally combine (same tech, etc.) may do so, but "
"if the Experience level of the two Groups differ, the resulting Group has"
" the lower Experience of the combining Groups."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4052
msgid "Military Academies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4056
msgid ""
"If not playing with Ship Experience, then Military Academies are not "
"used. Military Academies improve the skill of new ships:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4057
msgid ""
"- If a player has not researched Military Academies, all of their new "
"ships start as <i>Green</i>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4058
msgid ""
"- If a player has researched Military Academy level 1, all of their new "
"ships start as <i>Skilled</i>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4059
msgid ""
"- If a player has researched Military Academy level 2, all of their new "
"ships start as <i>Skilled</i> and all of their ships (including existing "
"ones) are more easily promoted."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4066
msgid "Gaining Experience"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4070
msgid ""
"Only Groups that have a section to track Experience on the Ship "
"Technology Sheet gain Experience. E.g. Bases and Shipyards do not gain "
"experience despite participating in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4077
msgid "Green Groups"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4081
msgid ""
"At the very start of the Economic Phase (before CP are collected), each "
"<i>Green</i> Group on the board is promoted to <i>Skilled</i>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4088
msgid "Experience Rolls"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4092
msgid ""
"Each Group may gain Experience whenever it destroys/captures a unit. When"
" the Group is done firing, one die is rolled for <i>each</i> unit "
"destroyed/captured by that Group. (But see [37.4.1] for exceptions). If "
"any of these die rolls are less than or equal to <i>twice the Hull "
"Size</i> of the destroyed/captured ship, then the Group that "
"destroyed/captured the ship gains a level of Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4093
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If the destroyed/captured ship has a Hull Size of 2, then a "
"die roll of 1-4 would gain Experience for the Group.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4100
msgid "Modifiers to Gaining Ship Experience"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4104
msgid "Modify any given Ship Experience die roll by the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4105
msgid ""
"-1 if the destroyed/captured ship has a larger Hull Size than the firing "
"ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4106
msgid "-1 if the side with the firing unit has Military Academy level 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4107
msgid "These modifiers are cumulative."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4118
msgid ""
"Gaining Experience happens immediately before the next Group fires. Only "
"one level of Experience may be gained by a Group in each battle. To track"
" this, when a Group gains a level of Experience, only put a half circle "
"around the next Experience letter and do not complete the circle until "
"the battle is complete. Groups that newly gain Experience should be moved"
" up halfway to the next row on the Battle Board – this makes it easier to"
" see which Groups can still gain Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4119
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: Player A has a Group of 5 DDs firing against 3 CAs. The DDs "
"are Skilled and Player A has Military Academy 2. The DDs roll 4 hits, "
"destroying 2 CAs. Player A rolls a die for each ship destroyed and needs "
"to roll a 4 or lower on one of the dice to gain Experience (the CAs have "
"a Hull Size of 2, doubled to 4). One is subtracted from the die roll "
"because the ship destroyed is larger than the firing ship, and one is "
"subtracted from the roll because of Military Academy 2. Player A rolls a "
"1 and a 3. The DDs are promoted to Veteran and moved halfway to the "
"Veteran row on the Battle Board.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4126
msgid "Multiple Groups"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4130
msgid ""
"If a player has multiple Groups that are firing at the same time, he may "
"fire them in any order, but must finish firing one Group before moving to"
" the next."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4137
msgid "Aliens"
msgstr "Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4141
msgid ""
"All Non-Player Alien (NPA) ships are considered to be <i>Skilled</i>. "
"Experience can be gained by attacking NPAs (18.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4148
msgid "Benefits of Experience"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4152
msgid "Experience provides the following benefits:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4153
msgid ""
"- If a Group has more Experience than the Group it is firing against, its"
" Attack Strength is increased by 1 for that attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4154
msgid ""
"- If a Group has 2 or more levels of Experience than a Group that is "
"firing at it, the Attack Strength of the firing ship is decreased by 1 "
"for that attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4155
msgid ""
"- A Group may not fire at a Group that has 3 or more levels of Experience"
" than them unless all remaining enemy Groups have 3 or more levels of "
"Experience than them. If that is the case, they may only fire at the "
"least Experienced Groups."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4156
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Group of Green DDs is faced by a Group of Veteran SCs and a"
" Group of Elite CAs. The DDs may fire only at the SCs (and their Attack "
"Strength will be decreased by one for the attack) until only the Elite "
"CAs are left.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4157
msgid ""
"- Elite and Legendary Groups pay half maintenance (rounded down). If that"
" Group would have already paid half maintenance because of other rules "
"(e.g., <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Low Maintenance #149</span>, see "
"the Card Manifest), then they pay no maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4158
msgid ""
"- Ships in a Legendary Group require one more hit to destroy than normal."
" For the purpose of Boarding Ships (19.0), their Hull Size is considered "
"to be one larger. This benefit is gained even if being fired upon by a "
"Shipyard, Base, or other unit that normally does not gain Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4159
msgid "<i>EXAMPLE: A Legendary Cruiser would require three hits to destroy.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4166
msgid "Groups That Cannot Gain Experience"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4170
msgid ""
"Bases (8.1), <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases (38.5), Defense Satellite "
"Networks (14.0)</mark>, Shipyards (8.2), and Ground Units (21.0) are not "
"affected by Experience. They do not gain Experience, are not penalized "
"when shooting at Experienced ships (the exception being that "
"<i>Legendary</i> ships still take an extra hit to destroy), Experienced "
"ships gain no benefit when firing at them, and ships do not gain "
"Experience when destroying them. Players do not get to roll for "
"Experience when they destroy a Doomsday Machine (29.0) or Space Amoeba "
"([SSB 3.0] or [CSB 10.0]). Units that cannot gain Experience are not used"
" to calculate which units the enemy can fire on based on their Experience"
" level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4177
msgid "Battle Board"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4181
msgid ""
"The Battle Board was included to make it easy to see the benefits of "
"Experience in a battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4188
msgid "Advanced Construction"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4197
msgid "Introduction & Procedures"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4201
msgid ""
"<i>Advanced Construction (AC) allows for the production of new ship "
"designs and technologies not usually available to the player.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4202
msgid ""
"Alien Technology cards (11.0) or Empire Advantage cards (10.0) that "
"impact the normal version of a ship have the same effect on any Advanced "
"and X versions of that ship type."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4203
msgid ""
"Advanced and X versions of ships gain the React Ability at the same "
"Movement technology as the normal version of that ship (35.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4204
msgid ""
"Advanced Construction cannot be researched until the Economic Phase after"
" a player <u>actually</u> builds a ship that requires at least Ship Size "
"4 (BC, BB, Unique Ship of that size, etc.). Like other technologies, "
"Advanced Construction levels must be purchased in numerical order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4205
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-beige\">DESIGNER NOTE: This is a thematic thing that "
"also makes the timing right. It adds options to the Raider and Fighter "
"tech lines, but not right away. This brings the DDs, Fighters, and "
"Raiders back into the late game. If Fighters and Raiders are curve balls,"
" F4/BV and RX are curve balls late in the count.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4212
msgid "Advanced Construction 1"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4216
msgid "Costs 10 CP and allows a player to do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4217
msgid ""
"- Build DDX ships (38.3) and <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Advanced Bases "
"(38.4)</mark>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4218
msgid ""
"- Research <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Tractor "
"Beams</span><sup>+</sup> to mount on BBs.<sup>*</sup>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4219
msgid ""
"- Research <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Shield "
"Projectors</span><sup>+</sup> to mount on DNs. Any ship with a <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Shield Projector</span> cannot be protected by "
"another ship with a <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Shield "
"Projector</span>, regardless of the type of ship.<sup>*</sup>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4220
msgid ""
"- Research Attack 4 to mount on Titans <mark class=\"hl-blue\"> and "
"Starbases</mark> (adds 4 to their Attack Strength). Attack 3 must also be"
" researched before Attack 4. ONLY Titans (22.0) and <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">Starbases (38.5)</mark> may mount Attack 4.<sup>*</sup>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4221
msgid ""
"<sup>*</sup> <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Tractor Beams</span>, <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Shield Projectors</span>, and Attack 4 are "
"independent of each other and do not have to be researched in any "
"specific order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4222
msgid "<sup>+</sup> See Unique Ship Table 3 on page 45."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4229
msgid "Advanced Construction 2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4233
msgid ""
"Costs 10 CP and allows a player to build <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">Starbases (38.5), Cyber Armor (38.7)</mark>, Battle Carriers "
"(38.6.2), Fighter 4 (if researched, 38.6.1), and the four MinerX counters"
" (38.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4240
msgid "Advanced Construction 3"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4244
msgid ""
"Costs 10 CP and allows a player to build RX ships (38.9), the SCX (38.10)"
" counter, and upgrade their Flagship to an Advanced Flagship (38.11)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4251
msgid "Conventions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4255
msgid ""
"When the word <i>Advanced</i> is used it means that a non-advanced unit "
"of that type may be upgraded to the Advanced version. <i>For example: "
"Advanced Bases, Advanced Flagships.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4256
msgid ""
"When X is added to the end of a type it means that a non-advanced unit of"
" that type may NOT be upgraded to the X version. <i>For example: DDX and "
"RX.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4263
msgid "DestroyerX (DDX)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4267
msgid ""
"DDX use the same counters as DDs. However, DDs may not be upgraded to "
"DDX. They may be built the turn AC 1 is researched. Circle the DD Group "
"<mark class=\"hl-green\">number</mark> on the Ship Technology Sheet to "
"show that the Group is DDX."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4268
msgid ""
"DDX may be equipped with one more level of Attack and Defense than their "
"Hull Size would normally allow and Fast 2 (9.9.2) technology if "
"researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4269
msgid ""
"All DDX are equipped with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heavy "
"Warheads</span> (p.45)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4276
msgid "Advanced Bases"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4280
msgid ""
"Advanced Construction 1 instantly converts all a player's Bases to "
"Advanced Bases. This does two things:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4281
msgid ""
"- Advanced Bases are equipped with Exploration 2 technology (if "
"researched, 35.1) and Scanners (if researched, 16.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4282
msgid ""
"- Advanced Bases may be built in any hex connected to a Colony by an MS "
"Pipeline, even if there is no planet there. This is treated exactly like "
"a Base at a Colony in every respect (pays no maintenance, only one per "
"hex, cannot be boarded, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4283
msgid ""
"If the Pipeline is disrupted after the Base is built, the Base is "
"unaffected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4290
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbases</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4299
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbase Characteristics</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4303
msgid ""
"Starbases become available after AC 2 is researched but cannot be built "
"directly. An Advanced Base can be upgraded to a Starbase (A7-3-x4, 2 "
"attacks) at a cost of 12 CP. Starbases cannot move and do not incur "
"maintenance costs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4304
msgid ""
"A Starbase provides the same benefits as one Shipyard for the purposes of"
" ship production and refitting. Because of this, upgrading a Base to a "
"Starbase counts as the one Shipyard that a Colony is allowed to build "
"during an Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4305
msgid ""
"Starbases automatically mount Attack 4 (if researched, 38.1.1) and "
"Exploration 2 (if researched, 35.1)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4312
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbase Restrictions</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4316
msgid ""
"A Colony that is upgrading a Base to a Starbase must have produced at "
"least 5 CP during the same Economic Phase not counting Facilities (36.0)."
" An Advanced Base that is upgraded to a Starbase must have been built in "
"the previous Economic Phase. An Advanced Base may not be upgraded to a "
"Starbase if a DSN (14.0) was placed in the hex in the same Economic "
"Phase. A Colony may not have both an Advanced Base and a Starbase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4317
msgid ""
"A Starbase built by a player with the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">On "
"the Move #58</span> Empire Advantage may not move. Starbases cannot be "
"built in Deep Space even if an Advanced Base was built in the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4324
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Starbase Combat</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4328
msgid ""
"Starbases may not retreat and cannot be boarded. Each hit from a Starbase"
" does 1 Damage, but they get two attacks each round. Starbases may target"
" the same or different Groups with both attacks. Enemy units do not get a"
" Fleet Size bonus when firing at a Starbase, but the Starbase can benefit"
" from the Fleet Size bonus if on the side with more units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4335
msgid "Fighter 4 and Battle Carriers (BV)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4339
msgid ""
"Fighter 4s and BVs may be built the turn AC 2 is researched. Fighter 4 "
"must still be researched as well in order to build Fighter 4s (although "
"only Fighter 1 and AC 2 are necessary to build BVs)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4346
msgid "Fighter 4"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4350
msgid "Upgrades Fighters one more level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4357
msgid "Battle Carriers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4361
msgid ""
"Can carry 6 Fighters and are treated as CVs (15.1) in all respects (a "
"card that gives half maintenance to CVs would also give BVs half "
"maintenance)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4362
msgid ""
"BVs can be equipped with Fast 2 (9.9.2) and Exploration 2 (35.1) "
"technology if researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4363
msgid ""
"BVs are equipped with the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Anti-Sensor "
"Hulls</span> technology (p.45), making them immune to Mines. However, it "
"does not make their Fighters immune to Mines."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4370
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Cyber Armor</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4374
msgid ""
"When AC 2 and Ground Combat 3 (21.0) have been researched, the player may"
" build Cyber Armor. A Cyber Armor unit counts as 3 Grav Armor units for "
"support purposes (21.11). Neither Grav Armor nor Cyber Armor themselves "
"can be supported."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4375
msgid ""
"<i>Example: During ground combat, an attacker has 2 Space Marines along "
"with 1 Cyber Armor and 2 Grav Armor (combined, the equivalent of 5 Grav "
"Armor). The defender has 6 Grav Armor and 5 Militia. With 1 more Grav "
"Armor than the attacker, the defender can support 1 Militia.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4382
#, fuzzy
msgid "MinerX"
msgstr "MinerX"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4386
msgid ""
"When AC 2 is researched, the player may build the 4 MinerX Counters "
"(MinerX 5-8). They are treated exactly as normal Miners with the "
"following exceptions: They are not limited to having a Move of 1, and "
"they automatically upgrade to the player's latest Move and Terraforming "
"technology. The original four Miner Counters may still be used but may "
"not be upgraded to MinerXs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4393
msgid "RaiderX (RX)"
msgstr "Aides"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4397
msgid ""
"RX use the same counters as Rs (16.1). However, Rs may not be upgraded to"
" RX. RX may be built the turn AC 3 is researched if Cloaking has also "
"been researched. Circle the R Group <mark class=\"hl-"
"green\">number</mark> on the Ship Technology Sheet to show that the Group"
" is RX."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4398
msgid ""
"RX may be equipped with one more level of Attack and Defense than their "
"Hull Size would normally allow, as well as Fast 2 (9.9.2) technology if "
"researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4399
msgid ""
"Each RX may carry 1 Ground Unit and can be equipped with Drop Ships if "
"Ground Combat 3 is researched (21.1.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4400
msgid ""
"The Ground Unit is deployed as if the RX was a Transport in all other "
"respects, but note that the RX don't count as Transports for game effects"
" (E.g. <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Air Support #25</span>, see the "
"Card Manifest)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4401
msgid ""
"If the RXs take advantage of the Movement Advantage (16.1.1) and are not "
"revealed then any Ground Troops carried by them are also not revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4408
msgid "ScoutX (SCX)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4412
msgid ""
"When AC 3 is researched, the player may build the ScoutX Group (SCX <mark"
" class=\"hl-green\">group</mark> 7). The original six SC counters may "
"still be used as normal after researching AC 3, but SCs may never be "
"upgraded to SCX. The SCX <mark class=\"hl-green\">group</mark> 7 Group "
"acts as a Scout counter in every way except that it is equipped with a "
"Movement technology three levels higher than what is assigned to them (to"
" a maximum of Move 7)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4413
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: The SCX <mark class=\"hl-green\">group</mark> 7 Group is "
"built when the player has Move 2 available. They are considered to have "
"Move 5. Later on, the player researches Move 3. When the SCX <mark class"
"=\"hl-green\">group</mark> 7 Group is upgraded to Move 3, they are "
"considered to have Move 6.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4414
msgid ""
"Once the SCX <mark class=\"hl-green\">group</mark> 7 Group is built with "
"or upgraded to Move 7, it confers no additional benefit and can be "
"combined with SC Groups subject to normal technology and Experience "
"matching requirements."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4415
msgid "Your Decoys do not gain any movement bonus from AC 3."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4422
msgid "Advanced Flagship"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4426
msgid ""
"After AC 3 is researched the player may upgrade his Flagship (23.0) to an"
" Advanced Flagship. As per [9.11.3], the cost is 3 CP. The Flagship "
"counter is removed and replaced with the Flagship A counter, all of its "
"technology is upgraded to current levels, and the player may pick one "
"special ability from Unique Ship Table 3 on page 45 (write it in the "
"margin next to the Flagship on the Ship Technology Sheet). This ability "
"may not be changed later, though additional tech that the Flagship may "
"mount can be put on the Advanced Flagship during a later upgrade. The "
"Flagship (still) may never be rebuilt if destroyed. If your Flagship is "
"captured, you must give the capturing player your Advanced Flagship "
"Counter so that they will have it available if they upgrade the captured "
"Flagship later."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4433
msgid "Stealing Advanced Tech"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4437
msgid ""
"Fighter 4 and Advanced Construction may not be stolen or gained by any "
"means except by researching them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4438
msgid ""
"By scrapping Advanced ships or \"X\" ships, players may gain any of the "
"following that were present on the ship: Attack, Defense, Tactics, "
"Exploration, Fast, Scanners, Cloaking, Fighter 1, Point Defense, or "
"Movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4439
msgid ""
"The only Ship Size that can be gained from scrapping an Advanced or \"X\""
" ship is Ship Size 2 from a DDX."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4440
msgid "Players may not gain any Movement tech from an SCX."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4441
msgid ""
"Players may steal Tractor Beam, Shield Projector, or Attack 4, but until "
"they research AC 1 they cannot mount these technologies on their ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4448
msgid "Resource Cards"
msgstr "Ressources"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4461
msgid ""
"Resource Cards add an extra element of flavor, strategy, and "
"unpredictability to the game. They are meant to be a change of pace that "
"can be optionally added into the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4468
msgid "Resource Card Management"
msgstr "Ressources"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4477
msgid "Create a Resource Deck for Each Player"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4481
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Split the resource cards into equal decks for "
"each player. Any leftover cards are not used in this game.</mark> Each "
"player shuffles their deck and places it face down near them. Each player"
" has their individual deck of Resource cards and their own discard pile. "
"Normally each player only has access to their own piles. Looking through "
"discard piles of any player is allowed at any time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4488
msgid "Drawing Cards"
msgstr "Cartes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4492
msgid ""
"Before the start of the game, each player draws the top three cards from "
"their deck. At the start of each Economic Phase, players may draw one "
"(and only one) Resource Card from their deck unless it is exhausted. A "
"player may choose to not draw a Resource Card in a turn (to avoid going "
"over their hand limit) but may not look at the Resource Card before "
"deciding to draw it and does not get to draw bonus cards in future turns."
" Once exhausted, a player's deck is not reshuffled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4499
msgid "Hand Size Limit"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4503
msgid ""
"A player may have <mark class=\"hl-blue\">no more than 6</mark> Resource "
"Cards in their hand after the completion of an Economic Phase. Discard "
"any cards over this limit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4510
msgid "Using Resource Cards"
msgstr "Ressources"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4514
msgid "There is no limit to the number of cards that can be played."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4521
msgid "Order of Play"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4525
msgid ""
"After drawing and looking at their new card, players may play one or more"
" cards that are playable at the start of the Economic Phase, in reverse "
"turn order. Once every player has drawn and played, each player gets one "
"chance to play Cancel Cards (39.3.5) in reverse turn order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4532
msgid "Events or CP"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4536
msgid ""
"Each card can be played for its event OR it may be discarded to a "
"player's own discard pile for the CP value on the card (see below). All "
"cards are played/discarded face up and seen by all."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4543
msgid "Discarding Cards for CP"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4547
msgid ""
"Cards can be discarded for their CP value at the start of your player "
"turn or during the Economic Phase (see below). Some cards have two values"
" listed for CP; use the lower value if <i>any</i> player is playing the "
"Replicators. The value of cards discarded for CP should be recorded on "
"the \"+ Minerals CP\" line of the Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4554
msgid "CP during the Economic Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4558
msgid ""
"The discarding of cards for their CP value during the Economic Phase (and"
" the playing of the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Research Breakthrough "
"#77</span> card – a special case) are not done until after the turn order"
" bid for the round is completed. This way, players bid for turn order "
"without knowing whether other players will play or discard any cards "
"during that Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4565
msgid "Cancel Cards"
msgstr "Cartes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4569
msgid ""
"Four of the cards in the deck are Cancel Cards which can be played for "
"the event written on them or discarded to cancel any Resource Card except"
" <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Research Breakthrough #77</span> (see the"
" Card Manifest) and Mission Cards (39.3.6) which was just played for its "
"event. When a Cancel Card is discarded in this way, the event written on "
"the Cancel Card is ignored. Cancel Cards discarded in this manner cannot "
"be cancelled by other Cancel Cards. However, it is possible to cancel a "
"Cancel Card if it was played for its written event."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4570
msgid "Resource Cards being discarded for CP cannot be cancelled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4577
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Mission Cards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4581
msgid ""
"Mission Cards sometimes require an objective to be completed on the map. "
"They cannot be cancelled by Cancel Cards. Players can earn various "
"rewards when completing Mission Cards. Use the Mission Benefit Table "
"(next) when indicated to determine the reward. All Mission Benefit Table "
"rolls are made openly."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4582
msgid ""
"A player may play a Mission Card on themselves anytime the card indicates"
" they may do so, but Mission Cards cannot be played on an opponent until "
"after Economic Phase 5. Completed Mission Cards are removed from the game"
" instead of being discarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4583
msgid ""
"If a Mission Card requires a player to reveal a ship, that ship may "
"already be revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4584
msgid ""
"All Mission Cards can be played for 2 CP instead of their normal effect; "
"in this case they are added to the player's discard pile like other "
"Resource Cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4585
msgid "<i>Do not use Mission Cards in games involving Replicators.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4592
msgid "Mission Benefit Table"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4596
msgid "[TABLE:mission_benefit]"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4603
msgid "Sequence of Card Play"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4607
msgid ""
"In cases where several players can play cards for events, the sequence of"
" when cards are played is determined by reverse turn order. Once each "
"player has had a chance to play cards for events, they each get one "
"chance to discard and activate Cancel Cards, again in reverse turn order."
" You may <i>discard</i> multiple Cancel Cards at the same time, but you "
"must specify which cards you are canceling."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4608
msgid ""
"Some cards' events will indicate that they cannot be played unless the "
"player discards another Resource Card unused from their hand. Such "
"discards are not completed until all Cancel Cards are resolved. If a "
"card's event is cancelled, then its discard cost is no longer required. "
"No additional discard cost is required in order to discard a card for its"
" CP value."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4609
msgid ""
"In cases where the card is played in response to a specific event, the "
"other players get one chance to use a Cancel Card in reverse turn order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4610
msgid "Played cards are placed faceup in that player's discard pile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4617
msgid "Replicator Resource Cards"
msgstr "Ressources"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4621
msgid ""
"Several cards have specific events that are only for Replicators. A non-"
"Replicator player cannot use these Replicator events. Likewise, the "
"Replicator player cannot use the non-Replicator events."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4632
msgid ""
"All of the special conditions related to each Resource Card could not fit"
" on many of the cards. Always check the Card Manifest to verify that you "
"completely understand your Resource Cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4639
msgid "Legalese"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4643
msgid ""
"You can probably skip this section when first reading the rules, but "
"hopefully this will help you resolve any difficult situations and rules-"
"lawyering regarding these cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4644
msgid "- A Resource Card is <i>played</i> to get its effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4645
msgid "- A Resource Card is <i>discarded</i> to get its value in CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4646
msgid ""
"- A Resource Card being used as a Cancel Card is <i>discarded</i> in "
"order to cancel another card that was <i>played</i>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4647
msgid ""
"- Cancel Cards can only be used to cancel <i>played</i> cards; hence they"
" cannot affect cards <i>discarded</i> for CP or cancelling. The ONLY "
"exceptions to this are the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Research "
"Breakthrough #77</span> card and Mission Cards, which cannot be cancelled"
" even though they are <i>played</i>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4648
msgid ""
"- When a card is played that can have multiple uses at the time it is "
"played, it is not announced which use it is being played for until Cancel"
" Cards are resolved."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4649
msgid ""
"- In cases where a card affects an attack, it must be played when the "
"attack is announced. The defender can then play any cards that affect the"
" defense. Then Cancel Cards are used in reverse player order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4650
msgid ""
"- For cards that are played during combat, you must have combat-capable "
"units involved in the combat to allow you to play any cards in that "
"combat. Two exceptions are <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Alien "
"Reinforcements #90</span> and <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Defending "
"Familiar Terrain #76 #170</span>. These can be played by a player that "
"does not have combat-capable units in a hex with NPAs that are being "
"attacked by another player. NPA ships are considered your ships if you "
"have captured them or if you have a Colony or any other unit in the same "
"hex as them. Space Pirate ships that have your Empire marker under them "
"are considered your ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4651
msgid ""
"- <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Coup #106</span> is played after combat "
"and thus can be played by a player that did not have ships in the combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4652
msgid ""
"- One or more cards that may usually be played at the start of your turn "
"may be played after Exploration technology is used, and before any of "
"your ships move."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4653
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: It is perfectly legal for Bob to play the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Play Dead #102</span> card when Jim destroys one of his BCs "
"and then for Jim to play <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Splash Damage "
"#110</span> to generate possible hits on Bob's remaining ships. Despite "
"the flavor text, Bob's BC is considered dead unless he wins the fight. "
"Jim does get to roll for Experience and play <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Splash Damage #110</span> as normal, and any Experience gain "
"persists even if Bob wins the fight.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4654
msgid "- Card Titles and Flavor Text do not supersede the Effect of the Card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4655
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If you are the 3rd player and you have used Exploration "
"technology this turn to find out that an unrevealed Deep Space marker is "
"a Super Nova that will block your advance, you could play <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Smuggler's Route #96 #97</span> to remove the marker "
"from the board. Now the 4th player will have a chance to discard a Cancel"
" Card, then the 2nd, then the 1st. If your <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Smuggler's Route #96 #97</span> card is not canceled, then "
"remove the counter and start your movement.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4662
msgid "Replicators"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4671
msgid "Introduction & General Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4675
msgid ""
"Von-Neumann Machines – or Clanking Replicators – are self-replicating "
"machines that are called Replicators for short. They have their own "
"Empire Advantages (10.0) to choose from and they behave, research, and "
"reproduce differently than other Empires. Only one player may play as the"
" Replicators. The Replicator player fills out a simplified Production "
"Sheet and does not track the technology on their ships. When a player is "
"playing the Replicators, the following rules are never used:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4676
msgid "- Facilities (36.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4677
msgid "- Terraforming Nebulae (34.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4678
msgid "- Unique Ships (41.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4679
msgid "- Ship Experience (37.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4680
msgid "- Reaction Movement (35.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4681
msgid "- Space Amoebas ([SSB 3.0] and [CSB 10.0])"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4682
msgid ""
"- <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Blood Brothers alliances</span> (CSB "
"1.3.2)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4683
msgid "- Galactic Capitol (28.1)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4684
msgid "- Mission Cards (39.3.6)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4691
msgid "Replicators Characteristics"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4695
msgid "- Replicator ships may not be boarded (19.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4696
msgid "- Replicator Colonies may not be attacked via Ground Combat (21.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4697
msgid ""
"- The Replicator player may not use Colony Ships, Bases, <mark class"
"=\"hl-blue\">Starbases, Defense Satellite Networks</mark>, Shipyards, and"
" MS Pipelines."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4698
msgid ""
"- Replicators are eliminated by destroying the Replicator Homeworld, but "
"it is more likely that the outcome of the game will be obvious before "
"then."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4705
msgid "Barren Planets"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4709
msgid ""
"The Barren Planet in the non-Replicator player's Home System is not "
"considered barren. Because of this, the non-Replicator players, including"
" <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Immortals #44</span> (see the Card "
"Manifest) start with 10 CP in the bank."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4716
msgid "Replicator Starting Forces"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4720
msgid ""
"The Replicator Homeworld marker on its FULL side, one Flagship (if "
"playing with Flagships, 23.0) and five Type 0 ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4727
msgid "Movement & Colonization"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4731
msgid "Replicators move and explore the same as non-Replicator players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4738
msgid "Movement Tech"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4742
msgid ""
"All Replicator ships have Move 1 technology unless a higher level is "
"purchased (40.6.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4743
msgid ""
"Replicators automatically gain an extra level of Move technology during "
"Economic Phase 8 and Economic Phase 16 at no cost. This is indicated on "
"the Replicator Production Sheet. This does not prevent them from also "
"buying an extra Move technology during that phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4750
msgid "Colonies & Colony Growth"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4754
msgid ""
"Replicators are allowed to colonize both normal and Barren Planets "
"without the need for Terraforming technology. Any Replicator ship can "
"colonize a planet by removing the ship and placing a Colony marker on the"
" planet on the Colony Start side."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4755
msgid ""
"Replicator Colonies grow the same as non-Replicator Colonies. At the end "
"of the first Economic Phase following the formation of the Colony, a 1 "
"Colony growth marker will be placed on the Colony. Fully grown Replicator"
" Colonies have the word Full written on the counters instead of 5 (CP)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4756
msgid "Replicator Colonies still grow when blockaded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4763
msgid "Replicators Attacking Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4767
msgid ""
"Replicators can bombard and destroy Colonies from space (5.10). If they "
"successfully eliminate a Colony, one of the bombarding ships may "
"immediately be removed to form a Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4774
msgid "Attacking Replicator Colonies"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4778
msgid ""
"Replicator Colonies can never be completely destroyed by other players "
"without Anti-Replicator Technology. Replicator Planets cannot be invaded,"
" but Ground Combat is allowed in games with Replicators and multiple non-"
"Replicator players. If bombarded from space, they are reduced from 5 "
"(Full) to 3 to 1. If the Colony takes another hit, it is not removed, but"
" flipped back to the Colony Start side. <i>They are very persistent, "
"self-replicating machines that are hard to completely eliminate.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4779
msgid ""
"Titans will destroy both a planet and eliminate the Replicator Colony on "
"it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4786
msgid "Anti-Replicator Technology"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4790
msgid ""
"A player may research Anti-Replicator technology for 10 CP during any "
"Economic Phase. Once researched, all Transports (21.0) may be equipped "
"with it. A Transport equipped with Anti-Replicator technology that is "
"over a Replicator Colony at the Colony Start stage of growth may "
"eliminate the Colony. A Transport can move in with a friendly fleet and, "
"if the fleet bombs the Colony down to Start, it will destroy the Colony "
"during that planetary bombardment. The Transport can fire using its 1 "
"Attack Strength and use its Anti-Replicator Tech on the same bombardment."
" A Transport can be equipped with Anti-Replicator Technology and still "
"carry 6 Ground Units <mark class=\"hl-blue\">and/or Fighters</mark>. The "
"Replicator Homeworld is treated the same as a Replicator Colony for all "
"rules governing growth, blockade, bombardment, and destruction."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4797
msgid "Production & Depletion"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4806
msgid "Hull Production"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4810
msgid ""
"Replicator players do not collect income, research, pay maintenance, or "
"fill out a Production Sheet like other players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4811
msgid ""
"Each Economic Phase, every Replicator Colony that is at Full (including "
"the Homeworld), may produce any ship they are allowed to produce with a "
"Hull Size of 1 (i.e., one Hull Point) at that Colony. At start, this will"
" only be Type 0 ships. Colonies may produce ships even if blockaded as "
"long as they are at Full. <i>(Replicators do not collect material to a "
"central location to produce at Shipyards – they simply replicate where "
"they are located.)</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4812
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: The Replicator player has 7 Colonies at Full and are "
"currently able to produce Type 0, Type II ships, and Type PD. They decide"
" to produce Type II ships at 4 of the Colonies and Type PD ships at 3 of "
"the Colonies.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4813
msgid ""
"If the Replicators get to 12 Research Points (RP, 40.5), they may produce"
" an additional Hull Point on their Homeworld (for a total of two Hull "
"Size 1 ships or a single Hull Size 2 ship)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4814
msgid ""
"If a ship is produced at a blockaded planet, combat does not occur until "
"the combat phase of either the Replicator or the blockading player's "
"turn. No ship can leave a hex containing enemy ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4815
msgid ""
"To avoid confusion when doing production, it is recommended that the "
"Replicator player place one ship directly on each Full Colony and then go"
" back and adjust the markers on Colonies that are still growing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4822
msgid "Combining Replicator Ships"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4826
msgid ""
"Replicators build ships larger than Hull Size 1 by combining two ships "
"together. Two ships of Hull Size 1 can be combined to make a Hull Size 2 "
"ship. Three ships of Hull Size 1 or one ship of Hull Size 2 and one ship "
"of Hull Size 1 may be combined to make a Hull Size 3 ship. Larger ships "
"may similarly be split into smaller ships. A ship may also be changed "
"into a ship of a different ship type of the same Hull Size. The ships "
"that are combining or being changed can do so only if they start a turn "
"that is at a Colony that is at FULL growth and by not moving for one "
"turn. An unlimited number of ships may combine, split, or be changed to a"
" different type at any Colony that is at FULL growth."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4833
msgid "Colony Depletion – Economic Phase 10"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4837
msgid ""
"Replicators produce rapidly and quickly use up the resources of a planet."
" At the start of Economic Phase 10 (before producing ships) and in every "
"Economic Phase after that, the Full Colony closest to the Replicator Home"
" World is depleted. If two Full Colonies are equidistant to the Home "
"World, the Replicator player may choose which is depleted. When a Colony "
"is depleted, remove both the Colony and the planet from the board, the "
"planet is no longer significant or useful in game terms to any player "
"because all the resources have been removed from it. The Replicator "
"Homeworld is never depleted."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4838
msgid ""
"If there are no FULL Replicator Colonies, then the Replicator Colony "
"closest to the Homeworld is depleted, regardless of its stage of growth."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4845
msgid "The Replicator Homeworld"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4849
msgid ""
"This is treated exactly like any other Colony, except that it is never "
"Depleted and losing it will cost the Replicators the game. It does not "
"produce more than other Colonies unless the player is using the <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Replicator Capitol #65</span> Empire Advantage, "
"has accumulated 12 RP (40.5), or has paid to boost production (40.6.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4856
msgid "Combat"
msgstr "Combat au sol"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4860
msgid ""
"Replicator Type XIII & XV ships require 3 Hulls to build but take 4 "
"damage to destroy – this is indicated on the Replicators Production Sheet"
" where they are listed as 3(4). All Replicator ships of Hull Size 1 get "
"the same benefit as Fighters when attacking a Titan: they get +1 to their"
" Attack Strength, they receive the Fleet Size Bonus, and a roll of a 1 "
"results in a hit. They are not treated as Fighters in any other "
"circumstances."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4861
msgid ""
"Some Replicator ship types are equipped with Tactics 1, they have a 1 in "
"the top right counter corner as a reminder of this."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4868
msgid "Research"
msgstr "Ressources"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4872
msgid ""
"Replicators do not research like other players. Instead, they adapt and "
"react to the non-Replicator players. Their ships are not equipped with "
"technology except when specifically noted in the rules. Some Replicator "
"ships may have a special ability depending on their Empire Advantage "
"(10.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4879
msgid "Earning Research Points"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4883
msgid ""
"Research Points (RP) are tracked by marking off the boxes found on the "
"Replicator Production Sheet. Each box is worth 1 RP. They can be earned "
"in the following ways:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4884
msgid ""
"- Every time the Replicator player encounters something (40.5.4) listed "
"under the Things Encountered section on their Production Sheet, the "
"appropriate box is marked. Anything not specified on the Production Sheet"
" yields no Research Points (e.g. Tactics 1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4885
msgid "- RP can be purchased directly using CP (40.6.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4886
msgid ""
"- Starting the game with the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Advanced "
"Research #64</span> Empire Advantage (see the Card Manifest) provides 1 "
"RP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4887
msgid ""
"- 1 RP is earned the first time the Replicator player has combat with "
"Non-Player Aliens (18.0)/a Space Pirate (25.7), or a Doomsday Machine "
"(29.0). They do NOT earn RP for the Tactics technology. 1 RP is also "
"earned for each Space Wreck found (see below). A combined maximum of 3 RP"
" may be gained from these sources as is indicated on the Production "
"Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4888
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: The Replicator Player has already encountered a Space Pirate "
"and two Space Wrecks. It therefore would not gain an RP from fighting a "
"Doomsday Machine.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4889
msgid ""
"When the Replicator player is able to mark a box in one of the Things "
"Encountered sections, all boxes above it in the same section may also be"
"  marked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4890
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: The Replicators encounter a BC, but previously had only "
"encountered SCs. The DD and CA boxes may be marked off as well as the BC "
"box.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4891
msgid ""
"Total RP can be tracked by marking numbers in the Total Research Points "
"Accumulated section of the Replicator Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4892
msgid ""
"Space Pirates that are under Replicator control do not gain RP for the "
"Replicators unless a friendly Replicator ship/Colony is in the same hex "
"as them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4899
msgid "Space Wrecks"
msgstr "Aides de jeu - Planètes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4903
msgid ""
"Replicator ships that enter the same hex as a Space Wreck immediately "
"gain 1 RP and the Space Wreck is removed. If enemy ships are in the hex "
"the Replicators must win the combat to pick up the Space Wreck. The "
"Replicators do not have to stop their movement to pick up the Space "
"Wreck."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4904
msgid ""
"After getting the 3 RP that are allowed from first combats and Space "
"Wrecks, Replicator ships will still remove any Space Wrecks they "
"encounter (40.5.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4911
msgid "15 RP Max"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4915
msgid ""
"Replicators may only have a total of 15 RP. Any boxes checked off over 15"
" do not add to the RP total."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4916
msgid ""
"Research Points are not spent. They represent a threshold that must be "
"passed before a ship type may be built. Once the threshold is passed, "
"existing ships may be converted to that type starting on the Replicator "
"player's next turn (40.3.2). The player does not need to wait until the "
"next Economic Phase to upgrade existing ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4923
msgid "Encountering Technology"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4927
msgid ""
"Ships and technology are considered encountered if they are present in a "
"battle – even if screened or if they bombard a Replicator Colony. For "
"Colony bombardment, this rule applies even for a unit that does not fire "
"at the Colony. This also applies to Attack technology in Asteroids and "
"Defense and Cloaking technology in Nebulae."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4934
msgid "Construction Points (CP)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4938
msgid ""
"Replicators normally start the game with 0 CP, but if any rule provides "
"players with CP to start the game the Replicator player also gains these "
"CP. They can only earn CP by gathering Minerals, discarding Resource "
"Cards (39.0), and turning in Alien Technology Cards (40.6.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4949
msgid ""
"Replicator ships that enter the same hex as a Mineral counter immediately"
" gain the CP for the Minerals and the counter is removed. If enemy ships "
"are in the hex the Replicators must win the combat to pick up the "
"Minerals. The Replicators do not have to stop their movement to pick up "
"the Minerals if no enemy ships are present."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4956
msgid "Alien Technology Cards and Replicators"
msgstr "Technologies Alien"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4960
msgid ""
"Replicators do not utilize Alien Technology Cards (11.0) like other "
"Empires. When the Replicator player earns one of these cards it is "
"discarded, providing the player with 10 CP. For play balance reasons, if "
"playing with both the Replicators and Alien Technology Cards, Non-Player "
"Aliens must also be used (18.0). As the Replicator only needs one card to"
" turn in for CP, they only draw one card instead of two."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4967
msgid "Spending CP"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4971
msgid "During the Economic Phase, CP can be spent on any of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4972
msgid "- Bidding for turn order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4973
msgid ""
"- Purchasing a Research Point for 30 CP each. This can only be done once "
"per Economic Phase. The Replicators may purchase a maximum of 5 RP per "
"game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4974
msgid ""
"- Researching Exploration technology at a cost of 15 CP. Once researched,"
" the ship type Exp (40.7.4) may be built. This can only be purchased if "
"all Replicator Home System Markers are revealed or an enemy unit has "
"entered the Replicator's Home System. In a game where the player's Home "
"System and Deep Space System markers are randomly mixed together, this "
"restriction does not apply. The Flagship is upgraded with Exploration "
"technology if it is researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4975
msgid ""
"- Researching PD, Scan, or Sweep without having to first encounter these "
"technologies for 15 CP each. More than one of these technologies may be "
"researched in the same Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4976
msgid ""
"- Researching the next level of Movement technology for 20 CP, only once "
"per Economic Phase. All Replicators instantly upgrade to the new level."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4977
msgid ""
"- Paying 8 CP once per Economic Phase to allow the Homeworld to boost "
"ship production by 1 Hull. This allows for a total production of two Hull"
" Size 1 ships or a single Hull Size 2 ship. This production boost must be"
" used in the Economic Phase during which it was purchased. If used with "
"some combination of Resource Cards <span class=\"text-uppercase\">#70 #71"
" #72 #73 #74 #75</span>, the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Replicator "
"Capitol #65</span> Empire Advantage Card, or the possession of 12 RP, "
"this may allow for the production of multiple Hulls at once. Four hulls "
"could be produced as:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4978
msgid "   - 4x Hull Size 1 ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4979
msgid "   - 1x Hull Size 3 ship and 1x Hull Size 1 ship"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4980
msgid "   - 2x Hull Size 2 ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4981
msgid "   - 2x Hull Size 1 ships and 1x Hull Size 2 ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4988
msgid "Carrying Over CP"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4992
msgid ""
"There is no limit to the CP that the Replicators can carry over between "
"Economic Phases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:4999
msgid "Ship Types"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5003
msgid ""
"Point Defense, Scanner, and Minesweeper technologies/ships are handled "
"differently than the Replicator's other technologies. They are not based "
"on Research Points (although encountering a Fighter, Raider, or Mine may "
"give RP). Instead, these technologies are unlocked for the Replicator "
"player after Fighters, Cloaking, and Mines are encountered respectively. "
"The player does not need to wait until the next Economic Phase to mark "
"these off on their Production Sheet. Alternatively, these technologies "
"may be purchased during an Economic Phase, allowing the Replicator player"
" to build or convert other ships into PD, Scan, and SW ship types prior "
"to having encountered such a ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5004
msgid ""
"A cloaked Unit that moves into the hex of a Replicator Colony allows the "
"research of the Scan Ship. A cloaked Unit that uses Cloak to avoid combat"
" by using their retreat advantage (16.1.2) will only allow the Replicator"
" Player to check off the Scan box."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5005
msgid ""
"If a Replicator fleet is wiped out by Mines before battle, they may "
"research Minesweepers, but do not get any RP for things they would have "
"encountered had the battle proceeded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5012
msgid "Point Defense Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5016
msgid ""
"The PD ship type is equipped with technology which is equivalent to Point"
" Defense 1 (15.3). It fires at A6 versus Fighters and E1 versus all other"
" ship types. Once the Replicator player's PD ships have destroyed 3 "
"Fighters, their PDs improve to A7 against Fighters. This does not occur "
"until their next turn after destroying the third Fighter; their PDs "
"remain at A6 against Fighters until then. The destroyed Fighters can be "
"marked off on their Production Sheet. The Fighters destroyed by PDs do "
"not have to be destroyed in the same battle. Fighters destroyed by other "
"Replicator ships do not count towards this."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5023
msgid "Scanner Ships"
msgstr "Cartes"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5027
msgid ""
"The Scanner ship type is equipped with technology equivalent to Scanner 2"
" (16.2). It fires as C6 versus units equipped with Cloaking technology "
"and E1 versus all other ship types. Scanner ships are Hull Size 2; see "
"[40.3.1] for information on building restrictions."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5034
msgid "Sweeper Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5038
msgid ""
"The Sweeper ship type is equivalent to a Minesweeper 1 ship (17.1). Once "
"the Replicator player has swept 3 Mines their SWs improve to Sweeper 2. "
"This does not occur until their next turn after sweeping the third Mine; "
"their SWs remain at Sweeper 1 until then. The swept Mines can be marked "
"off on their Production Sheet. The Mines swept do not have to be swept in"
" the same battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5039
msgid ""
"If the opponent has the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Minesweep Jammer "
"#24</span> Alien Technology Card (see the Card Manifest), any two SWs at "
"Sweeper 1 can sweep 1 Mine. Once the SWs have Sweeper 2 they will be able"
" to sweep one Mine per SW."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5046
msgid "Exploration Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5050
msgid ""
"The Exp ship type is equipped with Exploration 1 (9.8) once it has been "
"researched. Exploration ships are Hull Size 2; see [40.3.1] for "
"information on building restrictions."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5057
msgid "Replicator Flagship"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5061
msgid ""
"The Replicator Flagship (C-64) has the following stats at start: B1-1-x3,"
" Tactics 1 (noted in the upper right corner of the counter) and Move 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5062
msgid ""
"- Its Movement technology will increase with each level of Movement "
"technology that the Replicator player buys, like any other Replicator "
"ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5063
msgid ""
"- Its Attack Strength will increase with every Research Point that the "
"Replicator player gains after the first one. Once the Replicator player "
"has at least 1 RP the Strength is equal to the number of RP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5064
msgid ""
"- Its Defense Strength will increase by every 5 Research Points the "
"Replicator player gains."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5065
msgid ""
"- It will be refitted with Exploration technology as soon as it is "
"researched (40.6.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5066
msgid ""
"The Attack/Defense Strengths increase at the end of any turn they are "
"gained in."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5067
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: The Replicator player has encountered an Enemy CA and has 3 "
"RP as a result (because they are able to check the CA box as well as both"
" boxes to its left – see example in [40.5.1]). The Replicator Flagship is"
" now a B3-1-x3 unit. The Replicator player now has a battle where the "
"enemy has 2 BCs and 3 DDs. The enemy has Attack 1 and Defense 1 on some "
"of these ships. The Replicator player will gain 4 RP from this fight: One"
" for Ship Size (BC), one for Fleet Size Bonus (5 ships), and one each for"
" Attack 1 and Defense 1. After this battle is over the Replicator "
"Flagship will be a B7-2-x3 unit.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5068
msgid ""
"The Flagship tops out at B15-4-x3. The Replicator player cannot decide to"
" not upgrade the Flagship in an attempt to conceal their RP Total. The "
"Replicator Flagship cannot be broken down into smaller ships or changed "
"into a Type XIII/XV. It can be used to colonize a planet; however, it can"
" never be replaced if removed in this way or destroyed in any way."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5069
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: Turn order is Blue, Replicators and then Red. Blue goes "
"first. Replicators have 3 RP and their Flagship at B3-1-x3. Blue fights "
"the Replicators, and the Replicators gain 1 RP. At the very end of Blue's"
" turn, the Replicator Flagship will go up to B4-1-x3. During their turn, "
"the Replicators find a Space Wreck and fight Red, gaining 2 RP from the "
"combat. At the very end of the Replicators' turn, the Replicator Flagship"
" will go up to B7-2-x3. During Red's turn, Red attacks the Replicators "
"and the Flagship will be B7-2-x3 for the fight. The Replicators gain no "
"RP from this fight, so if the Flagship fights any battles with Blue "
"during Blue's next turn it will do so as a B7-2-x3 unit.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5076
msgid "Replicators Strategy"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5080
msgid ""
"A game with Replicators will play very differently – That was the goal! "
"Each player will have two forces pulling them in opposite directions:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5081
msgid ""
"- The non-Replicator player will want to hang back and hide their "
"technology, knowing that showing technology to the Replicator merely "
"makes the Replicator stronger. However, since the Replicator pays no "
"maintenance, hanging back too long is suicidal. Eventually the Replicator"
" would come with such a large fleet that defeat would be inevitable."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5082
msgid ""
"- Because of this, the Replicator player will also want to hang back and "
"amass as big a fleet as possible. However, they have to push forward to "
"get RP. Some ships have to be sacrificed in order to get technology. Deep"
" Space also becomes much more valuable. CP is precious, and Minerals are "
"easy to grab. Not to mention that it is so easy to colonize Deep Space "
"planets. It is not uncommon for every Deep Space hex to be explored."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5083
msgid ""
"In general, the non-Replicator player has three possible winning courses "
"of action:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5084
msgid ""
"- Throw curve balls at the Replicators – Fighters, Mines, Raiders – in "
"order to keep them away while not giving up too many RP, massing and "
"revealing a large technology leap all at once."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5085
msgid ""
"- Race to Titans as fast as possible, even at the expense of other "
"technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5086
msgid ""
"- Top out around DD and stay there, trying to <i>permanently</i> starve "
"the Replicator player of RP. This does not work in multiplayer games and "
"can be defeated by a Replicator player who maximizes RP purchasing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5087
msgid ""
"In either case, the goal is to hit the Replicators with a big enough "
"technology jump, close enough to their planets, that you can get in and "
"do some damage. Remember that time is on the side of the non-Replicator "
"player because eventually Replicator planets start to deplete."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5094
msgid "Balancing Replicators"
msgstr "Équipages Replicator"

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5098
msgid ""
"While we did our best to create an Empire that was completely different, "
"but still balanced across all the possible configurations, <i>we "
"recognize that is really an impossible task</i> – especially when you "
"consider the differing skill levels and play styles of groups. Once "
"experienced, we encourage players to bid to play the Replicators, with "
"the bid being the amount of CP added or subtracted from the Replicators "
"(a bid of +20 would mean that the Replicators get 20 CP to start the game"
" while a bid of -10 would mean that they started with -10 CP – they would"
" have to collect 10 CP before reaching zero). The player that bids the "
"lowest gets to play the Replicators. While the Replicators are not an "
"easy Empire to play, we can see them being given to a new player for them"
" to learn the game since there is no technology tracking for ships and "
"fewer technology decisions to make. In such a case, WE STRONGLY SUGGEST "
"that player is given:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5099
msgid "- An extra ship at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5100
msgid "- 2 Replicator Empire Advantages (they keep both of their cards)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5101
msgid "- 20 extra CP to start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5102
msgid ""
"A seasoned Space Empires player will still likely win, but this will make"
" the game much more fun for the newbie."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5109
msgid "Unique Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5113
msgid ""
"Each player has six Unique Ship counters. After drawing Empire Advantages"
" (10.0), but before the start of the game, each player designs a ship for"
" that counter (see below). All six Unique Ship counters use that same "
"design. These Unique Ships can be purchased (if the player's current "
"technology level allows) and used and have their technology upgraded like"
" any other ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5114
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-beige\">DESIGN NOTE: Unique Ships will not be a \"better"
" deal\" cost-wise when compared to SCs, DDs, etc. However, they will "
"allow you to spring some surprises on your opponent.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5121
msgid "Designing Unique Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5130
msgid "Initial Design"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5134
msgid ""
"The initial design for an Empire's Unique Ship must be completed before "
"the start of the game. To design a Unique Ship, consult Unique Tables 2 "
"and 3 (pp.44-45). Values that are not on the table cannot be selected. "
"Everything added to the ship design increases the building cost of the "
"ship. When the design is complete, write the values on the Ship "
"Technology Sheet right above the Groups for the Unique Ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5141
msgid "Redesign"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5145
msgid ""
"The design of an Empire's Unique Ship may be changed any time there are "
"no Unique Ships currently built. A player may scuttle ships in order to "
"do this (7.3.2). However, it costs 5 CP to create a new Unique Ship "
"design."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5152
msgid "Special Abilities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5156
msgid ""
"In addition to Weapon Class, Attack, Defense, and Hull Size, each Unique "
"Ship may have up to two special abilities. When choosing special "
"abilities, the same ability may not be selected twice (a ship may not "
"have two Mini-Fighter Bays, for example). Special abilities of a Unique "
"Ships are revealed in combat like other technologies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5167
msgid "The following restrictions apply to purchasing and upgrading Unique Ships:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5168
msgid ""
"- May not be purchased until the Ship Size (9.4) technology has been "
"researched that would allow their build. This is determined by the CP "
"cost of the ship – see Unique Ship Table 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5169
msgid ""
"  <i>EXAMPLE: A Unique Ship that costs 12 CP or less can be built when "
"Ship Size technology 3 is researched.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5170
msgid ""
"- If designed with a technology that must be researched (PD, Scanners, "
"Exploration, Fast BC), then that technology must be researched before the"
" ship may be built."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5171
msgid ""
"- May only upgrade their Attack and Defense technology up to their Hull "
"Size."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5172
msgid ""
"- <mark class=\"hl-blue\">All Unique Ships must have a minimum cost of 5 "
"CP. Unique Ships that carry Exploration Technology must have a minimum "
"cost of 9 CP.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5179
msgid "React Ability"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5183
msgid "All Unique Ships get the React ability at Move 5 (35.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5190
msgid "Hull Size Adjustments"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5194
msgid ""
"A player using either the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race "
"#34</span> or <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span> Empire"
" Advantages (see the Card Manifest) has the Hull Size of their Unique "
"Ship design adjusted like any other ship. If both the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Giant Race #34</span> and the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span> designed a Unique Ship with a Hull Size"
" of 2, they would both pay 4 CP for that in their design. However, the "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race #34</span> would get a ship "
"with a Hull Size of 3 and the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids "
"#43</span> would get a ship with a Hull Size of 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5201
msgid "Weapon Class Requirement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5205
msgid ""
"After adding up the cost of the Unique Ship, its Weapon Class may have to"
" be adjusted up, with a corresponding increase in price. Unique Ships "
"that cost 10+ CP must at least mount a D-Class Weapon. Unique Ships that "
"cost 20+ CP must at least mount a C-Class Weapon. Unique Ships that cost "
"30+ CP must at least mount a B-Class Weapon. If a mandatory Weapon Class "
"upgrade puts the ship in the next bracket, keep upgrading."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/master_rule_book.py:5206
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If a player designed a Unique Ship that was E6-1-x1 it would "
"cost 12 CP. They would then have to upgrade its Weapon to D-Class and its"
" cost to 13 CP.</i>"
msgstr ""

